{"id": "3418", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3418", "title": "Orcs", "text": " are one of the &lt;a href=\"Seven%20Races\"&gt;seven sentient races&lt;/a&gt; of &lt;a href=\"Rivellon\"&gt;Rivellon&lt;/a&gt;. They reside in the deserts of &lt;a href=\"Yuthul%20Gor\"&gt;Yuthul Gor&lt;/a&gt;, and don't usually venture into other territories.\nBackground.\nCreated and slaved by the god &lt;a href=\"Vrogir\"&gt;Vrogir&lt;/a&gt;, the orcs were his control his departure from Rivellon with the other &lt;a href=\"Seven%20Gods\"&gt;gods&lt;/a&gt;. In Rivellon's ancient history the cycle of enslavement continued: Orcs were not considered sapient, and were often enslaved by the other races; the &lt;a href=\"Council%20of%20Seven\"&gt;Council of Six&lt;/a&gt; even once voted on a motion that would allow the use of orc meat as emergency rations. Eventually, they would be recognized as a sapient race and given a seat on the Council.\nEven after their recognition, they were manipulated or enslaved; in 4 AR they were manipulated by the &lt;a href=\"Immaculattes\"&gt;Immaculattes&lt;/a&gt; and used as the physical army for the \"religious\" group and most recently, enslaved by the &lt;a href=\"Black%20Ring\"&gt;Black Ring&lt;/a&gt; to lead their armies in &lt;a href=\"Ferol\"&gt;Ferol&lt;/a&gt; as part of their plan to revive the god &lt;a href=\"Chaos\"&gt;Chaos&lt;/a&gt; in 1218 AD.\nAlthough they have been seen on the side of the aggressor, the orcs have also aligned themselves with the other sentient races. In 611 AD, &lt;a href=\"Go-Dar\"&gt;Go-Dar&lt;/a&gt; joined the other races as the orc representative to the League of Seven (a precursor to the Council of Seven) at &lt;a href=\"Stormfist%20Castle\"&gt;Stormfist Castle&lt;/a&gt; against Chaos and the League of the Damned (the precursor to the Black Ring).\nCulture.\nOrcish culture is based heavily around honour, to the point that a perceived insult to an orc's honour is enough to start a fight to the death. As the orc clans all have vastly different standards of behaviour, resulting much of their being time fighting amongst themselves; many of their interactions will have one clan take offence at what another clan thought was a harmless act.\nOn rare occasions, the Orc clans will unite in an attempt to attack other civilizations. Historically, this has often been the work of some third party manipulating them for their own ends. If the Orcs discover this, they may turn against the third party, as the deception would be considered an insult (such as the case with &lt;a href=\"Kroxy\"&gt;Kroxy&lt;/a&gt;). When warring with other civilizations, the Orcs will often try to outnumber their opponents or use guerrilla tactics to disrupt their activities."}
{"id": "17894", "revid": "27868532", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=17894", "title": "Orcs (Divine Divinity)", "text": "In 1218 AD, orcs have left their homeland or &lt;a href=\"Yuthul%20Gor\"&gt;Yuthul Gor&lt;/a&gt; under the direction of the &lt;a href=\"Black%20Ring\"&gt;Black Ring&lt;/a&gt; to assault the human lands of &lt;a href=\"Ferol\"&gt;Ferol&lt;/a&gt;. Although the bulk of the forces have been held back at the &lt;a href=\"orc%20camp\"&gt;orc camp&lt;/a&gt; to the east of the &lt;a href=\"destroyed%20village\"&gt;destroyed village&lt;/a&gt;, small pockets have managed to circumvent &lt;a href=\"Captain%20Mitox\"&gt;Captain Mitox&lt;/a&gt;'s forces and infiltrated the human lands as far as &lt;a href=\"Aleroth\"&gt;Aleroth&lt;/a&gt; in the north west.\nVariants.\nOrc Warrior.\nThe orc warrior is the basic orc melee fighter and forms the backbone of the orc war machine. Orc warriors are simple, sturdy and relentless. A single orc warrior is a generally simple task to handle.\nOrc Drummer.\nThis version is found at the gold trap near &lt;a href=\"Aleroth\"&gt;Aleroth&lt;/a&gt;. Due high health and regenerative drum, it can pose challenge.\nOrc Chief.\nThis variant is found at the camp near ladder to &lt;a href=\"Smiruk\"&gt;Smiruk&lt;/a&gt;. It can pose a challenge.\nHeavy Wardrummer.\nWardrummers heal nearby orcs and tend to flee melee range, making them hard foe to defeat.\nOrc Shaman.\nShamans can summon orc warriors and crossbow orcs. These summoned ones won't disappear even if shaman is killed.\nBerserk Orc Archer.\nVariant found at elevated area south of the destroyed village.\nBereserk Orc Warrior.\nVariant found at elevated area south of the destroyed village."}
{"id": "16234", "revid": "49426621", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=16234", "title": "Order for Grain", "text": " is a &lt;a href=\"Divine%20Divinity%20books%20and%20notes\"&gt;note&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Divine%20Divinity\"&gt;Divine Divinity&lt;/a&gt;\"."}
{"id": "4529", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4529", "title": "Order of the Viper Belt", "text": " is a &lt;a href=\"Dragon%20Knight%20Saga%20Accessories%23Belts\"&gt;special belt&lt;/a&gt; in \"\".\nDescription.\nOrder of the Viper belt is a special belt that are part of the &lt;a href=\"Order%20of%20the%20Viper%20Set\"&gt;Order of the Viper Set&lt;/a&gt;. The whole set can be found across &lt;a href=\"Aleroth\"&gt;Aleroth&lt;/a&gt; and is consisted of &lt;a href=\"Order%20of%20the%20Viper%20Helmet\"&gt;helmet&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Order%20of%20the%20Viper%20Cuirass\"&gt;cuirass&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Order%20of%20the%20Viper%20Bracers\"&gt;bracers&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Order%20of%20the%20Viper%20Leggings\"&gt;leggings&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Order%20of%20the%20Viper%20Belt\"&gt;belt&lt;/a&gt;. It requires atleast level 35 in order to be worn. When worn the belt will boost &lt;a href=\"Strength\"&gt;Strength&lt;/a&gt; attribute by 5 points, Hitpoints by 60 points, HP Regeneration by 0.1 point, Mana by 58 points, Mana Regeneration by 0.09 points and Critical Chance by 5 points. Furthermore it will grant its wearer 5 points in &lt;a href=\"Life%20Leech%20%28Dragon%20Knight%20Saga%29\"&gt;Life Leech&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Dragon%20Knight%20Saga%20Skills\"&gt;skill&lt;/a&gt;. The belt has 1 charm slot and 2 enchantment slots. \nHow to Obtain.\nCan be obtained from the body of champion general &lt;a href=\"Luxurius\"&gt;Luxurius&lt;/a&gt; at &lt;a href=\"Luxurius%27%20Mansion\"&gt;Luxurius' Mansion&lt;/a&gt;. The house is accessed during the quest &lt;a href=\"Beauty%20And%20The%20Beast\"&gt;Beauty And The Beast&lt;/a&gt;. \nSet Properties.\nOrder of the Viper Belt is a part of the set Order of the Viper Set which allows the item to gain additional, potentially increasing, properties the more items of the same set are worn. Order of the Viper Belt primary increased attribute is Magic Armour Rating, which is firstly gained by equipping 2 items from the set, and then increased by equipping more items from the set. "}
{"id": "4527", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4527", "title": "Order of the Viper Bracers", "text": " are a &lt;a href=\"Dragon%20Knight%20Saga%20Armour%23Unique%20Armour%20List\"&gt;special bracers&lt;/a&gt; in \"\".\nDescription.\nOrder of the Viper Bracers are a special bracers that are part of the &lt;a href=\"Order%20of%20the%20Viper%20Set\"&gt;Order of the Viper Set&lt;/a&gt;. The whole set can be found across &lt;a href=\"Aleroth\"&gt;Aleroth&lt;/a&gt; and is consisted of &lt;a href=\"Order%20of%20the%20Viper%20Helmet\"&gt;helmet&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Order%20of%20the%20Viper%20Cuirass\"&gt;cuirass&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Order%20of%20the%20Viper%20Bracers\"&gt;bracers&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Order%20of%20the%20Viper%20Leggings\"&gt;leggings&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Order%20of%20the%20Viper%20Belt\"&gt;belt&lt;/a&gt;. It requires atleast level 35 in order to be worn. When worn the bracers will boost &lt;a href=\"Spirit\"&gt;Spirit&lt;/a&gt; attribute by 7 points and Ranged Armour Rating by 5 points. Furthermore it will grant its wearer 5 points in &lt;a href=\"Fatality\"&gt;Fatality&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Dragon%20Knight%20Saga%20Skills\"&gt;skill&lt;/a&gt;. The bracers have 1 charm slot and 2 enchantments slots. \nHow to Obtain.\nChest in the secret room in the &lt;a href=\"Playhouse%20Cellar\"&gt;Playhouse Cellar&lt;/a&gt;. It can be found by pressing secret button can be found on the desk in the cellar.\nSet Properties.\nOrder of the Viper Bracers is a part of the set Order of the Viper Set which allows the item to gain additional, potentially increasing, properties the more items of the same set are worn. Order of the Viper Bracers primary increased attribute is &lt;a href=\"Strength\"&gt;Strength&lt;/a&gt;, which is firstly gained by equipping 2 items from the set, and then increased by equipping more items from the set. "}
