{"id": "21970", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=21970", "title": "Original Sin 2 Class Builds", "text": ""}
{"id": "10496", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=10496", "title": "Original Sin 2 Classes", "text": "The classes, commonly referred to as class builds, are specialisations of the &lt;a href=\"Companions%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;companions&lt;/a&gt; and the player character in \"\". \nOverview.\nClasses in this game are broken down into three groups, depending on their focus and playstyle, the groups are: \"warrior\", \"mage\" and \"survivor\". The classes are chosen at the character creation, when recruiting &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Companions\"&gt;origin companion&lt;/a&gt; and when &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Companions%23Recruiting%20Mercenaries\"&gt;hiring mercenaries&lt;/a&gt;. \nChoosing character class is one of the crucial aspects when creating a character and choosing companion. It defines their starting &lt;a href=\"Attributes%20and%20Abilities%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;attributes&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Attributes%20and%20Abilities%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;abilities&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Talents\"&gt;talents&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Skills\"&gt;spells or skills&lt;/a&gt; and their potential &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Items\"&gt;items&lt;/a&gt; and equipment. During character creation, the player can customise and combine abilities, attributes, talents and skills as they wish regardless of chosen preset class. \nIt should be noted however that preset classes are not permanent choice and can be altered at &lt;a href=\"the%20Lady%20Vengeance\"&gt;the Lady Vengeance&lt;/a&gt; through the course of the game itself. The classes themselves are not rigid, so it is possible to combine all sorts of &lt;a href=\"Attributes%20and%20Abilities%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;attributes, abilities&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Skills\"&gt;skills&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Talents\"&gt;talents&lt;/a&gt; as desired. If gift bag Fort Joy Magic Mirror is activated a Magic Mirror identical to one at Lady Vengeance will appear at &lt;a href=\"Arena%20of%20Fort%20Joy\"&gt;Arena of Fort Joy&lt;/a&gt;. This will allow to customize attributes and abilities of origin characters before reaching the Lady Vengeance. Note that activating any gift bag disables achievements.\nCreating Custom Classes.\nDespite being required to choose a preset class, it is possible to completely change character's abilities, attributes and skills in the character creation menu and at the Magic Mirror. The skills, abilities, stats and talents can be combined however the player wishes (provided the prerequisite abilities are met in some cases). For best effectiveness however it is advised to focus on only one type of damage in order to destroy the armour of enemies as soon as possible. Note however, that some enemies have resistances to certain types of damage (often elemental resistance and very rarely physical resistance) and therefore when focusing on one type of damage the player should have a back-up means of dealing different kind of damage in case of encountering resilient enemies. \nRegardless of enemy resistance, stripping enemies of their armour as fast as possible is crucial in order to win combat. Enemies without armour can be affected by status effects and therefore forced to skip turns or temporarily switch sides. Outside of damage affecting attributes (Intelligence, Strength and Finesse) it is important to invest points in Memory and Wits. Memory provides slots for additional active skills and spells character may use in combat. Wits affects critical chance and most importantly of all initiative which is used to determine who gets to act first in combat. Having greater wits that your opponents may prove crucial should their damage output be higher than yours. \nLastly it should be noted, that in spite of some classes and abilities having greater effectiveness (damage-wise), the game can be completed with any chosen preset class or custom created class with different combinations of stats. \nPreset Classes.\nMage classes.\nMages are primarily magic users who rely on their &lt;a href=\"Intelligence\"&gt;Intelligence&lt;/a&gt; attribute in order to survive and accomplish their goals. Their primary weapons are mostly one handed wands, two handed staves or occasionally daggers. They mainly focus on destroying magic armour of their enemies which protects them from elemental and magic induced status effects. \nThe Cleric is a mage, who harnesses the powers of &lt;a href=\"Necromancer%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Necromancy&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Hydrosophist%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Hydrosophy&lt;/a&gt; to decimate their enemies and heal their allies. Their primary weapons are a one-handed mace, axe or sword and a shield. Their primary attributes are &lt;a href=\"Strength\"&gt;Strength&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Intelligence\"&gt;Intelligence&lt;/a&gt;. Their combat abilities are further supported by their innate talent &lt;a href=\"Talents%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Hot Head&lt;/a&gt; which increases their critical chance by +10% critical chance as well as their accuracy by + 10%. This talent works however only when they are at their maximum Vitality. \nThe cleric starts with &lt;a href=\"Decaying%20Touch%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Decaying Touch&lt;/a&gt; which is a necromancer skill, dealing physical damage up close and applying decay if the target does not have \"physical armour\". Second starting necromancer skill is the &lt;a href=\"Blood%20Sucker%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Blood Sucker&lt;/a&gt; which allows its user to absorb the blood surface on which they stand in order to heal themselves. The last skill clerics have from start is the hydrosophist skill &lt;a href=\"Restoration%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Restoration&lt;/a&gt; which allows them to heal themselves and their allies. \nOutside combat they may utilise their &lt;a href=\"Bartering%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Bartering&lt;/a&gt; civil skill in order to make their dealings with traders easier.\nConjurer is a mage who relies on the power of &lt;a href=\"Summoning\"&gt;Summoning&lt;/a&gt; magic and their &lt;a href=\"Leadership\"&gt;Leadership&lt;/a&gt; skill in order to lead their summoned creatures. Their primary weapons are elemental wands in one hand and shield in the other. Their primary attributes are &lt;a href=\"Constitution\"&gt;Constitution&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Intelligence\"&gt;Intelligence&lt;/a&gt; which are needed to wield said weapons. \nTheir civil ability is &lt;a href=\"Loremaster\"&gt;Loremaster&lt;/a&gt; which allows them not only to identify the properties of found equipment but also to identify strengths and weaknesses of their enemies before engaging them. \nThis identification goes in hand with their starting skills. Their spell &lt;a href=\"Conjure%20Incarnate\"&gt;Conjure Incarnate&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Elemental%20Totem\"&gt;Elemental Totem&lt;/a&gt; allows them to summon said incarnate and totem on any surface in their vicinity. This allows them to conjure water totem to attack their fiery enemies, or blood incarnate to decimate their physically weak foes. Should Conjurer find themselves short of surfaces they may use their final starting spell &lt;a href=\"Dimensional%20Bolt\"&gt;Dimensional Bolt&lt;/a&gt; in order to attack their enemies at distance and create random surface beneath them. \nTheir talent is &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Talents\"&gt;Pet Pal&lt;/a&gt; which allows them to communicate with all sorts of animals in order to learn potentially useful information. \nEnchanter is a mage who are focused on &lt;a href=\"Aerotheurge%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Aerotheurge&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Hydrosophist%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Hydrosophist&lt;/a&gt; magic in order to support their allies. Their primary attributes are &lt;a href=\"Intelligence\"&gt;Intelligence&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Constitution\"&gt;Constitution&lt;/a&gt; which they need in order to wield their chosen weapon, a two-handed staff. Their combat abilities are further boosted by their talent &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Talents\"&gt;Far Out Man&lt;/a&gt; which increases the range of their spells by 2 meters. \nThe Enchanters startings spells are &lt;a href=\"Electric%20Discharge\"&gt;Electric Discharge&lt;/a&gt; which in combination with their second starting spell &lt;a href=\"Rain\"&gt;Rain&lt;/a&gt; can deal great air damage and potentially stun their Wet enemies. Their third and last starting skill is &lt;a href=\"Restoration%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Restoration&lt;/a&gt; which allows them to heal their allies and damage undead enemies.\nCivil ability of the Enchanter is &lt;a href=\"Loremaster\"&gt;Loremaster&lt;/a&gt; which allows them to identify properties of found gear and the weaknesses of their enemies. \nOut of all companions &lt;a href=\"Lohse\"&gt;Lohse&lt;/a&gt; is the one who chooses this specialisation by default. \nWitch is a mage who deals in &lt;a href=\"Necromancer%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Necromancy&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Scoundrel%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Scoundrel&lt;/a&gt; skills. Their primary attributes are &lt;a href=\"Intelligence\"&gt;Intelligence&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Finesse\"&gt;Finesse&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Constitution\"&gt;Constitution&lt;/a&gt;. Their primary weapon is a dagger. \nThe witches starting spells and skills are &lt;a href=\"Mosquito%20Swarm\"&gt;Mosquito Swarm&lt;/a&gt;, an offensive necromancer spell that summons mosquitos at their enemies. This spell is particularly useful in combination with the Witches talent &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Talents\"&gt;Leech&lt;/a&gt;, due to bleeding effect the spell causes and potential healing they may get if they stand upon the spilled blood. Their second starting spell is &lt;a href=\"Raise%20Bloated%20Corpse\"&gt;Raise Bloated Corpse&lt;/a&gt; which allows them to raise any fallen body to do their bidding. Their final third skill is &lt;a href=\"Chloroform\"&gt;Chloroform&lt;/a&gt; which allows the Witch to destroy magical armour and put their enemies to sleep at distance.\nOutside combat the Witches can use their civil skill &lt;a href=\"Persuasion\"&gt;Persuasion&lt;/a&gt; to achieve their goals. \nWizard is a mage specialising in &lt;a href=\"Geomancer%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Geomancer&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Pyrokinetic%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Pyrokinetic&lt;/a&gt; magic. Their primary attributes are &lt;a href=\"Intelligence\"&gt;Intelligence&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Constitution\"&gt;Constitution&lt;/a&gt;. Their primary weapons are wands.\nThe Wizards starting spells are &lt;a href=\"Fossil%20Strike\"&gt;Fossil Strike&lt;/a&gt; that allows them to hurl a chunk of earth at their enemies, creating oil surface beneath them. Afterwards they may set them on fire either by throwing their &lt;a href=\"Searing%20Daggers\"&gt;Searing Daggers&lt;/a&gt; at them or if they are close enough or feeling particularly destructive, set everything around them on fire through &lt;a href=\"Ignition\"&gt;Ignition&lt;/a&gt; spell.\nThe range of their spells are further improved by 2 meters through their talent &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Talents\"&gt;Far Out Man&lt;/a&gt;. Outside combat they rely on their &lt;a href=\"Loremaster\"&gt;Loremaster&lt;/a&gt; civil skill that allows them to identify properties of found gear and weaknesses of their enemies. \nOut of all companions &lt;a href=\"Fane\"&gt;Fane&lt;/a&gt; is the one who chooses this specialisation by default. \nSurvivor classes.\nAs the name implies, survivors specialize in pulling through tough situations by using any means necessary. They rely on their &lt;a href=\"Finesse\"&gt;Finesse&lt;/a&gt; when using all sorts of weapons ranging from bows, crossbows to daggers and spears. They primarily focus on dealing physical damage that destroys physical armour and complementing physical damage through various magic spells. \nMetamorph is a survivor who relies on the &lt;a href=\"Polymorph%20%28Skill%20Class%29\"&gt;Polymorph&lt;/a&gt; magic to adapt their body in response to danger and &lt;a href=\"Two-Handed%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Two-Handed&lt;/a&gt; expertise to wield their chosen weapon, a spear. Their primary attributes are &lt;a href=\"Strength\"&gt;Strength&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Finesse\"&gt;Finesse&lt;/a&gt;.\nMetamorphs chosen talent is the &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Talents\"&gt;Opportunist&lt;/a&gt; which allows them to attack enemies foolish enough to pass around them. Their first starting skill is &lt;a href=\"Bull%20Horns\"&gt;Bull Horns&lt;/a&gt; that allows them to rush through enemies and make them bleed. Their second starting skill is &lt;a href=\"Tentacle%20Lash\"&gt;Tentacle Lash&lt;/a&gt; that allows them to disarm enemies and the final starting skill is the &lt;a href=\"Chicken%20Claw\"&gt;Chicken Claw&lt;/a&gt; which allows them to transform unfortunate foes into harmless chickens. \nOutside combat, they rely on the &lt;a href=\"Persuasion\"&gt;Persuasion&lt;/a&gt; civil skill to achieve their goals through diplomacy or threats. \nRanger is a survivor focused on &lt;a href=\"Huntsman\"&gt;Huntsman&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Pyrokinetic%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Pyrokinetic&lt;/a&gt; skills. Their primary attributes are &lt;a href=\"Finesse\"&gt;Finesse&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Wits\"&gt;Wits&lt;/a&gt; which they need to wield ranged weapons like bows or crossbows. Their proficiency with bows and crossbows is further enhanced by their talent &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Talents\"&gt;Arrow Recovery&lt;/a&gt; which gives them 33 % chance of recovering special arrows after they are used.\nTheir first starting skill is &lt;a href=\"Elemental%20Arrowheads\"&gt;Elemental Arrowheads&lt;/a&gt; which allows them to adapt the damage type of their attacks. The second starting skill is &lt;a href=\"Ricochet%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Ricochet&lt;/a&gt; that allows them to attack multiple foes at once. Third and final starting skill is pyrokinetic spell &lt;a href=\"Peace%20of%20Mind\"&gt;Peace of Mind&lt;/a&gt; that increases attributes by 1 and removes status effects such as Blinded, Charmed or Taunted. \nOutside combat they rely on their civil ability &lt;a href=\"Lucky%20Charm\"&gt;Lucky Charm&lt;/a&gt; which increases their odds at finding treasure or equipment. \nRogue is a survivor who uses their &lt;a href=\"Scoundrel%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Scoundrel&lt;/a&gt; skill in combination with their &lt;a href=\"Dual%20Wielding\"&gt;Dual-Wielding&lt;/a&gt; skill. Their primary attributes are &lt;a href=\"Finesse\"&gt;Finesse&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Constitution\"&gt;Constitution&lt;/a&gt;. They primarily wield daggers in both hands. \nTheir first starting skill is &lt;a href=\"Throwing%20Knife\"&gt;Throwing Knife&lt;/a&gt; with which they can damage foes from distance. The second starting skill is &lt;a href=\"Backlash\"&gt;Backlash&lt;/a&gt; which allows them to teleport behind a foe and deal damage and their final starting skill is &lt;a href=\"Adrenaline%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Adrenaline&lt;/a&gt; which grants them more action points at the cost of the action points gained in next turn in combat. \nTheir mobility on battlefield is enhanced by their talent &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Talents\"&gt;The Pawn&lt;/a&gt; which allows them 1 free action point of movement at the start of their turn in combat. Their ability to move around is further enhanced by their civil ability &lt;a href=\"Sneaking\"&gt;Sneaking&lt;/a&gt; which makes their movement around undetected easier. \nOut of all companions &lt;a href=\"Sebille%20Kaleran\"&gt;Sebille Kaleran&lt;/a&gt; chooses this specialisation by default. \nShadowblade is a survivor relying on &lt;a href=\"Polymorph%20%28Skill%20Class%29\"&gt;Polymorph&lt;/a&gt; magic in addition to &lt;a href=\"Scoundrel%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Scoundrel&lt;/a&gt; skill. Their primary attributes are &lt;a href=\"Finesse\"&gt;Finesse&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Wits\"&gt;Wits&lt;/a&gt;. They mainly wield a single dagger. \nTheir first starting skill is &lt;a href=\"Backlash\"&gt;Backlash&lt;/a&gt; which allows them to teleport behind their foe and deal damage. The second starting skill is &lt;a href=\"Chicken%20Claw\"&gt;Chicken Claw&lt;/a&gt; spell which allows them to transform their foe into harmless chicken and their final starting skill is &lt;a href=\"Chameleon%20Cloak\"&gt;Chameleon Cloak&lt;/a&gt; that allows them to become invisible. The potential of this skill is further enhanced by their talent Guerilla which increases damage dealt when sneaking by 40 %.\nTheir civil talent is &lt;a href=\"Thievery\"&gt;Thievery&lt;/a&gt; which allows them to unlock locked doors, chests and to lighten the pockets of overly wealthy merchants. \nWayfarer is a survivor specialising in &lt;a href=\"Geomancer%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Geomancer&lt;/a&gt; magic and &lt;a href=\"Huntsman\"&gt;Huntsman&lt;/a&gt; skill. Their primary attributes are &lt;a href=\"Finesse\"&gt;Finesse&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Intelligence\"&gt;Intelligence&lt;/a&gt;. Their primary weapons are crossbows and bows. \nThe Wayfarer\u2019s first starting skill is &lt;a href=\"Elemental%20Arrowheads\"&gt;Elemental Arrowheads&lt;/a&gt; which allows them to adapt their damage type according to nearby surfaces. Their second starting skill is &lt;a href=\"Pin%20Down\"&gt;Pin Down&lt;/a&gt; which allows them to not only damage their foe but also immobilise them. The third final starting skill is &lt;a href=\"Fossil%20Strike\"&gt;Fossil Strike&lt;/a&gt; which allows them to hurl a chunk of earth at their enemies and create an oil surface beneath them. \nTheir civil skill is &lt;a href=\"Bartering%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Bartering&lt;/a&gt; which allows them to haggle better prices when dealing with Merchants. Their talent is &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Talents\"&gt;Pet Pal&lt;/a&gt; which allows them to speak to animals.\nOut of all companions &lt;a href=\"Ifan%20ben-Mezd\"&gt;Ifan ben-Mezd&lt;/a&gt; chooses this specialisation by default.\nWarrior classes.\nWarriors are wielders of &lt;a href=\"Strength\"&gt;Strength&lt;/a&gt; based weapons such as one-handed and two-handed swords, maces, axes and shields. Warrior classes focus on dealing large amount physical damage that destroys physical armour from up-close. \nBattlemage is a warrior who, besides relying on power of &lt;a href=\"Warfare\"&gt;Warfare&lt;/a&gt; skills, uses the &lt;a href=\"Aerotheurge%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Aerotheurge&lt;/a&gt; magic to defeat enemies. Their primary attributes are &lt;a href=\"Strength\"&gt;Strength&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Intelligence\"&gt;Intelligence&lt;/a&gt;. Battlemages mainly use two one-handed weapons like axes, swords or maces in combat. \nThe Battlemage\u2019s first starting skill is &lt;a href=\"Battering%20Ram\"&gt;Battering Ram&lt;/a&gt; which allows the Battlemage to rush forward and knock down enemies. The second starting skill is &lt;a href=\"Blinding%20Radiance%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Blinding Radiance&lt;/a&gt; spell which blinds and deals air damage to enemies close to the battlemage. The third and final skill is &lt;a href=\"Shocking%20Touch\"&gt;Shocking Touch&lt;/a&gt; which allows the Battlemage to deal air damage to enemies up-close. \nUnlike other classes, Battlemages need not fear defeat, thanks to their talent &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Talents\"&gt;Comeback Kid&lt;/a&gt; which allows them once per combat to cheat death. Outside combat though, they rely on their &lt;a href=\"Persuasion\"&gt;Persuasion&lt;/a&gt; skill to achieve their goals through diplomacy or threats. \nOut of all companions &lt;a href=\"Marcus%20Miles\"&gt;Marcus Miles&lt;/a&gt;, aka Beast, chooses this specialisation by default.\nFighters are warriors who alongside their &lt;a href=\"Warfare\"&gt;Warfare&lt;/a&gt; skill rely on the &lt;a href=\"Geomancer%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Geomancer&lt;/a&gt; magic to bolster their physical defenses. Their primary attributes are &lt;a href=\"Constitution\"&gt;Constitution&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Strength\"&gt;Strength&lt;/a&gt;. Their weapon of choice are one handed swords, axes or maces with a shield.\nThe Fighter\u2019s first starting skill is &lt;a href=\"Battle%20Stomp\"&gt;Battle Stomp&lt;/a&gt; which allows them to knock down enemies in front of them and clear some surfaces such as ice and fire. The second starting skill is &lt;a href=\"Bouncing%20Shield\"&gt;Bouncing Shield&lt;/a&gt; which lets them throw their shield at an enemy and if there is another enemy in 5 meter range they will be struck as well. The third and final skill is &lt;a href=\"Fortify\"&gt;Fortify&lt;/a&gt; which allows the Fighter to boost their physical armour. In combat the Fighter may also rely on their talent &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Talents\"&gt;Opportunist&lt;/a&gt; which allows them to attack any enemies that move next to them. \nOutside combat they rely on their &lt;a href=\"Bartering%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Bartering&lt;/a&gt; civil skill to haggle better prices when trading. \nOut of all companions &lt;a href=\"The%20Red%20Prince\"&gt;The Red Prince&lt;/a&gt; is the one who chooses this specialisation by default.\nInquisitor is a warrior who chose to walk a darker path by utilising &lt;a href=\"Necromancer%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Necromancy&lt;/a&gt; alongside their &lt;a href=\"Warfare\"&gt;Warfare&lt;/a&gt; skill. Their primary attributes are &lt;a href=\"Strength\"&gt;Strength&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Intelligence\"&gt;Intelligence&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Constitution\"&gt;Constitution&lt;/a&gt;. They mainly wield two-handed weapons like swords, axes or maces.\nThe Inquisitors first starting skill is &lt;a href=\"Battering%20Ram\"&gt;Battering Ram&lt;/a&gt; which allows them to move forward and knock down all enemies in their way. Their second starting skill is &lt;a href=\"Blood%20Sucker\"&gt;Blood Sucker&lt;/a&gt; which allows them to absorb the blood they are standing on in order to heal their wounds. The third and final starting skill is &lt;a href=\"Mosquito%20Swarm\"&gt;Mosquito Swarm&lt;/a&gt; which allows the Inquisitor to summon mosquitoes at their enemy in order to wound them and make them bleed. \nThe Inquisitors combat skills are further enhanced by their &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Talents\"&gt;Executioner&lt;/a&gt; talent, which gives them 2 Action Points for every killing blow. Alongside this they may utilise their civil skill &lt;a href=\"Telekinesis%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Telekinesis&lt;/a&gt; to move objects on their enemies. \nKnights are warriors purely focused on their &lt;a href=\"Warfare\"&gt;Warfare&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Two-Handed%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Two-Handed&lt;/a&gt; skills. Their primary attributes are &lt;a href=\"Strength\"&gt;Strength&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Constitution\"&gt;Constitution&lt;/a&gt; which they need in order to wield their weapon of choice: a two-handed sword, axe or mace.\nThe Knights first starting skill is &lt;a href=\"Battle%20Stomp\"&gt;Battle Stomp&lt;/a&gt; which allows them to knock down all enemies in front of them and clear away some surfaces. Their second starting skill is &lt;a href=\"Battering%20Ram\"&gt;Battering Ram&lt;/a&gt; which allows the Knight to rush forward and knock down all enemies in the way. The third and final skill is &lt;a href=\"Crippling%20Blow\"&gt;Crippling Blow&lt;/a&gt; which allows the Knight to immobilise their enemy. Besides the starting skills, Knight also has an &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Talents\"&gt;Opportunist&lt;/a&gt; talent which allows them to attack any enemy moving near them. \nOutside combat they rely on their &lt;a href=\"Bartering%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Bartering&lt;/a&gt; civil skill which improves the prices of items they are trading. "}
{"id": "10269", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=10269", "title": "Original Sin 2 Companions", "text": "Companions are characters which may accompany the main player character in \"\".\nOrigin characters.\nAll of origin companions are first met on &lt;a href=\"Merryweather\"&gt;Merryweather&lt;/a&gt; and can be recruited later when the main character reaches &lt;a href=\"Fort%20Joy\"&gt;Fort Joy&lt;/a&gt;. After the main character escapes Fort Joy they can be recruited one last time on &lt;a href=\"The%20Lady%20Vengeance\"&gt;the Lady Vengeance&lt;/a&gt;. However after Lady Vengeance departs the &lt;a href=\"Godwoken\"&gt;Godwoken&lt;/a&gt; that are not part of the main characters party will be killed and resurrected as &lt;a href=\"Undead\"&gt;undead&lt;/a&gt; sworn to the &lt;a href=\"God%20King\"&gt;God King&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"the%20Academy%20of%20the%20Seven\"&gt;the Academy of the Seven&lt;/a&gt; where they will fight the main character in &lt;a href=\"The%20Arena%20of%20the%20One\"&gt;the Arena of the One&lt;/a&gt;. \nThe Godwoken that have been dismissed from party after departing Fort Joy can be recruited once more on the Lady Vengeance.\n&lt;a href=\"Fane\"&gt;Fane&lt;/a&gt;.\nFane is an &lt;a href=\"Eternals\"&gt;Eternal&lt;/a&gt; scholar first encountered reading book in elven disguise within &lt;a href=\"Merryweather\"&gt;the Merryweather&lt;/a&gt; (x: 60,y: -233). At &lt;a href=\"Fort%20Joy\"&gt;Fort Joy&lt;/a&gt; he can be found within &lt;a href=\"Hidden%20Alcove\"&gt;Hidden Alcove&lt;/a&gt; where he attempts to carve out a face of a corpse in order to craft a mask (x:273, y:274). At &lt;a href=\"The%20Lady%20Vengeance\"&gt;Lady Vengeance&lt;/a&gt; before departing Fort Joy, he can be found standing in the Cabin (X:279, Y:596).\nFane's origin quest is &lt;a href=\"A%20Scholar%20from%20Times%20Past\"&gt;A Scholar from Times Past&lt;/a&gt;. Deity that chose Fane as her champion is &lt;a href=\"Amadia\"&gt;Amadia&lt;/a&gt;. His default class is a &lt;a href=\"Wizard%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Wizard&lt;/a&gt;.\n&lt;a href=\"Ifan%20ben-Mezd\"&gt;Ifan ben-Mezd&lt;/a&gt;.\nIfan ben-Mezd is an ex-&lt;a href=\"Paladins\"&gt;paladin&lt;/a&gt; turned Lone Wolf mercenary he was captured by &lt;a href=\"The%20Magisters\"&gt;Magisters&lt;/a&gt; when he took Drudanae and summoned a wolf into the &lt;a href=\"Undertavern\"&gt;Undertavern&lt;/a&gt;. On &lt;a href=\"Merryweather\"&gt;Merryweather&lt;/a&gt; he can be found standing near magister &lt;a href=\"Viktar\"&gt;Viktar&lt;/a&gt;. On &lt;a href=\"Fort%20Joy\"&gt;Fort Joy&lt;/a&gt; he can be found near the entrance to the &lt;a href=\"Fort%20Joy%20Ghetto\"&gt;Fort Joy Ghetto&lt;/a&gt; (X:204, Y:136) where he is defending &lt;a href=\"Elves\"&gt;elven&lt;/a&gt; woman &lt;a href=\"Elodi\"&gt;Elodi&lt;/a&gt; from &lt;a href=\"Griff\"&gt;Griff&lt;/a&gt;'s thugs. At &lt;a href=\"The%20Lady%20Vengeance\"&gt;Lady Vengeance&lt;/a&gt; before departing Fort Joy, Ifan can be found in the Cabin behind the stairs leading on the upper deck (X:329, Y:579).\nHis default class is a &lt;a href=\"Wayfarer%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Wayfarer&lt;/a&gt; and his origin quest is &lt;a href=\"A%20Wolf%20Alone\"&gt;A Wolf Alone&lt;/a&gt;. He is also the current champion of &lt;a href=\"Rhalic\"&gt;Rhalic&lt;/a&gt;. \n&lt;a href=\"Lohse\"&gt;Lohse&lt;/a&gt;.\nLohse is a &lt;a href=\"Humans\"&gt;human&lt;/a&gt; musician who had been sent to &lt;a href=\"Fort%20Joy\"&gt;Fort Joy&lt;/a&gt; after a failed concert at Agrid Hill in &lt;a href=\"Arx\"&gt;Arx&lt;/a&gt;. On &lt;a href=\"Merryweather\"&gt;the Merryweather&lt;/a&gt; she can be found surrounded by three children who ask her to sing (x: 41, y: -234). After the ship sinks she can be found in front of &lt;a href=\"Lucian\"&gt;Lucian&lt;/a&gt;'s statue within the &lt;a href=\"Fort%20Joy%20Ghetto\"&gt;Fort Joy Ghetto&lt;/a&gt; (X:203, Y:166). \nOriginally a champion of &lt;a href=\"Rhalic\"&gt;Rhalic&lt;/a&gt; she is forced to follow &lt;a href=\"Adramahlihk\"&gt;demonic influence&lt;/a&gt; on her way out of Fort Joy. Her default class is an &lt;a href=\"Enchanter%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Enchanter&lt;/a&gt;. Her origin quest is &lt;a href=\"The%20Thing%20Inside\"&gt;The Thing Inside&lt;/a&gt;. \nMahalia and Rahimus.\nMahalia (female name) and Rahimus (male name) are custom sourcerers created by players. Their &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Classes\"&gt;class&lt;/a&gt; specialisation, &lt;a href=\"Tag\"&gt;tags&lt;/a&gt;, gender, &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Races\"&gt;race&lt;/a&gt; and overall looks are determined only during the character creation (the overall looks have been expanded by &lt;a href=\"Larian%20Studios\"&gt;Larian Studios&lt;/a&gt; through release of the first \"Gift Bag: Beauty Salon\".) Alongside the choice of looks, players can also choose 2 tags that will determine the characters traits (example: Scholar, Noble etc.). Unlike the rest of the companions, custom godwoken do not have their own quests or tags. Their deity is determined by their race with the exception of &lt;a href=\"Undead\"&gt;Undead&lt;/a&gt; who will always be chosen by Amadia. \nUnlike the rest of the companions, all custom created Sourcerers share a &lt;a href=\"Source\"&gt;Source&lt;/a&gt; Skill: &lt;a href=\"Dome%20of%20Protection\"&gt;Dome of Protection&lt;/a&gt;.\n&lt;a href=\"Marcus%20Miles\"&gt;Marcus Miles&lt;/a&gt;.\nMarcus Miles also known as Beast is a dwarven noble who was captured by &lt;a href=\"The%20Magisters\"&gt;Magisters&lt;/a&gt; on the high seas. On &lt;a href=\"Merryweather\"&gt;Merryweather&lt;/a&gt; he can be found sitting among the &lt;a href=\"Dwarves\"&gt;dwarves&lt;/a&gt; (x: 51,y: -244). On &lt;a href=\"Fort%20Joy\"&gt;Fort Joy&lt;/a&gt; he can be found near ruined ship from which he is trying to get planks. &lt;a href=\"The%20Lady%20Vengeance\"&gt;At Lady Vengeance&lt;/a&gt;, prior to departing Fort Joy, Beast can be found near the ballistae in middle of the Cabin (X:306, Y:584). \nHis default class is &lt;a href=\"Battlemage%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Battlemage&lt;/a&gt; and his origin quest is &lt;a href=\"The%20Beast%20o%27%20the%20Sea\"&gt;The Beast o' the Sea&lt;/a&gt;. He is the chosen champion of &lt;a href=\"Duna\"&gt;Duna&lt;/a&gt;. \n&lt;a href=\"Sebille%20Kaleran\"&gt;Sebille Kaleran&lt;/a&gt;.\nSebille is an &lt;a href=\"Elves\"&gt;elven&lt;/a&gt; assassin who allowed herself to be captured by &lt;a href=\"The%20Magisters\"&gt;Magisters&lt;/a&gt; in order to find &lt;a href=\"The%20Shadow%20Prince\"&gt;the Master&lt;/a&gt;. On &lt;a href=\"Merryweather\"&gt;Merryweather&lt;/a&gt; she can be found playing dice in corner (x: 45, y: -249). On &lt;a href=\"Fort%20Joy\"&gt;Fort Joy&lt;/a&gt; she can be found initially in the kitchen of &lt;a href=\"Fort%20Joy%20Ghetto\"&gt;Fort Joy Ghetto&lt;/a&gt; spying on &lt;a href=\"Stingtail\"&gt;Stingtail&lt;/a&gt; and later follows him to his camp (X:180, Y:102). &lt;a href=\"The%20Lady%20Vengeance\"&gt;At Lady Vengeance&lt;/a&gt;, before departing Fort Joy, she can be found sitting in the Lower Deck (X:299, Y:507).\nHer default class is &lt;a href=\"Rogue%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Rogue&lt;/a&gt; and her origin quest is &lt;a href=\"Hunt%20for%20the%20Master\"&gt;Hunt for the Master&lt;/a&gt;. She is the chosen champion of &lt;a href=\"Tir-Cendelius\"&gt;Tir-Cendelius&lt;/a&gt;. If she is being spoken to by a &lt;a href=\"Lizards\"&gt;lizard&lt;/a&gt;, especially the Red Prince, she will be very hostile and needs to be persuaded in order to join the party. \n&lt;a href=\"The%20Red%20Prince\"&gt;The Red Prince&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe Red Prince is an exiled lizard prince of the &lt;a href=\"House%20of%20War\"&gt;House of War&lt;/a&gt; the Red Prince can be first found in the kitchen of the &lt;a href=\"Merryweather\"&gt;Merryweather&lt;/a&gt; ship, next to lizard &lt;a href=\"Namiyah\"&gt;Namiyah&lt;/a&gt; (x:58, y: -243). At &lt;a href=\"Fort%20Joy\"&gt;Fort Joy&lt;/a&gt; he can be found standing on the rock overlooking the sea (X:165, Y:282). At &lt;a href=\"the%20Lady%20Vengeance\"&gt;the Lady Vengeance&lt;/a&gt;, before departing Fort Joy, he can be found standing near &lt;a href=\"Simone\"&gt;Simone&lt;/a&gt; at the upper deck (X:621, Y:544). \nHis default class is &lt;a href=\"Fighter%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Fighter&lt;/a&gt; and his origin quest is &lt;a href=\"Redemption\"&gt;Redemption&lt;/a&gt;. He is the chosen champion of the goddess &lt;a href=\"Zorl-Stissa\"&gt;Zorl-Stissa&lt;/a&gt;. \nRecruiting Mercenaries.\nMercenaries are companions that can be recruited from Sergeant &lt;a href=\"Zrilla\"&gt;Zrilla&lt;/a&gt;, when the Godwoken reach Driftwood upon the Lady Vengeance ship. After Godwoken reach &lt;a href=\"Arx\"&gt;Arx&lt;/a&gt;, and if &lt;a href=\"Malady\"&gt;Malady&lt;/a&gt; is alive, Zrilla can be found on the ship that is stranded in &lt;a href=\"Hall%20of%20Echoes\"&gt;Hall of Echoes&lt;/a&gt;. The price for hiring a mercenary will increase as the game progresses. \nAll mercenaries have unique names, source skills which correspond with skills that Godwoken has already unlocked and an innate Source skill &lt;a href=\"Dome%20of%20Protection\"&gt;Dome of Protection&lt;/a&gt;. Upon recruitment mercenaries will be the same level as the party, however their stats and abilities will already be set. The only thing player can decide is the selection of &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Talents\"&gt;Talents&lt;/a&gt;, however all abilities and stats can be modified at Magic Mirror. Mercenaries also start with Starter, Novice and Adept (1-9 level) skills and spells that correspond with their class. The mercenaries only have racial and gender tags.\nMage mercenaries.\nMyrella is an &lt;a href=\"Elves\"&gt;elven&lt;/a&gt; mercenary who can be hired from Sergeant &lt;a href=\"Zrilla\"&gt;Zrilla&lt;/a&gt;. Her role on the battlefield is that of &lt;a href=\"Cleric%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;cleric&lt;/a&gt;, a &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Classes%23Mage%20classes\"&gt;mage&lt;/a&gt; who can support their allies through &lt;a href=\"Hydrosophist%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Hydrosophist&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Necromancer%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Necromancer&lt;/a&gt; magic. \nFrancesca is an &lt;a href=\"Humans\"&gt;human&lt;/a&gt; mercenary who can be hired from Sergeant &lt;a href=\"Zrilla\"&gt;Zrilla&lt;/a&gt;. Her role on the battlefield is that of &lt;a href=\"Conjurer%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;|conjurer&lt;/a&gt;, a &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Classes%23Mage%20classes\"&gt;mage&lt;/a&gt; who provides support through their &lt;a href=\"Summoning\"&gt;summoned&lt;/a&gt; minions.\nAurnia is an &lt;a href=\"Undead\"&gt;undead&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Dwarves\"&gt;dwarven&lt;/a&gt; mercenary who can be hired from Sergeant &lt;a href=\"Zrilla\"&gt;Zrilla&lt;/a&gt;. Her role on the battlefield is that of &lt;a href=\"Enchanter%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;enchanter&lt;/a&gt;, a &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Classes%23Mage%20classes\"&gt;mage&lt;/a&gt; who utilises &lt;a href=\"Aerotheurge%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Aerotheurge&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Hydrosophist%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Hydrosophist&lt;/a&gt; magic to support their allies.\nTaylia is an &lt;a href=\"Undead\"&gt;undead&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Elves\"&gt;elven&lt;/a&gt; mercenary who can be hired from Sergeant &lt;a href=\"Zrilla\"&gt;Zrilla&lt;/a&gt;. Her role on the battlefield is that of &lt;a href=\"Witch%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;witch&lt;/a&gt;, a &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Classes%23Mage%20classes\"&gt;mage&lt;/a&gt; who relies on &lt;a href=\"Necromancer%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Necromancer&lt;/a&gt; magic and &lt;a href=\"Scoundrel%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;scoundrel skills&lt;/a&gt; to defeat her enemies.\nForrex is an &lt;a href=\"Lizards\"&gt;lizard&lt;/a&gt; mercenary who can be hired from Sergeant &lt;a href=\"Zrilla\"&gt;Zrilla&lt;/a&gt;. His role on the battlefield is that of &lt;a href=\"Wizard%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;wizard&lt;/a&gt;, a &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Classes%23Mage%20classes\"&gt;mage&lt;/a&gt; who relies on &lt;a href=\"Geomancer%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;geomancer&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Pyrokinetic%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;pyrokinetic&lt;/a&gt; magic to vanquish his enemies.\nSurvivor mercenaries.\nTrxyl is an &lt;a href=\"Undead\"&gt;undead&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Lizards\"&gt;lizard&lt;/a&gt; mercenary who can be hired from Sergeant &lt;a href=\"Zrilla\"&gt;Zrilla&lt;/a&gt;. Her role on the battlefield is that of &lt;a href=\"Metamorph%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;metamorph&lt;/a&gt;, a &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Classes%23Survivor%20classes\"&gt;survivor&lt;/a&gt; using &lt;a href=\"Polymorph%20%28Skill%20Class%29\"&gt;polymorph magic&lt;/a&gt; to outsmart and overcome their enemies.\nVeeros is an &lt;a href=\"Elves\"&gt;elven&lt;/a&gt; mercenary who can be hired from Sergeant &lt;a href=\"Zrilla\"&gt;Zrilla&lt;/a&gt;. His role on the battlefield is that of &lt;a href=\"Ranger%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;ranger&lt;/a&gt;, a &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Classes%23Survivor%20classes\"&gt;survivor&lt;/a&gt; using &lt;a href=\"Huntsman\"&gt;Huntsman skills&lt;/a&gt; in combination with &lt;a href=\"Pyrokinetic%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Pyrokinetic magic&lt;/a&gt; to defeat his enemies.\nPestilence is an &lt;a href=\"Undead\"&gt;undead&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Lizards\"&gt;lizard&lt;/a&gt; mercenary who can be hired from Sergeant &lt;a href=\"Zrilla\"&gt;Zrilla&lt;/a&gt;. His role on the battlefield is that of &lt;a href=\"Rogue%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;rogue&lt;/a&gt;, a &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Classes%23Survivor%20classes\"&gt;survivor&lt;/a&gt; using &lt;a href=\"Scoundrel%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Scoundrel skills&lt;/a&gt; to decimate his foes.\nPestilence is an &lt;a href=\"Undead\"&gt;undead&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Human\"&gt;human&lt;/a&gt; mercenary who can be hired from Sergeant &lt;a href=\"Zrilla\"&gt;Zrilla&lt;/a&gt;. Her role on the battlefield is that of &lt;a href=\"Shadowblade%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;shadowblade&lt;/a&gt;, a &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Classes%23Survivor%20classes\"&gt;survivor&lt;/a&gt; using &lt;a href=\"Scoundrel%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Scoundrel skills&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Polymorph%20%28Skill%20Class%29\"&gt;Polymorph magic&lt;/a&gt; to decimate her foes.\nMorrgen is an &lt;a href=\"Undead\"&gt;Undead&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Humans\"&gt;human&lt;/a&gt; mercenary who can be hired from Sergeant &lt;a href=\"Zrilla\"&gt;Zrilla&lt;/a&gt;. His role on the battlefield is that of &lt;a href=\"Wayfarer%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;wayfarer&lt;/a&gt;, a &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Classes%23Survivor%20classes\"&gt;survivor&lt;/a&gt; using &lt;a href=\"Huntsman\"&gt;Huntsman skills&lt;/a&gt; in combination with &lt;a href=\"Geomancer%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Geomancer magic&lt;/a&gt; to defeat his enemies.\nWarrior mercenaries.\nRavella is a &lt;a href=\"Dwarves\"&gt;dwarven&lt;/a&gt; mercenary who can be hired from Sergeant &lt;a href=\"Zrilla\"&gt;Zrilla&lt;/a&gt;. Her role on the battlefield is that of &lt;a href=\"Battlemage%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;battlemage&lt;/a&gt;, a &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Classes%23Warrior%20Classes\"&gt;warrior&lt;/a&gt; who alongside her &lt;a href=\"Warfare\"&gt;Warfare&lt;/a&gt; skills relies on &lt;a href=\"Aerotheurge%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Aerotheurge&lt;/a&gt; magic to vanquish her foes.\nNestor is a &lt;a href=\"Dwarves\"&gt;dwarven&lt;/a&gt; mercenary who can be &lt;a href=\"Companions%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29%23Recruiting%20Mercenaries\"&gt;hired&lt;/a&gt; from Sergeant &lt;a href=\"Zrilla\"&gt;Zrilla&lt;/a&gt;. His role on the battlefield is that of fighter, a warrior who alongside his &lt;a href=\"Warfare\"&gt;Warfare&lt;/a&gt; skills relies on &lt;a href=\"Geomancer%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Geomancer&lt;/a&gt; magic to vanquish his foes.\nStraffan is a &lt;a href=\"Humans\"&gt;human&lt;/a&gt; mercenary who can be hired from Sergeant &lt;a href=\"Zrilla\"&gt;Zrilla&lt;/a&gt;. His role on the battlefield is that of &lt;a href=\"Inquisitor%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;inquisitor&lt;/a&gt;, a warrior who alongside his &lt;a href=\"Warfare\"&gt;Warfare&lt;/a&gt; skills relies on &lt;a href=\"Necromancer%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Necromancer&lt;/a&gt; magic to vanquish his foes.\nYastara is a &lt;a href=\"Lizards\"&gt;lizard&lt;/a&gt; mercenary who can be hired from Sergeant &lt;a href=\"Zrilla\"&gt;Zrilla&lt;/a&gt;. Her role on the battlefield is that of &lt;a href=\"Knight%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;knight&lt;/a&gt;, a warrior who relies purely on her &lt;a href=\"Warfare\"&gt;Warfare&lt;/a&gt; skills with a bit of &lt;a href=\"Pyrokinetic%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Pyrokinetic&lt;/a&gt; magic to vanquish her foes.\nTemporary Companions.\nTemporary companions are NPCs which may under specific circumstances temporarily join the party and follow the main character. Once the conditions have been met, they will leave the party. \nAlexandar can join the party, if he has been persuaded to abandon his pursuit of Divinity at &lt;a href=\"the%20Academy%20of%20the%20Seven\"&gt;the Academy of the Seven&lt;/a&gt;. He will join the party in &lt;a href=\"the%20Arena%20of%20the%20One\"&gt;the Arena of the One&lt;/a&gt; and will stay in the party for the time they traverse the location. \nDelorus may join the party on the &lt;a href=\"The%20Nameless%20Isle\"&gt;Nameless Isle&lt;/a&gt;, if he was saved at &lt;a href=\"Fort%20Joy\"&gt;Fort Joy&lt;/a&gt;. He will stay in the party until they reach Alexandar in the &lt;a href=\"Temple%20of%20Tir-Cendelius\"&gt;Temple of Tir-Cendelius&lt;/a&gt;.\nSaheila will join the party, once they had defeated &lt;a href=\"Roost%20Anlon\"&gt;Roost Anlon&lt;/a&gt; at &lt;a href=\"Cullwoods%20Mill\"&gt;Cullwoods Mill&lt;/a&gt;. She will stay with the party until they return to the &lt;a href=\"Elven%20Camp\"&gt;Elven Camp&lt;/a&gt;. Her survival is tied to the main quest &lt;a href=\"Powerful%20Awakening\"&gt;Powerful Awakening&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "10383", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=10383", "title": "Original Sin 2 Consumables", "text": "Consumables are a type of &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Items\"&gt;items&lt;/a&gt;, that can be used by characters, in \"\".\nDescription.\nConsumables are items which may be consumed by characters or NPCs for stats bonuses and losses for certain amount of turns. These bonuses, in most cases, can be doubled by having &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Talents\"&gt;Five-Star Diner talent&lt;/a&gt;. All of these items can be found in the game in containers, on ground or by trading with NPCs. Most of these items can be either crafted or used in crafting.\nConsumables themselves can be broken into following categories: food and drinks, plants, potions, herbmixtures, body parts, source orbs and miscellaneous.\nFood and Drink.\nFollowing tables shows all food and drinks that can be found and possibly crafted across &lt;a href=\"Rivellon\"&gt;Rivellon&lt;/a&gt;. Nearly all of these can be &lt;a href=\"Poisoned%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Poisoned&lt;/a&gt; to make it safe for &lt;a href=\"Undead\"&gt;Undead&lt;/a&gt; and receive bonus from &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Talents\"&gt;Five-Star Diner&lt;/a&gt; talent. \nPlants.\nHerbs.\nHerbs are consumable items which can be used as an ingredient to make potions or scrolls. Like other consumable items most of them are affected by &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Talents\"&gt;Five-Star Diner talent&lt;/a&gt; which will double the bonuses provided. All of these items (except &lt;a href=\"Wizard%27s%20Hat%20Agaric\"&gt;Wizard's Hat Agaric&lt;/a&gt;) can be found in the game in containers, on ground or by trading with NPCs.\nHerbmix.\nHerbmixes are assortments of herbs mixed with &lt;a href=\"Drudanae%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Drudanae&lt;/a&gt;. When smoked they bestow a large boon, depending on the herb used in its making. Herbmixes are one of the few consumable items that do not benefit from &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Talents\"&gt;Five-Star Diner talent&lt;/a&gt; and require &lt;a href=\"Dreamer%20Pipe\"&gt;Dreamer Pipe&lt;/a&gt; in order to be consumed.\nPotions.\nPotions are items that can be consumed to heal or temporary buff attributes and statistics of the character using them. These items may be used both during combat - to buff or heal the character - or outside the combat, while interacting with the environment.\nLow-tier potions may generally be crafted by combining an &lt;a href=\"Empty%20Potion%20Bottle\"&gt;Empty Potion Bottle&lt;/a&gt; with &lt;a href=\"Consumables%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29%23Plants\"&gt;Herbs&lt;/a&gt; found around the &lt;a href=\"Rivellon\"&gt;Rivellon&lt;/a&gt;. Instead, higher tier potions are generally crafted by combining 2 lower tier variants or a lower tier potion with an &lt;a href=\"Augmentor%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Augmentor&lt;/a&gt; (this is not always true, check crafting recipes for details).\nBody Parts.\nBody parts are unique consumables that are useful only to Elves, Undead Elves and those using the Mask of the Shapeshifter. For only elves can gain insight, skills and &lt;a href=\"Healing%20%28Status%29\"&gt;healing&lt;/a&gt; by consuming these. Following table shows unique body parts that provide atleast either skill or quest update. \nHerb Gardens.\nHerbs.\nGift Bag: Herb Gardens adds new type of herbs in addition to the original ones: Distinctive. These have faint light blue aura in their icon and are used to craft new potions and additionally blank skill books. They can be bought, found or grown when placing Seedling on \"oil surface\". Each Seedling placed on oil surface will yield 1 Distinctive herb."}
