{"id": "11364", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=11364", "title": "Original Sin 2 Hydrosophist", "text": "Hydrosophist is a &lt;a href=\"Attributes%20and%20Abilities%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;combat ability&lt;/a&gt;, that utilises magic known as &lt;a href=\"Hydrosophy\"&gt;hydrosophy&lt;/a&gt;, and is essential for learning and casting hydrosophist skills as well as crucial determining factor of the effectiveness of water based weapons and ammunition in \"\". \nDescription.\nCharacteristics.\nHydrosophist combat ability focuses on dealing water damage, which is resisted by Magic Armour and Water Resistance. Magic Armour prevents negative status effects from affecting characters whereas Water Resistance directly lowers water damage done. The reduction is based on percentage, therefore character with + 10 % water resistance will receive 10 % less water damage. \nHydrosophist combat ability is by default used by 2 preset classes. The &lt;a href=\"Cleric%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Cleric&lt;/a&gt;, which is a mage preset class, who uses Hydrosophist alongside &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Necromancer\"&gt;Necromancer&lt;/a&gt; combat ability and the &lt;a href=\"Enchanter%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Enchanter&lt;/a&gt;, which is a mage preset class, who uses Hydrosophist alongside &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Aerotheurge\"&gt;Aerotheurge&lt;/a&gt; combat ability.\nHydrosophist on its own offers 7 support skills, 1 utility skill and 7 offensive skills. Craftable skills that include Hydrosophist offer 10 support (2 are incarnate infusions) and 2 offensive skills. Overall Hydrosophist offers 17 support skills, 9 offensive skills and 1 utility skill.\nHydrosophist ability on its own increases water damage from all sources by 5 % per each point invested. Note that in order to learn all Hydrosophist skills, the character needs 5 points in Hydrosophist (either by investment or by bonuses from items).\nDamage of Hydrosophist Skills.\nDamage in \"Divinity: Original Sin II\" is calculated through this exact formula: Damage = (Base Damage) x (1 + Elemental Bonus%) x (1 + Attribute Bonus% + Weapon Skill Bonus% + Misc Bonuses% [if attack]) x (1 + High Ground Bonus% + Crit Bonus%) x ( 1 + Misc Bonus% [if spell])\nDue to skills under Hydrosophist ability being spells they all use the following formula for damage: (Base Damage) x (1 + Elemental Bonus%) x (1 + Attribute Bonus% + Weapon Skill Bonus %) x (1 + High Ground Bonus% + Crit Bonus%) x ( 1 + Misc Bonus %). Additionaly they cannot be cast if caster is affected by &lt;a href=\"Silenced%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Silenced&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Enraged%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Enraged&lt;/a&gt; status effects.\nSimply put for the water damage done by Hydrosophist skills the most crucial elements are: Level of the caster, Hydrosophist ability, Intelligence attribute, High Ground bonus and Critical Hit bonus. \nHydrosophist skills DO NOT rely on the base damage done by weapons. However weapons affect damage done if they provide boost to any of the above mentioned elements that affect water damage done.\nTherefore in order to boost damage done by Hydrosophist skills it is crucial to increase: Level, Hydrosophist, Intelligence, High Ground Bonus, Critical Hit Bonus. If possible it is wise to lower the water resistance of enemies. Note that bonus to damage provided by Intelligence is smaller than bonus provided by Hydrosophist ability. \nHydrosophist skills scale on Hydrosophist due to them being based on restoring Vitality or dealing water damage, however in the case of &lt;a href=\"Undead\"&gt;Undead&lt;/a&gt; it works slightly differently. Skills that will heal the living such as &lt;a href=\"Restoration%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Restoration&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Cleanse%20Wounds\"&gt;Cleanse Wounds&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Healing%20Tears\"&gt;Healing Tears&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Steam%20Lance\"&gt;Steam Lance&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Mass%20Cleanse%20Wounds\"&gt;Mass Cleanse Wounds&lt;/a&gt; will instead of restoring Vitality deal physical damage to the Undead. This damage is affected by both Hydrosophist, as it is considered as \"healing\", and &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Warfare\"&gt;Warfare&lt;/a&gt; as it is physical damage. Note that any damage reflected this way back to the \"living\" caster will restore Vitality instead of causing further damage.\nSurfaces and Status Effects.\nHydrosophist ability is focuses on mastering water. Therefore those who use it are most commonly capable of creating water and ice surfaces, which can be further enhanced into \"cursed water\" and \"holy water\" surfaces as well as \"cursed ice\" and \"blessed ice\" surfaces. Water surface can also be easily turned into Steam cloud if it comes into contact with any form of fire. Likewise ice can be melted into water surface.\nHydrosophist skills are also capable of causing a variety of status effects. Below is a table listing all effects caused by Hydrosophist combat ability skills.\nTraders.\nFollowing table shows all NPCs who are guaranteed to sell hydrosophist skillbooks, with their location and coordinates in the right column, from them. The location shown in the table (and the coordinates) are only for the initial location the NPC is in. Note that some of these may have other skillbooks and goods to sell. &lt;a href=\"Almira\"&gt;Almira&lt;/a&gt; may follow the Godwoken on &lt;a href=\"The%20Lady%20Vengeance\"&gt;Lady Vengeance&lt;/a&gt; if her demands are met. Also note that &lt;a href=\"Lizard%20Dreamer\"&gt;Lizard Dreamer&lt;/a&gt; requires a persuasion check to be passed in order to speak with him, otherwise he (and the whole encampment) will turn hostile. \nHydrosophist Skills.\nAbility Based.\nFollowing tables and sub-sections show hydrosophist skills that can be learnt by character if they have enough point in Hydrosophist ability. All of these skills can be crafted by combining corresponding scroll with &lt;a href=\"Blank%20Water%20Skillbook\"&gt;blank water skillbook&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Blank%20Water%20Skillbook\"&gt;high tier blank water skillbook&lt;/a&gt;. Note that not all skills have craftable scrolls. In base game (without cheats) skills from 9 level onward (Adept, Expert and Master tiers) can be gained only after escaping &lt;a href=\"Reaper%27s%20Eye\"&gt;Reaper's Eye&lt;/a&gt; island. \nEach skill belongs to a tier that is determined through characters level that determines whether it can be found and purchased and requires certain level in \"Hydrosophist ability\" in order to memorise the skill. Higher Tier skills may require more memory in order to use them in combat, this especially applies to skills that require &lt;a href=\"Source\"&gt;Source&lt;/a&gt; in order to cast them. \nCraftable.\nFollowing skillbooks are classified as craftable for they can be obtained only by crafting them. They cannot be bought from any trader in the game. However it is possible to get them as quest reward or find them as random loot.\nBase skillbooks are obtained whenever non-source Hydrosophist skillbook is combined with another non-source skillbook. Resulting skillbook will be a mix of both skillbooks and will require investment in both combat abilities under which the skillbooks belong. Example: In order to learn and cast Healing Tears, character needs 1 point in both Hydrosophist and Polymorph combat abilities.\nSource skillbooks are obtained whenever non-source Hydrosophist skillbook is combined with source skillbook and vice versa. One way or another there has to be source skillbook involved in crafting otherwise the resulting book will be non-source skillbook. Like base craftable skillbooks these also cannot be bought from traders in game.\nOther Skills.\nOutside of player accesible and craftable skills, there are skills exclusive to NPCs that are also clasiffied as Hydrosophist. Some of these are also accessible in Game Master Mode. Following table also includes skills exclusive to Gift Bag features such as Pet Power which allows player character to cast Infusions unto any summoned creature. These infusions sometimes grant unique skills unseen in the base game.\nItems.\nOutside of skills, the Hydrosophist combat ability affects also all manner of items which can deal water damage. Likewise the Hydrosophist ability can be boosted through items that provide bonus to it. Most notably this includes all arrows, grenades, traps, equipment and lastly runes. \nAmmunition.\nFollowing arrows and grenades are magical items that can be used both in and outside of combat to cause water damage and potentially create water or ice surfaces. All of the following arrows and grenades are empowered by Hydrosophist combat ability. Note that in order to use arrows, character must have bow or crossbow equipped.\nFollowing items are exclusive to Gift Bag features, most notably Crafter's Kit, and as such cannot be obtained, made or otherwise seen in the base game unless the feature has been manually activated.\nEquipment.\nHydrosophist combat ability is best paired with weapons that cause water damage (most commonly staves and wands) and equipment that increases Hydrosophist and Intelligence. \nRunes.\nAll equipment that has rune slots can be inserted with runes that will grant them additional properties. Most important rune for all who rely on Hydrosophist ability is the &lt;a href=\"Frost%20Rune\"&gt;Frost Rune&lt;/a&gt;, which increases not only water damage when inserted into weapon but also &lt;a href=\"Movement\"&gt;Movement&lt;/a&gt; when inserted into necklace and ring. Lastly the Frost Rune grants Water Resistance when inserted into armour. If the base Frost Rune of any size is put into \"rune frame\" it will gain additional effects.\n&lt;a href=\"Frost%20Rune\"&gt;Mystical Frost Rune&lt;/a&gt; of any size provides 1 point bonus to either &lt;a href=\"Leadership\"&gt;Leadership&lt;/a&gt; (if inserted into armour), &lt;a href=\"Single-Handed%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Single-Handed&lt;/a&gt; (if inserted into weapon) and Hydrosophist (if inserted into any necklace or ring) alongside its base effect.\n&lt;a href=\"Frost%20Rune\"&gt;Frost Rune of Power&lt;/a&gt; of any size will always provide bonus to &lt;a href=\"Intelligence\"&gt;Intelligence&lt;/a&gt; (depending on its size) whenever inserted into any equipment."}
