{"id": "11642", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=11642", "title": "Original Sin 2 Locations", "text": "Original Sin 2 Locations is a page detailing all locations found in \"\" game. \n&lt;a href=\"Reaper%27s%20Eye\"&gt;Reaper's Eye&lt;/a&gt;.\n&lt;dpl&gt;\ncategory=Reaper's Eye\nuses =Template:Infobox location\nincludepage = {Infobox location}:type:part of:quests:level:factions\ntable = class=\"article-table sortable\",Name,Type,Part of,Related quests,data-sort-type=\"number\"|Level,Factions\n&lt;/dpl&gt;\n&lt;a href=\"Reaper%27s%20Coast\"&gt;Reaper's Coast&lt;/a&gt;.\n&lt;dpl&gt;\ncategory=Reaper's Coast\nuses =Template:Infobox location\nincludepage = {Infobox location}:type:part of:quests:level:factions\ntable = class=\"article-table sortable\",Name,Type,Part of,Related quests,data-sort-type=\"number\"|Level,Factions\n&lt;/dpl&gt;\n&lt;a href=\"The%20Nameless%20Isle\"&gt;The Nameless Isle&lt;/a&gt;.\n&lt;dpl&gt;\ncategory=The Nameless Isle\nuses =Template:Infobox location\nincludepage = {Infobox location}:type:part of:quests:level:factions\ntable = class=\"article-table sortable\",Name,Type,Part of,Related quests,data-sort-type=\"number\"|Level,Factions\n&lt;/dpl&gt;\nMentioned Locations.\nFollowing locations and regions do not appear in the game and are only mentioned by NPCs, items or can be found within the lorebook. "}
{"id": "22725", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=22725", "title": "Original Sin 2 Magical Items", "text": "Magical items are a type of &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Items\"&gt;items&lt;/a&gt; found in \"\" \nDescription.\nMagical items are a type of item primarily used in and for combat purposes by player character, companions or NPCs. All of these items have variety of effects ranging from dealing damage to inflicting status effects and creating surfaces or even providing additional lasting bonuses. \nIn both Classic Edition and Definitive Edition there are 5 types of magical items: Runes, Skillbooks, Scrolls, Grenades and Arrows. In Definitive Edition with the release of the features: Herb Gardens and Crafter's Kit a new kinds of grenades and skillbooks have been added to the game. \nDepending on their effects, every item with the exception of runes and skillbooks, can be empowered by investing points in abilities and talents that either: increase damage, range or prolong the effects of inflicted status effects.\n\"Note: Due to slightly differing type of usage and overall utility the arrows and grenades have been moved to &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Munitions\"&gt;Munitions&lt;/a&gt; page.\"\nRunes.\nDescription.\nRunes are a type of magical items that can be crafted and inserted into equipment in order to provide specialised bonuses that depend on the type and size of the rune and the equipment it is inserted into. All runes can be inserted and removed from equipment as many times as needed. Each rune insertion fills 1 rune slot and all equipment can have a maximum of 3 rune slots.\nAll runes can be upgraded through crafting by combining two runes of the same size and type alongside &lt;a href=\"Pixie%20Dust\"&gt;Pixie Dust&lt;/a&gt;, which is also used to make the runes in the first place. Doing so will increase its size and effectiveness (this can be done until rune reaches the \"Giant\" size). Besides upgrading its effectiveness, all runes can be granted additional property by combining them with either &lt;a href=\"Rune%20Frame%20of%20Power\"&gt;Rune Frame of Power&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Mystical%20Rune%20Frame\"&gt;Mystical Rune Frame&lt;/a&gt;. Note that once combined it will be impossible to both remove the frame and upgrade the rune.\nRune Tables.\nFollowing 3 tables show all runes as well as their base properties and additional bonuses when combined with above mentioned rune frames.\nSkillbooks and Scrolls.\nScrolls.\nScrolls are a type of magical items that can be mostly crafted and used in and outside of combat in order to cast spells. Unlike runes, scrolls can be used only once before they disappear, unlike learnt spells they require only &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Action%20Points\"&gt;action points&lt;/a&gt; (this especially includes spells that utilise &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Source%20Points\"&gt;source points&lt;/a&gt;) in order to be cast. All of these with the exception of source spell &lt;a href=\"Curse%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;curse&lt;/a&gt; can be combined with blank skill books of corresponding type in order to create a proper skillbook. \nThe action point cost of using scrolls can be lowered by 1 point if character has &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Talents\"&gt;Ambidextrous&lt;/a&gt; talent. Scrolls are also affected by &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Talents\"&gt;Far Out Man&lt;/a&gt; talent. \nFollowing table shows all special or otherwise unique scrolls that are found in the game itself. Out of these only the &lt;a href=\"Voidwoken%20Fish%20Exchange\"&gt;Voidwoken Fish Exchange&lt;/a&gt; scroll cannot be crafted.\nFollowing table shows all scrolls that are found in the game itself. Note that some of these cannot be crafted."}
{"id": "10566", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=10566", "title": "Original Sin 2 Munitions", "text": "Munition or ammunition are a type of &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Items\"&gt;item&lt;/a&gt; found in \"\".\nDescription.\nMunition is a type of item primarily used in combat by player character, companions or NPCs. All of these items have variety of effects ranging from dealing damage to inflicting status effects and creating surfaces. All of these items are primarily thrown or shoot in order to achieve a desired effect. \nIn both Classic Edition and Definitive Edition there are two types of munition: arrows which can be used only if character wields a bow or crossbow, and grenades which can be thrown by any character and require no weapon. In Definitive Edition with the release of the features: Herb Gardens and Crafter's Kit a new kinds of grenades and most of all deployable traps have been added to the game.\nDepending on their effects, nearly every item can be empowered by investing points in abilities and talents that either: increase damage, range or prolong the effects of inflicted status effects.\nList of Munitions.\nBase Game.\nArrows.\nArrows are type of munition which are used when wielding &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Weapons%23Ranged\"&gt;bows&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Weapons%23Ranged\"&gt;crossbows&lt;/a&gt;. Nearly all arrows can be crafted or upgraded to have special properties, either from basic &lt;a href=\"Arrow\"&gt;arrow&lt;/a&gt; or from elemental arrow. Elemental arrows can be also crafted from &lt;a href=\"arrowhead\"&gt;arrowhead&lt;/a&gt;s, which can be crafted into special arrowheads. All of these arrows are affected by talents: &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Talents\"&gt;Arrow Recovery&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Talents\"&gt;Elemental Ranger&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Talents\"&gt;Far Out Man&lt;/a&gt;. \nGrenades.\nGrenades are a type of munition, which unlike arrows, can be used by any character. They can be thrown regardless of weapon(s) wielded and cause damage or any other effect in a designated area of impact. All of these grenades, except &lt;a href=\"Smoke%20Grenade\"&gt;Smoke Grenade&lt;/a&gt;, can be crafted. All of these grenades are affected by talents: &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Talents\"&gt;Ambidextrous&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Talents\"&gt;Slingshot&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Talents\"&gt;Far Out Man&lt;/a&gt;.\nGift Bag - Song Of Nature.\nFollowing grenades and traps had been added to the game through additional content known as the Gift Bag - Song of Nature. This gift bag added 6 new features out of which Herb Gardens and most notably Crafter's Kit add new craftable munitions to the game. While Herb Gardens are mostly focused on &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Consumables\"&gt;Herbs&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Consumables\"&gt;Potions&lt;/a&gt; it adds one grenade to the game, the &lt;a href=\"Eraser%20grenade\"&gt;Eraser grenade&lt;/a&gt; which can remove all manner of clouds and surfaces (deathfog and lava included). The rest of the grenades and traps in the list below are from Crafter's Kit feature. Note that \"having any of these features activated disables achievements\".\nGrenades.\nFollowing grenades are a type of munition that has been added to the game as part of a gift bag feature. They function similarly to their base game counterparts with the exception of &lt;a href=\"Eraser%20Grenade\"&gt;Eraser Grenade&lt;/a&gt; which has a unique ability to completely clear out any surfaces and clouds. Like their base game counterparts all of these grenades are affected by talents: &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Talents\"&gt;Ambidextrous&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Talents\"&gt;Slingshot&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Talents\"&gt;Far Out Man&lt;/a&gt;."}
