{"id": "11367", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=11367", "title": "Original Sin 2 Pyrokinetic", "text": "Pyrokinetic is a &lt;a href=\"Attributes%20and%20Abilities%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;combat ability&lt;/a&gt;, that utilises magic known as &lt;a href=\"Pyrokinesis\"&gt;pyrokinesis&lt;/a&gt;, and is essential for learning and casting pyrokinetic skills as well as crucial determining factor of the effectiveness of fire based weapons and ammunition in \"\". \nDescription.\nCharacteristics.\nPyrokinetic combat ability focuses on dealing fire damage, which is resisted by Magic Armour and Fire Resistance. Magic Armour prevents negative status effects from affecting characters whereas Fire Resistance directly lowers fire damage done. The reduction is based on percentage, therefore character with + 10 % fire resistance will receive 10 % less fire damage. \nPyrokinetic combat ability is by default used by 2 preset classes. The &lt;a href=\"Wizard%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Wizard&lt;/a&gt;, which is a mage preset class, who uses Pyrokinetic alongside &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Geomancer\"&gt;Geomancer&lt;/a&gt; combat ability and the &lt;a href=\"Ranger%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Ranger&lt;/a&gt;, which is a survivor preset class, who uses Pyrokinetic alongside &lt;a href=\"Huntsman\"&gt;Huntsman&lt;/a&gt; combat ability.\nPyrokinetic on its own offers 4 support skills, 1 summoning spell and 10 offensive skills. Craftable skills that include pyrokinetic offer 5 support (2 are incarnate infusions) and 7 offensive skills. Overall Pyrokinetic offers 9 support skills, 17 offensive skills and 1 summon spell.\nPyrokinetic ability on its own increases fire damage from all sources by 5 % per each point invested. Note that in order to learn all Pyrokinetic skills, the character needs 5 points in Pyrokinetic (either by investment or by bonuses from items).\nDamage of Pyrokinetic Skills.\nDamage in \"Divinity: Original Sin II\" is calculated through this exact formula: Damage = (Base Damage) x (1 + Elemental Bonus%) x (1 + Attribute Bonus% + Weapon Skill Bonus% + Misc Bonuses% [if attack]) x (1 + High Ground Bonus% + Crit Bonus%) x ( 1 + Misc Bonus% [if spell])\nDue to skills under Pyrokinetic ability being spells they all use the following formula for damage: (Base Damage) x (1 + Elemental Bonus%) x (1 + Attribute Bonus% + Weapon Skill Bonus %) x (1 + High Ground Bonus% + Crit Bonus%) x ( 1 + Misc Bonus %). Additionaly they cannot be cast if caster is affected by &lt;a href=\"Silenced%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Silenced&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Enraged%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Enraged&lt;/a&gt; status effects.\nSimply put for the fire damage done by Pyrokinetic skills the most crucial elements are: Level of the caster, Pyrokinetic ability, Intelligence attribute, High Ground bonus and Critical Hit bonus. \nPyrokinetic skills DO NOT rely on the base damage done by weapons. However weapons affect damage done if they provide boost to any of the above mentioned elements that affect fire damage done.\nTherefore in order to boost damage done by Pyrokinetic skills it is crucial to increase: Level, Pyrokinetic, Intelligence, High Ground Bonus, Critical Hit Bonus. If possible it is wise to lower the fire resistance of enemies. Note that bonus to damage provided by Intelligence is smaller than bonus provided by Pyrokinetic ability.\nSurfaces and Status Effects.\nPyrokinetic ability is focuses on mastering fire. Therefore those who use it are most commonly capable of creating fire surfaces, which can be further enhanced into \"cursed fire\" and \"holy fire\" surfaces. Fire surfaces can be easily created from \"oil\" and \"poison\" surfaces which are flammable (and explosive) as well as \"web surface\" (which can be negated only by fire). All fire surfaces that dissipate on their own leave smoke cloud in their place. The cloud will block vision of all affected characters and thus prevent them from casting ranged skills at other characters within the smoke unless their impact is large enough.\nPyrokinetic skills are also capable of causing a variety of status effects. Below is a table listing all effects caused by Pyrokinetic combat ability skills.\nTraders.\nFollowing table shows all NPCs who are guaranteed to sell pyrokinetic spellbooks, with their location and coordinates in the right column, from them. The location shown in the table (and the coordinates) are only for the initial location the NPC is in. Note that some of these may have other skillbooks and goods to sell. &lt;a href=\"Almira\"&gt;Almira&lt;/a&gt; may follow the Godwoken on &lt;a href=\"The%20Lady%20Vengeance\"&gt;Lady Vengeance&lt;/a&gt; if her demands are met.\nPyrokinetic Skills.\nAbility Based.\nFollowing tables and sub-sections show pyrokinetic skills that can be learnt by character if they have enough point in Pyrokinetic ability. All of these skills can be crafted by combining corresponding scroll with &lt;a href=\"blank%20fire%20skillbook\"&gt;blank fire skillbook&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"high%20tier%20blank%20fire%20skillbook\"&gt;high tier blank fire skillbook&lt;/a&gt;. Note that not all skills have craftable scrolls. In base game (without cheats) skills from 9 level onward (Adept, Expert and Master tiers) can be gained only after escaping &lt;a href=\"Reaper%27s%20Eye\"&gt;Reaper's Eye&lt;/a&gt; island. \nEach spell belongs to a tier that is determined through characters level that determines whether it can be found and purchased and requires certain level in \"Pyrokinetic ability\" in order to memorise the spell. Higher Tier skills may require more memory in order to use them in combat, this especially applies to skills that require &lt;a href=\"Source\"&gt;Source&lt;/a&gt; in order to cast them. \nCraftable.\nFollowing skillbooks are classified as craftable for they can be obtained only by crafting them. They cannot be bought from any trader in the game. However it is possible to get them as quest reward or find them as random loot.\nBase skillbooks are obtained whenever non-source Pyrokinetic skillbook is combined with another non-source skillbook. Resulting skillbook will be a mix of both skillbooks and will require investment in both combat abilities under which the skillbooks belong. Example: In order to learn and cast Bleed Fire, character needs 1 point in both Pyrokinetic and Polymorph combat abilities.\nSource skillbooks are obtained whenever non-source Pyrokinetic skillbook is combined with source skillbook and vice versa. One way or another there has to be source skillbook involved in crafting otherwise the resulting book will be non-source skillbook. Like base craftable skillbooks these also cannot be bought from traders in game.\nOther Skills.\nOutside of player accesible and craftable skills, there are skills exclusive to NPCs that are also clasiffied as Pyrokinetic. Some of these are also accessible in Game Master Mode. Following table also includes skills exclusive to Gift Bag features such as which allows player character to cast Infusions unto any summoned creature. These infusions sometimes grant unique skills unseen in the base game (and Classic Edition of the game).\nItems.\nOutside of skills, the Pyrokinetic combat ability affects also all manner of items which can deal fire damage. Likewise the Pyrokinetic ability can be boosted through items that provide bonus to it. Most notably this includes all arrows, grenades, traps, equipment and lastly runes. \nAmmunition.\nFollowing arrows and grenades are magical items that can be used both in and outside of combat to cause fire damage and potentially create fire surfaces. All of the following arrows and grenades are empowered by Pyrokinetic combat ability. Note that in order to use arrows, character must have bow or crossbow equipped.\nFollowing items are exclusive to Gift Bag features, most notably Crafter's Kit, and as such cannot be obtained, made or otherwise seen in the base game unless the feature has been manually activated.\nEquipment.\nPyrokinetic combat ability is best paired with weapons that cause fire damage (most commonly staves and wands) and equipment that increases Pyrokinetic and Intelligence. \nRunes.\nAll equipment that has rune slots can be inserted with runes that will grant them additional properties. Most important rune for all who rely on Pyrokinetic ability is the &lt;a href=\"Flame%20Rune\"&gt;Flame Rune&lt;/a&gt;, which increases not only fire damage when inserted into weapon but also &lt;a href=\"Critical%20Chance\"&gt;Critical Chance&lt;/a&gt; when inserted into necklace and ring. Lastly the Flame Rune grants Fire Resistance when inserted into armour. If the base Flame Rune of any size is put into \"rune frame\" it will gain additional effects.\n&lt;a href=\"Flame%20Rune\"&gt;Mystical Flame Rune&lt;/a&gt; of any size provides 1 point bonus to either &lt;a href=\"Huntsman\"&gt;Huntsman&lt;/a&gt; (if inserted into armour), Pyrokinetic (if inserted into weapon) and &lt;a href=\"Ranged\"&gt;Ranged&lt;/a&gt; (if inserted into any necklace or ring) alongside its base effect.\n&lt;a href=\"Flame%20Rune\"&gt;Flame Rune of Power&lt;/a&gt; of any size will always provide bonus to &lt;a href=\"Intelligence\"&gt;Intelligence&lt;/a&gt; (depending on its size) whenever inserted into any equipment."}
