{"id": "10314", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=10314", "title": "Original Sin 2 Quests", "text": "Original Sin 2 Quests is a page detailing all \"quests\" and \"chronicles\" in \"\" game. With few exceptions all of these quests and chronicles are present in both \"Classic\" and \"Definitive Edition\" of the game. "}
{"id": "10880", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=10880", "title": "Original Sin 2 Races", "text": "Original Sin 2 Races shows and describes playable races in . \nOverview.\n&lt;a href=\"Elves\"&gt;Elves&lt;/a&gt;.\nInnate Talents.\n&lt;a href=\"Talents%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Elegant&lt;/a&gt;: Replaced by Ancestral Knowledge at full launch: Gives +1 to Loremaster\n&lt;a href=\"Talents%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Corpse Eater&lt;/a&gt;: Allows you to consume body parts and learn new skills from them. Also heals you.\nInnate Abilities.\n&lt;a href=\"Flesh%20Sacrifice\"&gt;Flesh Sacrifice&lt;/a&gt;: Grants 2 extra AP and 5% damage boost at the cost of Constitution points. The amount of points Constitution is lowered by varies depending on character level.\nElves make for good &lt;a href=\"Ranger%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Ranger&lt;/a&gt;s and &lt;a href=\"Rogue%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Rogue&lt;/a&gt;s due to their innate Finesse bonuses.\nDue to the elves' ability to gain memories from body parts they eat the elves are possibly the best race to play for story as you will gain more insight into characters and some relevant stories by consuming body parts.\n&lt;a href=\"Humans\"&gt;Humans&lt;/a&gt;.\nInnate Talents.\n1.\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0 Early release: \n2.\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0 Classic version: \n3.\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0 Definitive Edition: \nInnate Abilities.\n&lt;a href=\"Talents%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Encourage&lt;/a&gt;: Grants small boost to stats and heals for a small amount on cast.\nHumans are good for playing Rogues, &lt;a href=\"Shadowblade%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Shadowblade&lt;/a&gt;s or &lt;a href=\"Ranger%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Ranger&lt;/a&gt;s.\n&lt;a href=\"Lizards\"&gt;Lizards&lt;/a&gt;.\nInnate Talents.\n&lt;a href=\"Talents%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Sophisticated&lt;/a&gt;: Gives you +10% Fire resistance and +10% Poison resistance.\n&lt;a href=\"Talents%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Spellsong&lt;/a&gt;: Gives +1 in Persuasion.\nInnate Abilities.\n&lt;a href=\"Dragon%27s%20Blaze\"&gt;Dragon's Blaze&lt;/a&gt;: A small coned fire damage ability.\nDue to the Intelligence boost, Lizards make excellent spell casters such as &lt;a href=\"Wizard%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Wizard&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Witch%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Witch&lt;/a&gt;es or &lt;a href=\"Enchanter%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Enchanter&lt;/a&gt;s.\n&lt;a href=\"Dwarves\"&gt;Dwarves&lt;/a&gt;.\nInnate Talents.\n&lt;a href=\"Talents%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Sturdy&lt;/a&gt;: Gives +10% maximum Vitality and +5% Dodging.\n&lt;a href=\"Talents%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Dwarven Guile&lt;/a&gt;: +1 &lt;a href=\"Sneaking\"&gt;Sneak&lt;/a&gt;.\nInnate Abilities.\n&lt;a href=\"Petrifying%20Touch%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Petrifying Touch&lt;/a&gt;: Petrify a target, increases &lt;a href=\"Physical%20and%20Magical%20Armor%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Physical Armor&lt;/a&gt; and removes Bleeding, Burning, Poisoned and Crippled.\nDwarves make for great &lt;a href=\"Fighter%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Fighters&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Knight%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Knights&lt;/a&gt;.\n&lt;a href=\"Undead\"&gt;Undead&lt;/a&gt;.\nAbilities.\n&lt;a href=\"Play%20Dead\"&gt;Play Dead&lt;/a&gt;: The player falls to the ground pretending to be dead and loses aggression from NPCs.\nThe Undead are also harmed by healing potions and healing spells, so to heal them you need to inflict poison onto them, drink a poisoned health potion or walk into a poison field."}
