{"id": "11368", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=11368", "title": "Original Sin 2 Scoundrel", "text": "Scoundrel is a &lt;a href=\"Attributes%20and%20Abilities%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;combat ability&lt;/a&gt;, based on non-magical skill known as &lt;a href=\"Roguery\"&gt;roguery&lt;/a&gt; and is essential in memorising and using scoundrel based skills in \"\". \nDescription.\nThis combat ability focuses on mobility, invisibility, crowd control and high single target damage.\nBonuses Per Point Invested\nTraders.\nFollowing table shows all NPCs who are guaranteed to sell scoundrel skillbooks, with their location and coordinates in the right column, from them. The location shown in the table (and the coordinates) are only for the initial location the NPC is in. Note that some of these may have other spell/skillbooks and goods to sell.\nSkill Tiers.\nFollowing tables and sub-sections show scoundrel skills that can be learnt by character if they have enough point in Scoundrel ability. In base game (without cheats) spells from 9 level onward (Adept, Expert and Master tiers) can be gained only after escaping &lt;a href=\"Reaper%27s%20Eye\"&gt;Reaper's Eye&lt;/a&gt; island. \nEach skill belongs to a tier that is determined through characters level that determines whether it can be found and purchased and requires certain level in \"Scoundrel ability\" in order to memorise the skill. Higher Tier skills may require more memory in order to use them in combat, this especially applies to spells that require &lt;a href=\"Source\"&gt;Source&lt;/a&gt; in order to cast them. \nStarter.\nThis is the lowest tier which contains spells available during the Character Creation and can be purchased from vendors from start of the game.\nNovice.\nNovice Tier spells start to be available once characters reach level 4.\nAdept.\nAdept Tier spells start to be available once characters reach level 9.\nExpert.\nExpert Tier spells start to be available once characters reach level 13.\nMaster.\nMaster Tier spells start to be available once characters reach level 16.\nCraftable skills.\nFollowing skillbooks are classified as craftable for they can be obtained only by crafting them. They cannot be bought from any trader in the game. However possible to get them as quest reward or find them as random loot.\nBase.\nBase skillbooks are obtained whenever non-source Scoundrel skillbook is combined with another non-source skillbook. Resulting skillbook will be a mix of both skillbooks and will require investment in both combat abilities under which the skillbooks belong. Example: In order to learn and cast Sabotage, character needs 1 point in both Scoundrel and Pyrokinetic combat abilities.\nSource.\nSource skillbooks are obtained whenever non-source Scoundrel skillbook is combined with source skillbook and vice versa. One way or another there has to be source skillbook involved in crafting otherwise the resulting book will be non-source skillbook. Like base craftable skillbooks these also cannot be bought from traders in game. "}
{"id": "22735", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=22735", "title": "Original Sin 2 Scrolls", "text": ""}
{"id": "10340", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=10340", "title": "Original Sin 2 Skills", "text": "Skills are actions that consist of using weapons or magic in order to achieve desired effect during and outside of combat in \"\" game.\nGeneral Description.\nSkills are specific actions which any character (both Player and NPC) may take during and outside of combat itself. Each (player accessible) skill contains:\nCharacter may cast any skill they want both during and outside of combat if they meet certain criteria. These criteria wary, not just in the amount of AP and SP but also depending on type of the ability they fall under. Additionally, many skills rely also on Attributes which determine how strong is going to be the effect of said skill. \nImportant thing to note is that all skills (with the exception of skills that provide set bonuses such as &lt;a href=\"Haste%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Haste&lt;/a&gt;, or change environment like &lt;a href=\"Terrain%20Transmutation\"&gt;Terrain Transmutation&lt;/a&gt;) do not receive any bonuses from attributes or level of the caster. Nearly all skills however, are affected by &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Talents\"&gt;Talents&lt;/a&gt; of the caster.\nDue to some skills providing bonuses to range, base damage dealt it is possible for skills themselves to affect each other. Furthermore, depending on the effects of the skills, some skills may be affected by multiple abilities of different categories. For example all damage dealing skills are affected by &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Necromancer\"&gt;Necromancer&lt;/a&gt; ability which will restore the Vitality of the caster if they damage Vitality of their opponents. Essentialy this means that the effects of abilities can affect all skills the character has at their disposal if they meet the base criteria (ie. cause damage, are ranged etc.)\nIn case of &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Warfare\"&gt;Warfare&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Scoundrel\"&gt;Scoundrel&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Huntsman\"&gt;Hunstman&lt;/a&gt; abilities, their skills are additionally affected by weapons which the caster has equipped (this is seen in the damage calculation formula, which is different for magic-based abilities). The damage, which is most often of physical type (and thus affected by Warfare ability) drastically affects damage done by skills. The higher damage the weapon deals, the greater damage will be done by the skill that requires weapons. \nFollowing table shows all skill categories present in the game as well as attributes assigned to them (in terms of skills accessible to the Player character), alongside damage type the skills under that category do and what armour and resistances counter skills in said category.\nLearning and Using Skills.\nSkills are actions which can be learnt either by reading Skillbooks (which can be found on Rivellon, which includes buying or stealing them from NPCs), completing certain quests, equipping specific type of weapon or by eating limbs. The last applies only to &lt;a href=\"Elves\"&gt;Elven&lt;/a&gt; characters as they possess racial &lt;a href=\"Corpse%20Eater%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Corpse Eater&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Talents\"&gt;talent&lt;/a&gt;. \nIn order to learn desired skill from Skillbook, character must meet the required Ability points criteria and in order to use the skill, character must have at least 1 free Memory slot for it. Ability skills using Source require at minimum 2 Memory slots. \nSome skills, most notably those of &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Polymorph\"&gt;Polymorph&lt;/a&gt; category, are automatically learnt and available to the caster once specific skill has been cast. For example &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Polymorph\"&gt;Polymorph&lt;/a&gt; skill &lt;a href=\"Spread%20Your%20Wings\"&gt;Spread Your Wings&lt;/a&gt; will grant the caster skill &lt;a href=\"Flight\"&gt;Flight&lt;/a&gt; which can be used for as long as the skill &lt;a href=\"Spread%20Your%20Wings\"&gt;Spread Your Wings&lt;/a&gt; is active. \nFurthermore the &lt;a href=\"Flight\"&gt;Flight&lt;/a&gt; skill can be learnt and cast if character has unique chestplate called &lt;a href=\"Kvyn%27s%20Heart\"&gt;Kvyn's Heart&lt;/a&gt; equipped. Should the chestplate be equipped character will forget &lt;a href=\"Flight\"&gt;Flight&lt;/a&gt; skill. Note that skill learnt before equipping item that grants them are not unlearnt. The difference is that skills granted by items do not require \"Memory\" or \"Ability\" criteria to be met.\nOutside of quests and limbs, it is possible to craft skillbooks out of scrolls if they are combined with the correct tier of blank skillbook. All skills from Starter to Adept tier (from level 1 to 9 respectively) require base Blank Skillbook, while Expert and Master tier (from level 13 to 16) require High Tier Blank Skillbooks. For example it is possible to craft &lt;a href=\"Fireball%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Fireball skillbook&lt;/a&gt; by combining Fireball Scroll with a &lt;a href=\"Blank%20Fire%20Skillbook\"&gt;Blank Fire Skillbook&lt;/a&gt;, but &lt;a href=\"Epidemic%20of%20Fire\"&gt;Epidemic of Fire&lt;/a&gt; skill requires Epidemic of Fire scroll in combination with &lt;a href=\"Blank%20Fire%20Skillbook\"&gt;High Tier Blank Fire Skillbook&lt;/a&gt;. \nThere are certain skills however, that can be learnt only by combining two different skillbooks. These skills can be found randomly across &lt;a href=\"Rivellon\"&gt;Rivellon&lt;/a&gt;, but they will never be sold by NPCs. \nSkills are used by selecting them from the bottom hotbar. Skills that require a target to be selected (whether area, character or object) will cause character to enter a \"casting\" animation and prompt player to select desired target. Some skills such as &lt;a href=\"Spread%20Your%20Wings\"&gt;Spread Your Wings&lt;/a&gt; will omit this action and immediately cast the skill as their only target is caster themselves. \nAll skills require certain amount of &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Action%20Points\"&gt;Action Points&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Source%20Points\"&gt;Source Points&lt;/a&gt; in order to be cast during combat. If this criteria is not met, character will not be able to cast desired skill. Note that in case of Magic based skills and few Weapon-based skills it is possible to prevent character from casting these by having them be afflicted with &lt;a href=\"Silenced%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Silenced&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Enraged%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Enraged&lt;/a&gt; status effects.\nAll skills can be cast only once per turn, with number on the bottom left of the screen indicating how many turns must the character wait before they can use the skill again. The cooldown lenght varies between skills. There are some skills such as &lt;a href=\"Apotheosis\"&gt;Apotheosis&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Time%20Warp\"&gt;Time Warp&lt;/a&gt; which can be used only once per combat while others such as &lt;a href=\"Staff%20of%20Magus\"&gt;Staff of Magus&lt;/a&gt; can be used every turn. \nList of Skills.\nAbility Skills.\nAbility skills are the most common type of skill the Player is going to encounter and learn in the game itself. These are the skills the Player may buy and steal from NPC Traders or loot from containers across the world. These skills are separated into 6 tiers, 5 of which are centered around the Level of the Player character.\nSkills which do not rely on character level are regarded as Tierless skill. These skills can be mostly learnt through crafting, completing quests, acquiring specific equipment or summoning creatures who can use said skills.\nSpecial Skills.\nSpecial skills are Tierless skills which are automatically learnt by the Player Character and do not require any Ability or Memory slots. This category can be divided into 3 sub-categories:\n&lt;a href=\"Sourcery%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Sourcery Skills&lt;/a&gt;.\nSourcery skills are skills that rely solely on Source magic. They are acquired only through quests or by wearing unique equipment. Outside of the skill Bless (which requires 1 Memory slot) they do not require Memory Slots. Additionaly only &lt;a href=\"Curse%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Curse&lt;/a&gt; skill can be crafted in the form of a scroll.\nNote that using &lt;a href=\"Source%20Vampirism\"&gt;Source Vampirism&lt;/a&gt; will make casting character unable to pass the &lt;a href=\"the%20Path%20of%20Blood\"&gt;Path of Blood&lt;/a&gt;.\nCraftable Skills.\nFollowing table shows skills which cannot be bought from NPCs. Instead they are crafted by combining two different skillbooks. In order to use these, character must have sufficient Ability points in two Ability categories to which the original skillbooks belonged.\nFor example in order to craft the skill &lt;a href=\"Breathing%20Bubble\"&gt;Breathing Bubble&lt;/a&gt;, character must combine non-source &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Aerotheurge\"&gt;Aerotheurge&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Warfare\"&gt;Warfare&lt;/a&gt; skillbooks. In order to learn and use it character must have at least 1 point into Aerotheurge and Warfare.\nOther Skills.\nFollowing skills are Tierless skills which cannot be bought or crafted by the Player character like Ability skills from above. \nThe column \"Summon Skills\" shows skills which are available to summoned creatures in the base game. These skills are automatically learnt and usable by the summoned creatures and follow the same rules as base ability skills (Action Point requirement, Cooldown, Level scaling etc.) Note that the table shows skills exclusive to the Summoned creatures; Incarnate may learn ability skills such as &lt;a href=\"Tactical%20Retreat%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Tactical Retreat&lt;/a&gt; if they are under the influence of &lt;a href=\"Warp%20Infusion\"&gt;Warp Infusion&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Summoning\"&gt;Summoning&lt;/a&gt; skill.\nNPC column shows skills exclusive to the \"Non-Playable Characters\" and skills which are categorised as \"Monster\" skills in Game Master Mode (GM). Large part of these skills cannot be learnt and used by the Player Character on their own.\nThe last column Gift Bag Exclusive Skills shows skills which are exclusive to any of the Gift Bag features released by the Larian Studios. Most of these skills fall under (marked as PP in table) which allowed Player to cast Infusion skills unto all summoned creatures. These infusions in some cases unlocked unique skills unseen in the base game such as &lt;a href=\"Deviant%20Blood%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Deviant Blood&lt;/a&gt;. Lastly some skills have been added to the game as part of the final (marked as FRR in table) which centers around 4 unique sets of armour which some grant unique skills to the Player. For example the Contamination Armour Set grants the Player unique &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Geomancer\"&gt;Geomancer&lt;/a&gt; skill called &lt;a href=\"Trigger%20Spores%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Trigger Spores&lt;/a&gt;."}
