{"id": "11369", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=11369", "title": "Original Sin 2 Summoning", "text": "Summoning is a &lt;a href=\"Attributes%20and%20Abilities%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;combat ability&lt;/a&gt;, utilising magic known as &lt;a href=\"Summoning\"&gt;summoning&lt;/a&gt; and essential for casting summoning &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Skills\"&gt;skills&lt;/a&gt; in \"\". \nDescription.\nIt allows the character to summon aid in the form of minions which can be buffed in order to expand their repertoire of support, damage and mobility spells as well as change their direct damage type and resistances. For each point invested in this ability summoned creatures gain + 10% extra Vitality, Damage, Physical Armour and Magic Armour.\nTraders.\nFollowing table shows all NPCs who are guaranteed to sell summoning spellbooks, with their location and coordinates in the right column, from them. The location shown in the table (and the coordinates) are only for the initial location the NPC is in.\nSpell Tiers.\nFollowing tables and sub-sections show summoning spells that can be learnt by character if they have enough point in Summoning ability. All of these spells can be crafted by combining corresponding scroll with &lt;a href=\"Blank%20Summoning%20Skillbook\"&gt;blank summoning skillbook&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Blank%20Summoning%20Skillbook\"&gt;high tier blank summoning skillbook&lt;/a&gt;. Note that not all spells have craftable scrolls. In base game (without cheats) spells from 9 level onward (Adept, Expert and Master tiers) can be gained only after escaping &lt;a href=\"Reaper%27s%20Eye\"&gt;Reaper's Eye&lt;/a&gt; island. \nEach spell belongs to a tier that is determined through characters level that determines whether it can be found and purchased and requires certain level in \"Summoning ability\" in order to memorise the spell. Higher Tier spells may require more memory in order to use them in combat, this especially applies to spells that require &lt;a href=\"Source\"&gt;Source&lt;/a&gt; in order to cast them. \nStarter Tier.\nThis is the lowest tier which contains spells available during the Character Creation and can be purchased from vendors from start of the game.\nNovice Tier.\nNovice Tier spells start to be available once characters reach level 4.\nAdept Tier.\nAdept Tier spells start to be available once characters reach level 9.\nExpert Tier.\nExpert Tier spells start to be available once characters reach level 13.\nMaster Tier.\nMaster Tier spells start to be available once characters reach level 16.\nCraftable.\nFollowing skillbooks are classified as craftable for they can be obtained only by crafting them. They cannot be bought from any trader in the game. However possible to get them as quest reward or find them as random loot.\nNote that all of the following infusions are available in the base game and do not require any gift bags in order to work. All of these infusions are usable only on the &lt;a href=\"Conjure%20Incarnate\"&gt;Incarnate&lt;/a&gt; in the base game.\nBase.\nBase skillbooks are obtained whenever non-source Summoning skillbook is combined with another non-source skillbook. Resulting skillbook will be a mix of both skillbooks and will require investment in both combat abilities under which the skillbooks belong. Example: In order to learn and cast Fire Infusion, character needs 1 point in both Summoning and Pyrokinetic combat abilities.\nSource.\nSource skillbooks are obtained whenever non-source Summoning skillbook is combined with source skillbook and vice versa. One way or another there has to be source skillbook involved in crafting otherwise the resulting book will be non-source skillbook. Like base craftable skillbooks these also cannot be bought from traders in game.\nSpecial.\nThese spells are special, due to them being exclusive to certain characters, or acquirable through specific means outside of crafting, finding or buying them. \nSummoned Creatures list.\nAll of these spells (save for &lt;a href=\"Summon%20Inner%20Demon\"&gt;Summon Inner Demon&lt;/a&gt;) allow the caster to summon additional help in combat which will act as a temporary companion and as such will receive a bonus from Summoning ability even if their ability type does not match it. There can be only one summoned creature per character, summoning any other creature will cause the previous one to disappear. None of these can be infused or adapted through surfaces by normal means. \nGift Bag: Pet Power.\nGift Bag: Pet Power grants 4 new craftable spells which can be used not only on the &lt;a href=\"Conjure%20Incarnate\"&gt;Incarnate&lt;/a&gt; but also on all other summoned creatures (Not limited on summoned creatures summoned through Summoning skill). Their cooldowns also had been reduced from 3 turns to 1 turn. \nCraftable Infusions.\nFollowing infusions require gift bag: Pet Power in order to be craftable and usable. Non-source skills gained by casting said shown spells are based upon infusing conjured incarnate. "}
{"id": "10455", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=10455", "title": "Original Sin 2 Talents", "text": "Talents are abilities which can be given to a character once they reach certain level in \"\". Talents are acquired by spending \"talent points\" which are automatically given to characters once they reach levels 1, 3, 8, 13 and 18. Each talent costs 1 talent point. Certain interactions may also give a talent point. For example speaking with &lt;a href=\"Karon\"&gt;Karon&lt;/a&gt;'s spirit after defeating him can grant a talent point. 2 Talent points can also be gained if &lt;a href=\"Undead\"&gt;Undead&lt;/a&gt; character or &lt;a href=\"Fane\"&gt;Fane&lt;/a&gt; become &lt;a href=\"Sworn\"&gt;Sworn&lt;/a&gt; to the &lt;a href=\"God%20King\"&gt;God King&lt;/a&gt;. \nTalents.\n\"Divine Talents\" gift bag.\nThese talents require the activation of gift bag \"Divine Talents\", note that this is a permanent modification which cannot be removed and it will disable achievments. The game will automatically save and load after activating it."}
{"id": "11370", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=11370", "title": "Original Sin 2 Warfare", "text": "Warfare is a &lt;a href=\"Attributes%20and%20Abilities%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;combat ability&lt;/a&gt;, based on non-magical skill known as &lt;a href=\"warfare\"&gt;warfare&lt;/a&gt; and essential for memorising and using warfare skills in \"\". \nDescription.\nBonuses Per Point Invested\nAll tiers - Physical damage increased by 5%\nTraders.\nFollowing table shows all NPCs who are guaranteed to sell warfare skillbooks, with their location and coordinates in the right column, from them. The location shown in the table (and the coordinates) are only for the initial location the NPC is in. Note that some of these may have other spell/skillbooks and goods to sell. &lt;a href=\"Gareth\"&gt;Gareth&lt;/a&gt; may follow the Godwoken on &lt;a href=\"The%20Lady%20Vengeance\"&gt;Lady Vengeance&lt;/a&gt; if his demands are met.\nSkill Tiers.\nFollowing tables and sub-sections show warfare skills that can be learnt by character if they have enough point in Warfare ability. In base game (without cheats) spells from 9 level onward (Adept, Expert and Master tiers) can be gained only after escaping &lt;a href=\"Reaper%27s%20Eye\"&gt;Reaper's Eye&lt;/a&gt; island. \nEach skill belongs to a tier that is determined through characters level that determines whether it can be found and purchased and requires certain level in \"Warfare ability\" in order to memorise the skill. Higher Tier skills may require more memory in order to use them in combat, this especially applies to spells that require &lt;a href=\"Source\"&gt;Source&lt;/a&gt; in order to cast them. \nStarter.\nThis is the lowest tier which contains spells available during the Character Creation and can be purchased from vendors from start of the game.\nNovice.\nNovice Tier spells start to be available once characters reach level 4.\nAdept.\nAdept Tier spells start to be available once characters reach level 9.\nExpert.\nExpert Tier spells start to be available once characters reach level 13.\nMaster.\nMaster Tier spells start to be available once characters reach level 16.\nCraftable skills.\nFollowing skillbooks are classified as craftable for they can be obtained only by crafting them. They cannot be bought from any trader in the game. However possible to get them as quest reward or find them as random loot.\nBase.\nBase skillbooks are obtained whenever non-source Warfare skillbook is combined with another non-source skillbook. Resulting skillbook will be a mix of both skillbooks and will require investment in both combat abilities under which the skillbooks belong. Example: In order to learn and cast Breathing Bubble, character needs 1 point in both Warfare and Aerotheurge combat abilities.\nSource.\nSource skillbooks are obtained whenever non-source Warfare skillbook is combined with source skillbook and vice versa. One way or another there has to be source skillbook involved in crafting otherwise the resulting book will be non-source skillbook. Like base craftable skillbooks these also cannot be bought from traders in game. "}
{"id": "10377", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=10377", "title": "Original Sin 2 Weapons", "text": "Weapons are items which can be equipped by characters and used in order to damage their enemies in \"\". There are three kinds of weapons, one-handed, two-handed weapons and ranged weapons. \nDamage types.\nThere are overall 3 types of damage depending on the armour types. First is physical damage which is resisted only by physical armour. Second is piercing damage which directly damages Vitality regardless of armour. Third and last is magic damage which is further divided into fire, earth, air, water and poison damage, and is resisted only by magic armour. All damage scales with weapon level, the higher level weapon has the higher its damage will be.\nOne-Handed weapons.\nOne handed weapons are weapons which can be held in one hand. These weapons include daggers, wands and one-handed swords, axes and maces. All of these weapons can be also put in second hand in order to use two one-handed weapons. Depending on whether one or both hands are used, these weapons benefit from &lt;a href=\"Single-Handed%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Single-Handed&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Dual%20Wielding\"&gt;Dual Wielding&lt;/a&gt; combat abilities. One-handed weapons are the only weapons which can be used alongside shields. \nDagger.\nDagger is a one-handed weapon which relies on &lt;a href=\"Finesse\"&gt;Finesse&lt;/a&gt; attribute. It is the only weapon which can be used to \"backstab\" enemy, in order to deal them guaranteed critical damage. &lt;a href=\"Sheep%20Shears\"&gt;Sheep Shears&lt;/a&gt; are also the only way to get &lt;a href=\"Wool\"&gt;Wool&lt;/a&gt; from Sheep. \nOne-Handed Axe.\nAxes are melee weapons which rely on &lt;a href=\"Strength\"&gt;Strength&lt;/a&gt; to be used. \nOne-Handed Mace.\nMaces are melee weapons which rely on &lt;a href=\"Strength\"&gt;Strength&lt;/a&gt; to be used. \nOne-Handed Sword.\nSwords are melee weapons which rely on &lt;a href=\"Strength\"&gt;Strength&lt;/a&gt; to be used. \nShield.\nShields are one-handed weapons which can be used only off-hand in combination with other one-handed weapon of different type (example: One-Handed Sword, Wand etc.) . They rely on &lt;a href=\"Constitution\"&gt;Constitution&lt;/a&gt; in order to be used. They are required for the &lt;a href=\"Warfare\"&gt;warfare&lt;/a&gt; skill &lt;a href=\"Bouncing%20Shield\"&gt;Bouncing Shield&lt;/a&gt; and greatly boost physical and magical armour. Using shield gives character &lt;a href=\"Special%20Skills%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;special&lt;/a&gt; skill &lt;a href=\"Shields%20Up%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Shields Up&lt;/a&gt; \nWand.\nWands are one-handed weapons used by mages. Wands require &lt;a href=\"Intelligence\"&gt;Intelligence&lt;/a&gt; in order to be used and benefit from &lt;a href=\"Single-Handed%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Single-Handed&lt;/a&gt; combat ability. Aside from Unique wands, all wands deal random elemental damage which is either: air, earth, water, fire or poison.\nTwo-Handed.\nTwo-Handed weapons are weapons which require both hands to be wielded. Therefore they cannot be wielded simultaneously with other weapon. All Two-Handed weapons benefit from &lt;a href=\"Two-Handed%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Two-Handed&lt;/a&gt; combat ability. \nTwo-Handed Axe.\nTwo-Handed axes are weapons used by &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Classes\"&gt;Warriors&lt;/a&gt;. They require &lt;a href=\"Strength\"&gt;Strength&lt;/a&gt; in order to be used. \nTwo-Handed Mace.\nTwo-Handed maces are weapons used by &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Classes\"&gt;Warriors&lt;/a&gt;. They require &lt;a href=\"Strength\"&gt;Strength&lt;/a&gt; in order to be used.\nTwo-Handed Sword.\nTwo-Handed swords are weapons used by &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Classes\"&gt;Warriors&lt;/a&gt;. They require &lt;a href=\"Strength\"&gt;Strength&lt;/a&gt; in order to be used. \nSpear.\nSpears are two-handed weapons used by &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Classes\"&gt;Survivors&lt;/a&gt;. Spears require &lt;a href=\"Finesse\"&gt;Finesse&lt;/a&gt; in order to be used.\nStaff.\nStaff is a two-handed melee weapon which is best utilised by &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Classes\"&gt;mages&lt;/a&gt;. They require &lt;a href=\"Intelligence\"&gt;Intelligence&lt;/a&gt; to be wielded and deal elemental damage with their basic attack. Once per turn its wielder may harness &lt;a href=\"Staff%20of%20Magus\"&gt;Staff of Magus&lt;/a&gt; to throw an elemental projectile upon their enemy. \nRanged.\nRanged weapons include weapons that deal base damage to enemies from afar. These include bows and crossbows and as the name implies, these weapons gain bonus from &lt;a href=\"Ranged\"&gt;Ranged&lt;/a&gt; combat ability. Besides Ranged ability these weapon require sufficient &lt;a href=\"Finesse\"&gt;Finesse&lt;/a&gt; in order to be used. Their damage also scales with &lt;a href=\"Finesse\"&gt;Finesse&lt;/a&gt;."}
