{"id": "11432", "revid": "27868532", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=11432", "title": "Original Sin Characters", "text": "From the typical human, to imps and lizards, there is a wide range of characters in \"\".\nPlayer Characters.\nAt the start of the game you can create and fully customize two characters. Later in the game, you can hire two additional characters.\nYou can choose a predefined class for your characters or create your own."}
{"id": "5581", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5581", "title": "Original Sin Classes", "text": "The classes are specialisations of the &lt;a href=\"Source%20Hunters\"&gt;Source Hunters&lt;/a&gt; and their &lt;a href=\"Companions%20%28Original%20Sin%29\"&gt;companions&lt;/a&gt; in \"\" and .\nOverview.\n&lt;a href=\"Class\"&gt;Class&lt;/a&gt;es in \"Divinity: Original Sin\" form the basis of the two Source Hunters &lt;a href=\"Abilities%20%28Original%20Sin%29\"&gt;Abilities&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Attributes%20%28Original%20Sin%29\"&gt;Attributes&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Skills%20%28Original%20Sin%29\"&gt;Skills&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%20Talents\"&gt;Talents&lt;/a&gt;. Additionally it determines the two Hunters &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%20Weapons\"&gt;weapons&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%20Armour\"&gt;armour&lt;/a&gt;.\nIn total there are 12 classes, which fall into one of three groups: Warrior, Mage and Survivor. Each class will allocate a total of 5 points to each player characters' &lt;a href=\"Attributes%20%28Original%20Sin%29\"&gt;Attributes&lt;/a&gt;.\nMage classes.\nMage classes abilities stem from the various magic schools, most prefer to use long range attacks or &lt;a href=\"Skills%20%28Original%20Sin%29\"&gt;summons&lt;/a&gt;, with the exception of , who use a mixture of close and long range techniques.\n&lt;a href=\"Cleric%20%28Original%20Sin%29\"&gt;Cleric&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe cleric is a mage who specialises in &lt;a href=\"Hydrosophist\"&gt;Hydrosophist&lt;/a&gt; magic, which they complement with martial &lt;a href=\"Man-at-Arms%20%28Original%20Sin%29\"&gt;Man-at-Arms&lt;/a&gt; skills. Their weapon of choice is a one-handed mace complemented with a shield. They utilise &lt;a href=\"Melee%20Power%20Stance\"&gt;Melee Power Stance&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Divine%20Light\"&gt;Divine Light&lt;/a&gt; to hinder their enemies and either &lt;a href=\"Minor%20Heal\"&gt;Minor Heal&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Regeneration%20%28DOS%20EE%29\"&gt;Regeneration&lt;/a&gt; spell to support their allies. \n&lt;a href=\"Enchanter%20%28Original%20Sin%29\"&gt;Enchanter&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe enchanter is a mage who specialises in &lt;a href=\"Hydrosophist\"&gt;Hydrosophist&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Aerotheurge\"&gt;Aerotheurge&lt;/a&gt; magic, which they accompany with their &lt;a href=\"Telekinesis\"&gt;Telekinesis&lt;/a&gt; and either &lt;a href=\"Wand%20%28skill%29\"&gt;Wand&lt;/a&gt; (Enhanced Edition) or (Classic Edition) abilities. Their weapon of choice (depending on the setting) is either &lt;a href=\"Source%20Hunter%27s%20Air%20Staff\"&gt;Source Hunter's Air Staff&lt;/a&gt; (Classic Edition) or one-handed &lt;a href=\"Old%20Wooden%20Water%20Wand\"&gt;Old Wooden Water Wand&lt;/a&gt; (Enhanced Edition). \n&lt;a href=\"Witch%20%28Original%20Sin%29\"&gt;Witch&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe witch is a mage who specialises in &lt;a href=\"Witchcraft\"&gt;Witchcraft&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Geomancer%20%28Original%20Sin%29\"&gt;Geomancer&lt;/a&gt; magic which they complement with their &lt;a href=\"Willpower%20%28Original%20Sin%29\"&gt;Willpower&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Loremaster\"&gt;Loremaster&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Charisma%20%28Original%20Sin%29\"&gt;Charisma&lt;/a&gt; abilities. Their weapon of choice is two-handed staff which they wield as they &lt;a href=\"Summon%20Spider\"&gt;summon spiders&lt;/a&gt; and weaken their foes.\n&lt;a href=\"Wizard%20%28Original%20Sin%29\"&gt;Wizard&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe wizard is a mage who specialises in &lt;a href=\"Pyrokinetic\"&gt;Pyrokinetic&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Geomancer\"&gt;Geomancer&lt;/a&gt; magic which they complement with their &lt;a href=\"Loremaster\"&gt;Loremaster&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Willpower%20%28Original%20Sin%29\"&gt;Willpower&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Charisma%20%28Original%20Sin%29\"&gt;Charisma&lt;/a&gt; abilities. Their weapon of choice is two-handed staff which they wield as they decimate their enemies from far distance.\nSurvivor classes.\nSurvivors rely on fast attacks and skills such as theft and lock picking to complete their objectives. Their primary interest is in their well-being and self preservation.\n&lt;a href=\"Ranger%20%28Original%20Sin%29\"&gt;Ranger&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe ranger is a survivor who utilises &lt;a href=\"Expert%20Marksman\"&gt;Expert Marksman&lt;/a&gt; ability to shoot their enemies from afar. Their weapon of choice is always a bow. Additionaly they rely on their &lt;a href=\"Crafting\"&gt;Crafting&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Loremaster\"&gt;Loremaster&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Blacksmithing%20%28Original%20Sin%29\"&gt;Blacksmithing&lt;/a&gt; abilities to craft special arrows, depending on their enemies weaknesses. \n&lt;a href=\"Rogue%20%28Original%20Sin%29\"&gt;Rogue&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe rogue is a survivor who utilises &lt;a href=\"Scoundrel\"&gt;Scoundrel&lt;/a&gt; ability in combination with &lt;a href=\"Sneaking%20%28DOS%20EE%29\"&gt;Sneaking&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Lockpicking%20%28Original%20Sin%29\"&gt;Lockpicking&lt;/a&gt; in order to backstab their foes and additionaly open few locked doors or chests. Their weapon of choice are always one-handed daggers either wielded in single or both hands. \n&lt;a href=\"Shadowblade%20%28Original%20Sin%29\"&gt;Shadowblade&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe shadowblade is a survivor who utilises &lt;a href=\"Scoundrel\"&gt;Scoundrel&lt;/a&gt; ability in combination with &lt;a href=\"Witchcraft\"&gt;Witchcraft&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Aerotheurge\"&gt;Aerotheurge&lt;/a&gt; magic. They primarily rely on their ability to &lt;a href=\"Sneaking%20%28DOS%20EE%29\"&gt;sneak&lt;/a&gt; in order to backstab their enemies with either a single dagger or dagger and a one-handed sword. Depending on their specialisation in &lt;a href=\"Single-handed%20%28DOS%20EE%29\"&gt;Single-handed&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Dual%20Wielding\"&gt;Dual Wielding&lt;/a&gt; abilities. If they cannot backstab their foes up-close they may resort to magic in order to hinder, or otherwise eliminate their foes. \n&lt;a href=\"Wayfarer%20%28Original%20Sin%29\"&gt;Wayfarer&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe wayfarer is a survivor who utilises &lt;a href=\"Expert%20Marksman\"&gt;Expert Marksman&lt;/a&gt; ability in combination with &lt;a href=\"Hydrosophist%20%28Original%20Sin%29\"&gt;Hydrosophist&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Geomancer\"&gt;Geomancer&lt;/a&gt; magic. Their weapon of choice is either &lt;a href=\"Source%20Hunter%27s%20Bow\"&gt;Source Hunter's Bow&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Light%20Old%20Crossbow\"&gt;Light Old Crossbow&lt;/a&gt; depending on whether they specialise in wielding &lt;a href=\"Bow\"&gt;Bow&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Crossbow%20%28Original%20Sin%29\"&gt;Crossbow&lt;/a&gt;.\nWarrior classes.\nWarrior classes focus primarily on physical attack and defence and as such, are best suited to close quarters combat.\n&lt;a href=\"Battlemage%20%28Original%20Sin%29\"&gt;Battlemage&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe battlemage is a warrior who utilises &lt;a href=\"Witchcraft\"&gt;Witchcraft&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Pyrokinetic\"&gt;Pyrokinetic&lt;/a&gt; magic alongside their martial &lt;a href=\"Single-handed%20%28DOS%20EE%29\"&gt;Single-handed&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Man-at-Arms%20%28Original%20Sin%29\"&gt;Man-at-Arms&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Armour%20Specialist%20%28DOS%20EE%29\"&gt;Armour Specialist&lt;/a&gt; combat skills. Their weapon of choice is one-handed weapon and shield. \n&lt;a href=\"Fighter%20%28Original%20Sin%29\"&gt;Fighter&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe fighter is a brutal warrior and expert in close combat. Focusing on &lt;a href=\"Single-handed%20%28DOS%20EE%29\"&gt;single-handed&lt;/a&gt; weaponry, and skills, the fighter begins initially with &lt;a href=\"Battering%20Ram\"&gt;Battering Ram&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Melee%20Power%20Stance\"&gt;Melee Power Stance&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Dust%20Devil\"&gt;Dust Devil&lt;/a&gt;. Allowing them to charge into battle, focus on hard hitting attacks and deal damage to those around them respectively. In addition to this, they also focus on , and to be able to withstand oncoming attacks.\n&lt;a href=\"Inquisitor%20%28Original%20Sin%29\"&gt;Inquisitor&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe Inquisitor is a warrior who utilises pure &lt;a href=\"Witchcraft\"&gt;Witchcraft&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Pyrokinetic\"&gt;Pyrokinetic&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Aerotheurge\"&gt;Aerotheurge&lt;/a&gt; magic when dealing with enemies up close. Their weapon of choice are dual-wielded wands which they use to deal with their foes up range. If needed they can use their spells to decimate enemies near them. \n&lt;a href=\"Knight%20%28Original%20Sin%29\"&gt;Knight&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe knight is the counterpart to the fighter, focusing more on hitting hard with a large blade than defending themselves with a shield. They do however, balance this out with a focus on healing their comrades and &lt;a href=\"Encourage\"&gt;encouraging&lt;/a&gt; them into battle."}
