{"id": "6144", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=6144", "title": "Original Sin Pyrokinetic", "text": "Pyrokinetic is the skillful manipulation of the fire element, and many of the skills in this group are Area of Effect skills (e.g. &lt;a href=\"Small%20Fireball\"&gt;Small Fireball&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Infectious%20Flame\"&gt;Infectious Flame&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Meteor%20Shower\"&gt;Meteor Shower&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Lava%20Core\"&gt;Lava Core&lt;/a&gt;), which can affect harm allies caught in the crossfire. Mastery of Pyrokinetics depends on a character's &lt;a href=\"Intelligence\"&gt;Intelligence&lt;/a&gt;.\nPyrokinetic abilities can be used in conjunction with oil surfaces; not necessarily to damage enemies but to control the battlefield. Setting an oil surface aflame will create a dark cloud that impedes targeting both inside and through it. As such, pyrokinetics can be used to mitigate damage, force enemies to walk through a fire surface or funnel them into a specific location.\nOriginal Sin.\nPyrokinetics has the only Stun-removal skill in game, Purifying Fire. The most damaging of the Elemental skill groups, Pyrokinetic skills only have one detrimental Status Effect: , which deals additional damage over time.\nAdditionally, reaching level 5 will allow the character to accept the Demon talent, which grants a chance to burn an opponent who strikes with a melee weapon however, the character earns a permanent 25% penalty to Water Resistance. \nEnhanced Edition.\nThe bracket after the CD of each skill indicates the minimum cooldown (achieved when INT is 15 or higher).\n\u221e) Can only be cast once per combat."}
