{"id": "18941", "revid": "54598427", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=18941", "title": "Original Sin Secrets", "text": "Secrets are maps and rewards that can be obtained by purchasing the relevant map from the &lt;a href=\"Teller%20of%20Secrets\"&gt;Teller of Secrets&lt;/a&gt;.\nOverview.\nEach secret purchased and then read will add a clue to the secrets section on your map along with a corresponding marker in the relevant area. If you have already found a secret, trying to read the purchased secret will make your character say \"I've already read this!\". For this reason it is advised to save before purchasing if you wish to avoid disappointment. Or not, it depends how much you like to roleplay these things!\nAll secrets can be found through normal play by either looking in the right place, pushing the right button, or by doing the above but with a certain Perception skill.\nSecret of the Black Cove Pirates: A bloodied gift from the stars has upset many a ghost's journey in the Black Cove.\nThis treasure is located in Black Cove's final area where you face Pontius. The loot is Pontius' Chest.\nMaradino claims his prize in Luculla came from the stars themselves\nThe Nested Library: Under the altar of the old cathedral of Luculla lies a library that houses many secrets.\nThe Iron Maiden: A common iron maiden became enchanted when she recieved a dark blessing from a mad king.\nThe Treasures of the Winter King: The Winter King's castle houses one of the largest treasure rooms in the Realm of Faery.\nThe Bloodied Chest: Behind every darkness, there is a spot of light.\nThe Pirate's key: The Black Cove's fiercest pirate seems to have dropped a key in this area.\nThis treasure is located in Black Cove's final area where you face Pontius. The loot is a key.\nBuried Treasure: Rumours say that when the White Witch heard her sister was coming for her, she buried a treasure just here.\nA Secluded Secret: This chest is protected by the enchanted waters of Luculla, realm of the White Witch.\nThe Lair of the Mysterious Wizard: The great Maradino is rumoured to have constructed his lair in the impenetrable high plains of Luculla.\nThe Frozen Chest: Rumours say a secret chest is waiting buried in the snows of Hiberheim, free for the taking to any intrepid adventurer.\nThe Legend of the Lighthouse: Some say a paranoid old lighthouse keeper hid away his most effective defense mechanism in case of emergency.\nThe Dark King's Knowledge: Many a great war was won with this particular spell at the Dark King's side.\nThe Cultist's Secret: Some say an entire town of non-believers could be laid low by a single shot from this terrible skill.\nKnowledge of the Dead: This rare skill book is said to sweep the dead from Rivellon and straight into the Hall of Echoes.\nForgotten Legends: An aged necromancer left this ancient tome as his last legacy, hoping none would uncover the dark power he had set loose...\nPlundered Loot: Some say a secret treasure is buried here...\nA Secret Grimoire: According to legend, this rare tome contains the power to fry enemies to a crisp.\nWhat the Witch Knew: Harness the power of the forest with a skillbook as rare as it is legendary.\nForbidden Knowledge: Deep beneath the Phantom Forest, legends of an ancient skillbook have tempted those unable to reach its depths.\nSnow and Ice: In this land of winter, ice magic was perfected many eons ago...\nSealed Secrets: In the Phantom Forest's darkest dungeons, ancient secrets lie dormant."}
{"id": "4978", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4978", "title": "Original Sin Skills", "text": "Skills are actions or spells that can be performed by a character that cause a particular effect dependent on the skill. They have a cooldown, which determines the number of turns the character must wait between each use. They also have an &lt;a href=\"Action%20Points%20%28Original%20Sin%29\"&gt;Action Point&lt;/a&gt; (AP) cost, which is deducted from the character's available AP upon use.\nLearning Skills.\nSkills are learned permanently by using Skill Books, which can be bought from &lt;a href=\"%23Vendors\"&gt;vendors&lt;/a&gt; or found scattered throughout the world. Each Skill has a minimum Level requirement which must be reached before it can be learned from its associated Skill Book. Skills can be forgotten, which will free up the skill slot that it previously occupied. Once forgotten, a Skill can only be reacquired by finding another copy of the associated Skill Book.\nA character can learn up to 3 Skills associated with each Ability they have one point in, and every further Ability point invested increases this limit by 2, as shown in the table below.\nAbility Level Requirement.\nEach skill is associated with a specific , and requires a certain level of this Ability to be used effectively. if this level is not met, the AP cost of the skill is increased by 2 for each Ability level below the requirement.\nThe Maximum Skill Level is the soft max at which skills have a higher action point cost to use if they are beyond that level. Each level of the ability below the max adds 2 extra action points to the cost. For example, a 13th skill level spell used with only 1 level of the associated ability would cost 6 more action points than usual (+2 for each missing ability level).\nHere is an example of the AP cost of casting through different ability levels of Pyrokinetic.\nMinimum Attribute Effectiveness.\nEach skill is associated with a particular attribute. For example, Man at arms skills require strength while Pyrokinetic or Hydrosophist skills require intelligence.\nSkills have a minimum Attribute requirement based on their Skill level, as shown in table below. Each Attribute point below the requirement reduces the effectiveness of the Skill by 10%, while each Attribute point above the requirement grants a 5% bonus. This effectiveness modifies the chance that the skills status effect has of taking effect. The damage of the skill is also affected by the attribute requirement.\nFor example, if a 5th level skill has a 100% base chance to set a status, but you only have 8 of that attribute, the base chance will be 90% instead. If you instead have 12 of that attribute, the +3 extrapoints equates to a base chance of 115% to set the same status. This bonus is useful because each point of willpower or body building that an enemy might have gives them a 10% better chance to resist your spells, effectively offsetting your base chance.\nHere is an example of the effectiveness of casting Infectious Flame through different Intelligence levels.\nBase Cooldown.\nBase cooldown is the cooldown of a Skill with a base intelligence of 5. Every 2 after 4 int reduces the cooldown by 1 turn. For example, a character with 10 intelligence reduces magical cooldowns by 3 turns.\nThis only affects Magic Schools of Skills, which are , , , &lt;a href=\"Pyrokinetic\"&gt;Pyrokinetic&lt;/a&gt;, and .\nVendors.\nVendors reset their inventory the first time you talk to them, each time your character levels up. A good tip on trying to get a skillbook you want is to save just before talking to the vendor &amp; reloading the game until he/she has stock of the skillbook you want.\nHomestead.\nThere are Elemental Halls in &lt;a href=\"Homestead\"&gt;Homestead&lt;/a&gt; where you can buy skillbooks."}
