{"id": "16520", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=16520", "title": "Orivand", "text": " is a &lt;a href=\"The%20Magisters\"&gt;magister&lt;/a&gt; residing at &lt;a href=\"Fort%20Joy\"&gt;Fort Joy&lt;/a&gt; in 1242 AD.\nBackground.\nThe High Judge Orivand is a magister and leading figure of Fort Joy. He is in charge of purging the &lt;a href=\"Sourcerer\"&gt;Sourcerer&lt;/a&gt;s and carries this act in Hall of Penitence where he spends most of his time. \nOrivand firmly believes that what he does is right, however he realises that it is not pleasant and would not look forward into such a fate himself. He believes Sourcerers should be told why they have to be purged as part of \"education\" for all and that if Sourcerers are not purged &lt;a href=\"Rivellon\"&gt;Rivellon&lt;/a&gt; will continue to suffer from &lt;a href=\"Voidwoken\"&gt;Voidwoken&lt;/a&gt; attacks. Orivand also believes that purged Sourcerers are heroes (since they sacrificed the spark of life within them) and wonders whether they could not be used to build an army for the &lt;a href=\"Divine%20Order\"&gt;Divine Order&lt;/a&gt;. \nLoot Table.\nFollowing table shows all possible items which can be found in the corpse of the defeated NPC. Note that the properties of randomly obtained equipment may change (name, stats etc.). The amount of randomly obtained items such as potions, gold may also change.\nOrivand has been observed to drop uncommon (green) rarity armour or weapon and a random small rune. "}
