{"id": "14410", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=14410", "title": "Patriarch the Black", "text": " \nPatriarch the Black is an ancient &lt;a href=\"dragon\"&gt;dragon&lt;/a&gt; residing on &lt;a href=\"Rivellon\"&gt;Rivellon&lt;/a&gt;. His true name is so powerful that speaking it out loud would be like a spell that would utterly change the world, causing new creatures to spawn into existence. Simply thinking about his name may cause new breeds of flowers to sprout forth from the ground. \nBackground.\nOne of the last members of his race, Patriarch is an ancient &lt;a href=\"dragon\"&gt;dragon&lt;/a&gt; possibly as old as &lt;a href=\"Rivellon\"&gt;Rivellon&lt;/a&gt; itself. As one of the most powerful beings on Rivellon he has influenced on events throughout Rivellons history. It was he who had opened a portal to the &lt;a href=\"Hall%20of%20Echoes\"&gt;Hall of Echoes&lt;/a&gt; for &lt;a href=\"Maxos\"&gt;Maxos&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Yuthul%20Gor\"&gt;Yuthul Gor&lt;/a&gt;. \nIn 1218 AD he is encountered by &lt;a href=\"Lucian%20the%20Divine\"&gt;Lucian the Divine&lt;/a&gt; in the Yuthul Gor wastes and is subsequently tricked into revealing the secret of becoming a spirit.\nIn 1300 AD, he is approached by both &lt;a href=\"Damian\"&gt;Damian&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"the%20Dragon%20Knight\"&gt;the Dragon Knight&lt;/a&gt; in his lair in &lt;a href=\"Orobas%20Fjords\"&gt;Orobas Fjords&lt;/a&gt;, who want a portal to the Hall of Echoes opening; for Damian he refuses, but opens the path for the Dragon Knight, creating the entryway beneath the roots of &lt;a href=\"Irminsul\"&gt;Irminsul&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "19308", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=19308", "title": "Patrick", "text": " is one of the &lt;a href=\"Humans\"&gt;human&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Divine%20Divinity%20characters\"&gt;noblemen&lt;/a&gt; living in &lt;a href=\"Verdistis\"&gt;Verdistis&lt;/a&gt; in 1218 AD.\nBackground.\nAs a wealthy nobleman, Sir Patrick provides loans to others with repayment terms. Aside from this, he has a dislike of &lt;a href=\"Sir%20Dante\"&gt;Sir Dante&lt;/a&gt; who he feels cursed him following a falling out at the auction house where Patrick won the bid. Since the falling out he feels that every terrible act in his life is due to Dante."}
