{"id": "10405", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=10405", "title": "Peace of Mind", "text": " is a &lt;a href=\"Pyrokinetic%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;starter Pyrokinetic&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Skills\"&gt;skill&lt;/a&gt; in \"\".\nDescription.\nSkill.\n is a supportive pyrokinetic skill that allows caster to boost either themselves or a single ally, thus granting them &lt;a href=\"Clear-Minded%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Clear-Minded&lt;/a&gt; status effect for 3 turns which grants bonuses to &lt;a href=\"Finesse\"&gt;Finesse&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Intelligence\"&gt;Intelligence&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Strength\"&gt;Strength&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Wits\"&gt;Wits&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Accuracy\"&gt;Accuracy&lt;/a&gt;. Since it grants &lt;a href=\"Clear-Minded%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Clear-Minded&lt;/a&gt; status effect it clears &lt;a href=\"Blinded%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Blinded&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Drunk%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Drunk&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Terrified%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Terrified&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Charmed%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Charmed&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Taunted%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Taunted&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Sleeping%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Sleeping&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Enraged%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Enraged&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Mad%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Mad&lt;/a&gt; status effects. Since this skill applies positive status effect it will always bypass armour.\nSince relies on &lt;a href=\"Pyrokinesis\"&gt;Pyrokinesis&lt;/a&gt; magic it cannot be cast if caster is affected by &lt;a href=\"Silenced%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Silenced&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Enraged%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Enraged&lt;/a&gt; status effects.\nSkillbook and Scroll.\n skillbook is a magical item that allows its reader to learn skill, if they have at least 1 point into &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Pyrokinetic\"&gt;Pyrokinetic&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Attributes%20and%20Abilities%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;ability&lt;/a&gt;, and use it indefinitely. In order to be able to cast the skill, character needs 1 free memory slot. Note that the book will disappear once read. The book weights 0.5 and its base value is 120 gold. A skillbook can be crafted if a scroll is combined with a &lt;a href=\"Blank%20Fire%20Skillbook\"&gt;Blank Fire Skillbook&lt;/a&gt;. Since is a starter Pyrokinetic skill, it is available right from the start of the game. Traders selling Pyrokinetic skillbooks will have this book for sale since the start of the game as well. \n scroll is a magical item that allows any character to cast skill, regardless of skill prerequisites, but only once. The only limiting element in casting this way is the amount of &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Action%20Points\"&gt;Action Points&lt;/a&gt; character has at their disposal in current turn. The scroll is craftable, weights 0.02 and has base value of 60 gold.\nThe cost of Action Points between scroll and skill themselves remains the same. Both the scroll and the skill itself are affected by other skills and talents that may provide additional bonuses.\nSkill Modifiers.\n is a supportive skill that provides bonuses to attributes. With the exception of Accuracy, the bonuses applied to the attributes largely depend on the casters level. Due to the nature of the bonuses, it is not possible to increase them, however they can stack with other items, skills or talents that provide them. Since the AP cost to cast this skill is always 1 AP it cannot be lowered by any means.\nThe only way to improve this skill is to increase its range through skills or talents.\nLocations.\nTraders.\nFollowing table shows all NPCs who are guaranteed to sell pyrokinetic spellbooks, with their location and coordinates in the right column, from them. The location shown in the table (and the coordinates) are only for the initial location the NPC is in. Note that some of these may have other spell/skillbooks and goods to sell. &lt;a href=\"Almira\"&gt;Almira&lt;/a&gt; may follow the Godwoken on &lt;a href=\"The%20Lady%20Vengeance\"&gt;Lady Vengeance&lt;/a&gt; if her demands are met."}
{"id": "15878", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=15878", "title": "Pear", "text": "Pear is a &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Consumables\"&gt;consumable item&lt;/a&gt; in ' and '.\nCharacteristics.\n is a consumable item that will heal 10 % of maximum Vitality and grant + 5 % Poison resistance when consumed. Characters with &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Talents\"&gt;Five-Star Diner talent&lt;/a&gt; are healed for 20 % maximum Vitality and are granted + 10 % Poison resistance. The effects of last 3 turns.\nPoisoned is a food that was poisoned through various means (either &lt;a href=\"Poison%20Bottle%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;poison bottle&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Zaikk%27s%20Talon\"&gt;Zaikk's Talon&lt;/a&gt;). Instead of healing it will deal poison damage equal to 10 % of the consumers maximum Vitality, rendering it unsafe for the living but safe for &lt;a href=\"Undead\"&gt;Undead&lt;/a&gt; and grant + 5 % Poison resistance. The effects last 3 turns.\nLocations.\nTraders.\nFollowing NPCs sell a large variety of food and thus have a solid chance (not guaranteed) of having in their stock. Note that as a consumable item may be very randomly sold by other NPCs."}
