{"id": "10952", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=10952", "title": "Physical Armour Potion", "text": "The Physical Armour Potion is a &lt;a href=\"Consumables%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;consumable item&lt;/a&gt; in \"\".\nCharacteristics.\nPhysical armour potion is a potion which increases Physical Armour by 29 points for 5 turns. If character has &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Talents\"&gt;Five-Star Diner talent&lt;/a&gt; the amount of Physical Armour increased will be 58 points instead of 29. Its weight is 0.25 and value is 15 gold.\nMedium physical armour potion is a potion which increases Physical Armour by 102 points for 5 turns. If character has Five-Star Diner talent the amount of Physical Armour increased will be 204 points instead of 102. Its weight is 0.25 and value is 55 gold.\nLarge physical armour potion is a potion which increases Physical Armour by 244 points for 5 turns. If character has Five-Star Diner talent the amount of Physical Armour increased will be 488 points instead of 244. Its weight is 0.25 and value is 95 gold.\nGiant physical armour potion is a potion which increases Physical Armour by 475 points for 5 turns. If character has Five-Star Diner talent the amount of Physical Armour increased will be 950 points instead of 475. Its weight is 0.25 and value is 170 gold.\nLocations.\nTraders.\nFollowing NPCs sell a large variety of potions and thus have a solid chance (not guaranteed) of having in their stock. Note that as a consumable item may be very randomly sold by other NPCs."}
{"id": "10885", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=10885", "title": "Physical and Magical Armor (Original Sin 2)", "text": "Physical and Magical armor is a new mechanic introduced in Divinity: Original Sin 2 to add more depth to combat by introducing a new obstacle to plan around, where as in DoS1 it was easier to bombard the enemy with damage without a second thought. In DoS2 you will have to scout out your enemies, if you know they are there, and discover their Armor and plan accordingly. \nHow it works.\nPhysical and Magical armor both serve the purposes of reducing damage and stopping disabling attacks, however as the names suggest they only affect an attack of the same type, Physical attacks will only be stopped by Physical Armor and the same goes for Magical Armor.\nDamage cannot be done to an enemy or yourself unless the armor bar is broken by the same type of damage or if an ability has a piercing affect that goes through armor.\nSource of armor.\nBoth Physical and Magical armor can come from a multitude of sources, the most common and influential on your stats would be armor itself. Other methods of raising your Armors include..\nWhat does it block.\nAs stated before Physical and Magical Armor both block specific types of damage and disabling effects, some effects may overlap. "}
