{"id": "13952", "revid": "53418829", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=13952", "title": "Pierce", "text": " is a &lt;a href=\"Verdistis\"&gt;Verdistis&lt;/a&gt; wine merchant in 1218AD.\nBackground.\nA renowned merchant of exotic elven wines, Pierce is the proprietor of &lt;a href=\"Pierce%27s%20Wine%20Barrel\"&gt;Pierce's Wine Barrel&lt;/a&gt;. Unbeknownst to him, his mind is being manipulated by the vampire &lt;a href=\"Tutamun\"&gt;Tutamun&lt;/a&gt; so the creature of the night can remain in his cellar undetected.\nDue to the operations of Tutamun from his cellar, Pierce has been marked as a suspect in the &lt;a href=\"A%20murderer%20in%20Verdistis\"&gt;murder of two young women&lt;/a&gt; in Verdistis. The merchant himself is happy to prove his innocence when confronted by &lt;a href=\"Lucian\"&gt;Lucian&lt;/a&gt; and gives the future Divine One free access to search his home and business."}
{"id": "13953", "revid": "46132361", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=13953", "title": "Pierce's Wine Barrel", "text": " is a store in &lt;a href=\"Verdistis\"&gt;Verdistis&lt;/a&gt;.\nBackground.\nPierce's Wine Barrel is an exotic wine merchants run by &lt;a href=\"Pierce\"&gt;Pierce&lt;/a&gt;, the store's namesake to the north of the easternmost point in &lt;a href=\"Verdistis\"&gt;Verdistis&lt;/a&gt;. In 1218 AD, the store became the focus of &lt;a href=\"Kratus\"&gt;Kratus&lt;/a&gt;' investigation into the &lt;a href=\"A%20murderer%20in%20Verdistis\"&gt;murder of two young women&lt;/a&gt;, following &lt;a href=\"Jacob\"&gt;Jacob&lt;/a&gt; seeing someone leaving the property at night.\nUnbeknownst to the owner at the time, a vampire, &lt;a href=\"Tutamun\"&gt;Tutamun&lt;/a&gt;, had taken residence in the cellar.\nLayout.\nThe store can be accessed from the eastern side, which leads into the sales floor of the shop. To the south of the sales floor is the archway leading into the passage separating home from business. To the southeast of the passage is the bedroom, which contains a bed, two tables, three chairs, a cupboard, bookcase and locked chest.\nTo the west of the passage is what appears to be a dining area, with a grand table and chairs set in the centre of the room; there is another door past this which leads to the cellar.\nThe cellar itself sits neatly under the building; after gaining access through the hatch into the cellar's atrium, a door on the eastern wall leads into the cellar proper. Behind several crates against the northern wall, a secret alcove can be found, containing Tutamun's coffin."}
