{"id": "17001", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=17001", "title": "Poison Arrow", "text": " is a type of &lt;a href=\"Munitions%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;ammunition&lt;/a&gt; in \"\"\nCharacteristics.\n is a special arrow which deals poison damage and inflicts &lt;a href=\"Poisoned%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Poisoned Status&lt;/a&gt; (3 turns) if the Magic Armour of affected characters reaches 0. Additionaly this arrow will create a poison surface at the area of impact (2 meter radius).\nCharacters need to wield &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Weapons\"&gt;bow or crossbow&lt;/a&gt; in order to use this arrow. The damage of the arrow depends on: base damage of the wielded weapon, &lt;a href=\"Finesse\"&gt;Finesse&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Geomancer%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Geomancer&lt;/a&gt; and height (bonus from height difference is affected by &lt;a href=\"Huntsman\"&gt;Huntsman&lt;/a&gt;).\nSince is a special arrow it is affected by &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Talents\"&gt;Arrow Recovery&lt;/a&gt; talent which grants 33 % chance to recover a special arrow after firing it. This arrow is also affected by &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Talents\"&gt;Elemental Ranger&lt;/a&gt; talent that grants additional elemental damage bonus depending on the surface the shooting character is standing in. It is possible to increase the range of the arrow by 2 meters through the &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Talents\"&gt;Far Out Man&lt;/a&gt; talent."}
{"id": "3585", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3585", "title": "Poison Arrows", "text": "Poison Arrows is a &lt;a href=\"Dragon%20Knight%20Saga%20Skills%23Ranger\"&gt;Ranger skill&lt;/a&gt; that can be used by &lt;a href=\"the%20Dragon%20Knight\"&gt;the Dragon Knight&lt;/a&gt; in \"\".\nDescription.\nPoison Arrows is a active Ranger skill that allows the Knight to shoot a poisoned arrow at their target, dealing continous amount of damage until the effect wears out. This skill requires equipped bow in order to be used, therefore using this skill with melee weapon in hand will cause the Knight to automatically switch to equipped bow."}
{"id": "10955", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=10955", "title": "Poison Bottle (Original Sin 2)", "text": "Poison Bottles are &lt;a href=\"Consumables%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29%23Potions\"&gt;consumable items&lt;/a&gt; in \"\".\nCharacteristics.\nWhen consumed it will cause Poison Damage and set the &lt;a href=\"Poisoned%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Poisoned&lt;/a&gt; status to all targets within its splash radius. Damage and Poisoned turns amount depend on the size of the bottle.\nIf consumed by &lt;a href=\"undead\"&gt;undead&lt;/a&gt; characters, it will heal rather than harm them.\nPoison bottles can also be combined with &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Weapons\"&gt;Weapons&lt;/a&gt; to permanently imbue them with poison damage, or with &lt;a href=\"Food%20and%20Drinks\"&gt;Food and Drinks&lt;/a&gt; to make them usable by undead characters.\nLocations.\nTraders.\nFollowing NPCs sell a large variety of potions and thus have a solid chance (not guaranteed) of having in their stock. Note that as a consumable item may be very randomly sold by other NPCs.\nUsage.\nFollowing table shows all items for which this item is used for."}
{"id": "17034", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=17034", "title": "Poison Cloud Grenade", "text": " is a type of &lt;a href=\"Munitions%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;ammunition&lt;/a&gt; in \"\".\nCharacteristics.\n is a throwable grenade that deals poison damage and inflicts &lt;a href=\"Poisoned%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Poisoned Status&lt;/a&gt; (2 turns) in 2 meter radius, if the Magic Armour of affected characters reaches 0. Additionaly this grenade creates a poison cloud at the area of impact.\nAll characters can throw this grenade. The damage of the grenade depends on &lt;a href=\"Geomancer%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Geomancer&lt;/a&gt; ability and can be further increased by &lt;a href=\"Huntsman\"&gt;Huntsman&lt;/a&gt; which boosts the damage bonus provided by height difference.\nSince is a grenade it is affected by &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Talents\"&gt;Ambidextrous&lt;/a&gt; talent which decreases the cost of using grenades and scrolls by 1 AP when the secondary hand is free. is also affected by &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Talents\"&gt;Slingshot&lt;/a&gt; which increases its range by 5 meters and by &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Talents\"&gt;Far Out Man&lt;/a&gt; talent which increases range by 2 meters.\nUsage.\nFollowing table shows all items for which this item is used for."}
{"id": "14853", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=14853", "title": "Poison Damage", "text": " is a &lt;a href=\"Divine%20Divinity%20skills%23Way%20of%20the%20warrior\"&gt;Warrior skill&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Divine%20Divinity\"&gt;Divine Divinity&lt;/a&gt;\".\nDescription.\nPoison Damage is a passive skill that grants a chance to apply poison damage with melee &lt;a href=\"Divine%20Divinity%20weapons\"&gt;weapons&lt;/a&gt;. Since this is a passive skill it is always active and does not require magic or stamina."}
{"id": "11377", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=11377", "title": "Poison Dart", "text": " is a &lt;a href=\"Geomancer%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;starter Geomancer&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Skills\"&gt;skill&lt;/a&gt; in \"\".\nDescription.\nSkill.\n is a offensive geomancer skill that allows caster to shoot a poisonous dart at a target area in 13 meter radius. The dart will deal poison damage to all characters in 1 meter impact radius and create a poison surface. \nCharacters without Magic Armour will be afflicted with &lt;a href=\"Poisoned%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Poisoned&lt;/a&gt; status effect for 3 turns and suffer damage directly to their health, with the exception of &lt;a href=\"Undead\"&gt;Undead&lt;/a&gt; who will receive &lt;a href=\"Poisoned%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Poisoned&lt;/a&gt; status effect regardless of their armour values and restore their health in proportion to the poison damage dealt by the status.\nSince relies on &lt;a href=\"Geomancy\"&gt;Geomancy&lt;/a&gt; magic it cannot be cast if caster is affected by &lt;a href=\"Silenced%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Silenced&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Enraged%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Enraged&lt;/a&gt; status effects. skill is reflected back when the target is under &lt;a href=\"Deflective%20Barrier\"&gt;Deflective Barrier&lt;/a&gt; skill (Definitive Edition only).\nScroll and Skillbook.\n skillbook is a magical item that allows its reader to learn skill, if they have at least 1 point into &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Geomancer\"&gt;Geomancer&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Attributes%20and%20Abilities%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;ability&lt;/a&gt;, and use it indefinitely. In order to be able to cast the skill, character needs 1 free memory slot. Note that the book will disappear once read. The book weights 0.5 and its base value is 120 gold. A skillbook can be crafted if a scroll is combined with a &lt;a href=\"Blank%20Earth%20Skillbook\"&gt;Blank Earth Skillbook&lt;/a&gt;. Since is a starter Geomancer skill, it is available right from the start of the game. Traders selling Geomancer skillbooks will have this book for sale since the start of the game as well. \n scroll is a magical item that allows any character to cast skill, regardless of skill prerequisites, but only once. The only limiting element in casting this way is the amount of &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Action%20Points\"&gt;Action Points (AP)&lt;/a&gt; character has at their disposal in current turn. The scroll is craftable, weights 0.02 and has base value of 70 gold.\nThe cost of Action Points between scroll and skill themselves remains the same. Both the scroll and the skill itself are affected by other skills and talents that may provide additional bonuses.\nSkill Modifiers.\nDamage of this skill is calculated with the following formula: (Base Damage) x (1 + Elemental Bonus%) x (1 + Attribute Bonus% + Weapon Skill Bonus %) x (1 + High Ground Bonus% + Crit Bonus%) x ( 1 + Misc Bonus %)\nThe damage of this skill is affected by the following attributes of the caster:\nOut of these the most effect on the damage have Level and then Geomancer ability as the latter increases damage by 5 % per point. Level provides greatest boost to the damage done. Intelligence provides the lowest bonus out of the three (3 points in Intelligence are equal to 1 point of Geomancer).\nWhen it comes to enemies they may resist poison damage if they have: Poison Immunity Status and high enough Poison Resistance (which lowers poison damage done). Additionally any character that is Undead or has the talent &lt;a href=\"Undead%20%28talent%29\"&gt;Undead&lt;/a&gt;, will automatically have + 200 % Poison Resistance which will cause them to heal from all poison damage done.\n properties can be affected by talents, consumable items (some of which may be affected by &lt;a href=\"Five-Star%20Diner%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Five-Star Diner&lt;/a&gt; talent) and other skills. \nLocations.\nTraders.\nFollowing table shows all NPCs who are guaranteed to sell Geomancer spellbooks, with their location and coordinates in the right column, from them. The location shown in the table (and the coordinates) are only for the initial location the NPC is in. Note that some of these may have other spell/skillbooks and goods to sell. Out of these only &lt;a href=\"Gareth%20Pryce\"&gt;Gareth&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Almira\"&gt;Almira&lt;/a&gt; may follow the &lt;a href=\"Godwoken\"&gt;Godwoken&lt;/a&gt; throughout the game on &lt;a href=\"the%20Lady%20Vengeance\"&gt;the Lady Vengeance&lt;/a&gt;, provided their demands are met."}
{"id": "17109", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=17109", "title": "Poison Dazzler Grenade", "text": " is a type of &lt;a href=\"Munitions%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;ammunition&lt;/a&gt; in \"\".\nCharacteristics.\n is a throwable grenade that deals no damage on its own but inflicts &lt;a href=\"Blinded%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Blinded Status&lt;/a&gt; (2 turns) in 4 meter radius, if the Magic Armour of affected characters reaches 0. Unlike simple &lt;a href=\"Razzle%20Dazzle%20Grenade\"&gt;Razzle Dazzle Grenade&lt;/a&gt; the also creates a poison surface at an area of impact in 2 meter radius.\nAll characters can throw this grenade. However due to the grenade dealing no damage and only inflicting status effect it is not possible to increase its effectiveness through abilities or attributes.\nSince is a grenade it is affected by &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Talents\"&gt;Ambidextrous&lt;/a&gt; talent which decreases the cost of using grenades and scrolls by 1 AP when the secondary hand is free. is also affected by &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Talents\"&gt;Slingshot&lt;/a&gt; which increases its range by 5 meters and by &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Talents\"&gt;Far Out Man&lt;/a&gt; talent which increases range by 2 meters."}
