{"id": "12446", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=12446", "title": "Poison Infusion", "text": "Poison Infusion is a &lt;a href=\"Geomancer%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Geomancer&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Summoning\"&gt;Summoning skill&lt;/a&gt; in \"\".\nDescription.\nSkill.\n is a supportive mixed skill that allows caster to change their summoned Incarnate's element to poison. By changing the element, the Incarnate gains multiple boons associated with it. Its basic close attack will deal poison damage. Due to the Incarnate being infused with poison it gains Poison Resistance + 100 % but it suffer from decreased resistances: Air Resistance - 20 %. Besides Poison resistance being increased the Incarnate becomes immune to &lt;a href=\"Poisoned%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Poisoned&lt;/a&gt; status effect. Alongside this the Incarnate learns the Geomancer skill &lt;a href=\"Poison%20Dart\"&gt;Poison Dart&lt;/a&gt;. Lastly it will receive + 5 points to Geomancer ability itself.\nNote that the effects of are achieved by summoning the Incarnate unto any poison surface.\nSince relies on &lt;a href=\"Geomancy\"&gt;Geomancy&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Summoning\"&gt;Summoning&lt;/a&gt; magic it cannot be cast if caster is affected by &lt;a href=\"Silenced%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Silenced&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Enraged%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Enraged&lt;/a&gt; status effects.\nScroll and Skillbook.\n skillbook is a magical item that allows its reader to learn skill, if they have at least 1 point into both &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Geomancer\"&gt;Geomancer&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Summoning\"&gt;Summoning&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Attributes%20and%20Abilities%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;abilities&lt;/a&gt;, and use it indefinitely. In order to be able to cast the skill, character needs 1 free memory slot. Note that the book will disappear once read. The book weights 0.5 and its base value is 190 gold. A skillbook can be crafted if a any non-source &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Geomancer\"&gt;Geomancer&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Summoning\"&gt;Summoning&lt;/a&gt; skillbooks are combined. Since is a mixed skill, traders do not have the skillbook for sale.\n is one of the few magic-based skills in the game that does not have a scroll.\nLocations.\nTraders.\nThis skill cannot be bought or stolen from NPCs in the game.\nGift Bag: Pet Power.\nGift Bag: Pet Power allows this skill to be used on any summoned creature. This gift bag also shortens the cooldown of this skill from 3 turns to 1 turn. Following table shows what skills will specific summoned entity gain from . Note that there are no changes to the skill and bonuses granted by the skill to the &lt;a href=\"Conjure%20Incarnate\"&gt;Incarnate&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "17144", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=17144", "title": "Poison Nailbomb", "text": " is a type of &lt;a href=\"Munitions%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;ammunition&lt;/a&gt; in \"\"\nCharacteristics.\n is a throwable grenade that deals physical damage and inflicts &lt;a href=\"Bleeding%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Bleeding Status&lt;/a&gt; (3 turns) in 4 meter radius, if the Physical Armour of affected characters reaches 0. Unlike simple &lt;a href=\"Nailbomb%20Grenade\"&gt;Nailbomb grenade&lt;/a&gt; the also creates a poison surface at an area of impact in 2 meter radius.\nAll characters can throw this grenade. The damage of the grenade depends on &lt;a href=\"Warfare%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Warfare&lt;/a&gt; ability and can be further increased by &lt;a href=\"Huntsman\"&gt;Huntsman&lt;/a&gt; which boosts the damage bonus provided by height difference.\nSince is a grenade it is affected by &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Talents\"&gt;Ambidextrous&lt;/a&gt; talent which decreases the cost of using grenades and scrolls by 1 AP when the secondary hand is free. is also affected by &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Talents\"&gt;Slingshot&lt;/a&gt; which increases its range by 5 meters and by &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Talents\"&gt;Far Out Man&lt;/a&gt; talent which increases range by 2 meters."}
{"id": "10956", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=10956", "title": "Poison Resistance Potion (Original Sin 2)", "text": "The is a type of &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Consumables%23Potions\"&gt;potion&lt;/a&gt; in \"\".\nCharacteristics.\nMedium is a consumable potion that grants 50 % Poison resistance for 3 turns. If character has Five-Star Diner talent, the potion will grant 100 % Poison resistance instead of 50 %. The potions weight is 0.25 and its value is 45 gold.\nLocations.\nTraders.\nFollowing NPCs sell a large variety of potions and thus have a solid chance (not guaranteed) of having in their stock. Note that as a consumable item may be very randomly sold by other NPCs."}
{"id": "12333", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=12333", "title": "Poison Wave", "text": "Poison wave is an &lt;a href=\"Geomancer%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;adept Geomancer&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Skills\"&gt;skill&lt;/a&gt; in \"\".\nDescription.\nSkill.\n is a offensive geomancer skill that allows caster to release a poisonous wave around themselves which will create poisonous clouds (which do not disappear) in 4 meter radius. This wave does poison damage to all hostile characters. The caster themselves will be fortified with an &lt;a href=\"Earth%20Immunity%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Earth Immunity&lt;/a&gt; status effect which increases their Earth and Poison resistances by 100 % and grants them immunity to &lt;a href=\"Poisoned%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Poisoned&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Petrified%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Petrified&lt;/a&gt; status effects for 1 turn.\nCharacters without Magic Armour will be afflicted with &lt;a href=\"Poisoned%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Poisoned&lt;/a&gt; status effect for 2 turns and suffer damage directly to their health, with the exception of allied &lt;a href=\"Undead\"&gt;Undead&lt;/a&gt; who will receive &lt;a href=\"Poisoned%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Poisoned&lt;/a&gt; status effect regardless of their armour values and restore their health in proportion to the poison damage dealt by the status. \nSince relies on &lt;a href=\"Geomancy\"&gt;Geomancy&lt;/a&gt; magic it cannot be cast if caster is affected by &lt;a href=\"Silenced%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Silenced&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Enraged%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Enraged&lt;/a&gt; status effects. skill is not reflected back when the target is under &lt;a href=\"Deflective%20Barrier\"&gt;Deflective Barrier&lt;/a&gt; skill (Definitive Edition only).\nScroll and Skillbook.\n skillbook is a magical item that allows its reader to learn skill, if they have at least 2 points into &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Geomancer\"&gt;Geomancer&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Attributes%20and%20Abilities%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;ability&lt;/a&gt;, and use it indefinitely. In order to be able to cast the skill, character needs 1 free memory slot. Note that the book will disappear once read. The book weights 0.5 and its base value is 500 gold. A skillbook can be crafted if a scroll is combined with a &lt;a href=\"Blank%20Earth%20Skillbook\"&gt;Blank Earth Skillbook&lt;/a&gt;. Since is an adept Geomancer skill, traders will start selling the skillbook once player character or their &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Companions\"&gt;companions&lt;/a&gt; reach level 9. \n scroll is a magical item that allows any character to cast skill, regardless of skill prerequisites, but only once. The only limiting element in casting this way is the amount of &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Action%20Points\"&gt;Action Points (AP)&lt;/a&gt; character has at their disposal in current turn. The scroll is craftable, weights 0.02 and has base value of 260 gold.\nThe cost of Action Points between scroll and skill themselves remains the same. Both the scroll and the skill itself are affected by other skills and talents that may provide additional bonuses.\nSkill Modifiers.\nDamage of this skill is calculated with the following formula: (Base Damage) x (1 + Elemental Bonus%) x (1 + Attribute Bonus% + Weapon Skill Bonus %) x (1 + High Ground Bonus% + Crit Bonus%) x ( 1 + Misc Bonus %)\nThe damage of this skill is affected by the following attributes of the caster:\nOut of these the most effect on the damage have Level and then Geomancer ability as the latter increases damage by 5 % per point. Level provides greatest boost to the damage done. Intelligence provides the lowest bonus out of the three (3 points in Intelligence are equal to 1 point of Geomancer).\nWhen it comes to enemies they may resist poison damage if they have: Poison Immunity Status and high enough Poison Resistance (which lowers poison damage done). Additionally any character that is Undead or has the talent &lt;a href=\"Undead%20%28talent%29\"&gt;Undead&lt;/a&gt;, will automatically have + 200 % Poison Resistance which will cause them to heal from all poison damage done.\n properties can be affected by talents, consumable items (some of which may be affected by &lt;a href=\"Five-Star%20Diner%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Five-Star Diner&lt;/a&gt; talent) and other skills. \nLocations.\nTraders.\nFollowing table shows all NPCs who are guaranteed to sell Geomancer spellbooks, with their location and coordinates in the right column, from them. The location shown in the table (and the coordinates) are only for the initial location the NPC is in. Note that some of these may have other spell/skillbooks and goods to sell. Out of these only &lt;a href=\"Gareth%20Pryce\"&gt;Gareth&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Almira\"&gt;Almira&lt;/a&gt; may follow the &lt;a href=\"Godwoken\"&gt;Godwoken&lt;/a&gt; throughout the game on &lt;a href=\"the%20Lady%20Vengeance\"&gt;the Lady Vengeance&lt;/a&gt;, provided their demands are met."}
{"id": "14188", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=14188", "title": "Poison Weapon", "text": "Poison Weapon is a\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Divine%20Divinity%20skills%23Way%20of%20the%20survivor\"&gt;Survivor skill&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0in &lt;a href=\"Divine%20Divinity\"&gt;Divine Divinity&lt;/a&gt;.\nDescription.\nThis skill lets you to apply poison to a weapon. The Strength of this skill depends on the strength of the used poison. The poison has no effect on &lt;a href=\"undead\"&gt;undead&lt;/a&gt;."}
