{"id": "20216", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=20216", "title": "Poisoned (Status)", "text": "Poisoned is a &lt;a href=\"Status%20Effects%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;status effect&lt;/a&gt; in \"\".\nDescription.\nPoisoned is a negative environmental status effect that inflicts poison damage upon the afflicted character, damaging their Magic armour first and Vitality afterwards. Unlike most status effects this one has beneficial effect upon the &lt;a href=\"Undead\"&gt;Undead&lt;/a&gt;; instead of harm the amount of \"poison damage\" normally dealt will restore their Vitality. \nCause.\nThere are many ways through which burning status effect can be triggered. On &lt;a href=\"Rivellon\"&gt;Rivellon&lt;/a&gt; poisoned can be afflicted by being in contact with \"poison surface\" and/or \"poison cloud\". In combat one may use items and spells to inflict Poisoned upon their foes, however one unassuming way of poisoning characters is by disguising &lt;a href=\"Poison%20Bottle%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Poison Bottle&lt;/a&gt; with &lt;a href=\"Red%20Fabric%20Dye\"&gt;Red Fabric Dye&lt;/a&gt; into &lt;a href=\"Healing%20Potion%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Healing Potion&lt;/a&gt;.\nTreatment.\nPoisoned status effect can be treated by either negating the status effect or endured by keeping Magic armour above 0. \nStatus removal.\n is a status that can be removed mostly only through spells/skills or scrolls. Out of items only &lt;a href=\"Stoneskin%20Potion\"&gt;Stoneskin Potion&lt;/a&gt; can remove this status effect by providing immunity against it."}
