{"id": "14374", "revid": "53418829", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=14374", "title": "Sourcerer", "text": "Sourcerers are individuals with the innate ability to wield &lt;a href=\"Source\"&gt;Source&lt;/a&gt; energy. Predominantly they have been considered a danger by society, however there have been exceptions throughout the ages, including &lt;a href=\"Lucian\"&gt;Lucian&lt;/a&gt;, whose abilities came about from his ascension to Divinity.\nDue to the nature of the Source, Sourcerers were capable of feats beyond the reaches of other magic users, such as resurrection, the summoning and creation of creatures and breaking unbreakable curses. In addition, they were capable of seeing spirits and feeding on the Source of mortal beings.\u00a0The most powerful of the Sourcerers were called masters of the Source.\nBackground.\nAlthough Source itself is a part of all individuals, the history of Sourcerers can be traced back to Anno Rivellonis (AR) and the rule of &lt;a href=\"Braccus%20Rex\"&gt;Braccus Rex&lt;/a&gt;, also known as the Sourcerer King, who used his own power to assert his position over the wider society until his removal from power by the &lt;a href=\"Order%20of%20the%20Source%20Hunters\"&gt;Order of the Source Hunters&lt;/a&gt;. The order would continue to hunt Sourcerers until the closing years of AR, after which their operations and the use of Source magic fell into a state of obscurity. Until the Age of the Damned there was a distinct lack of Sourcery, until in c. 600 Annos Deorum (AD) a distant traveller know as &lt;a href=\"Ruganol\"&gt;Ruganol&lt;/a&gt; taught the healers of &lt;a href=\"Dylan%20Ferol\"&gt;Dylan Ferol&lt;/a&gt; how to wield this power again.\nBy 1238 AD, the number of Source users had grown exponentially, many of which never received any training or actively sought to use it."}
{"id": "16351", "revid": "49426621", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=16351", "title": "Sourcerer Records", "text": " is a &lt;a href=\"Books%20and%20notes%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;book&lt;/a&gt; in \"\".\nLocation.\nReading this book will make party members discuss about the fate of their fellow prisoners still at Fort Joy."}
{"id": "13008", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=13008", "title": "Sourcery (Original Sin 2)", "text": "Source skills are a set of skills and spells that rely either exclusively or partially on &lt;a href=\"Source\"&gt;Source&lt;/a&gt; in \"\". If &lt;a href=\"Sourcerer\"&gt;Sourcerer&lt;/a&gt; is wearing an active &lt;a href=\"Source%20Collar\"&gt;Source Collar&lt;/a&gt; they will be unable to perform these spells and skills due to their reliance on Source.\nCombat Source Skills.\nFollowing skills and spells are mix of source and &lt;a href=\"Attributes%20and%20Abilities%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;combat ability&lt;/a&gt;, because they require not only enough Source points but also sufficient combat ability level. Some of these may be acquired through items and therefore bypass the combat ability level requirement.\nCraftable Source skills.\nFollowing Source skills are crafted by combining a combat skill book with source elemental spell book and vice versa. Requirements of these skills and spells are derived from the books used in crafting.\nPet Power gift bag.\nFollowing spells can only be crafted if Gift Bag: Pet Power has been activated. Like other infusions they also require Summoning and other corresponding combat ability level. In this case it is either &lt;a href=\"Geomancer%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Geomancer&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Necromancer%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Necromancer&lt;/a&gt; level. Note that following skills gained by casting the spell are applied on &lt;a href=\"Conjure%20Incarnate\"&gt;Incarnate&lt;/a&gt;. If infusions are applied on different summoned creature, then the secondary gained skill may be different.\nPure Source Skills.\n&lt;a href=\"Companions%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Origin&lt;/a&gt; skills.\nFollowing skills are Source skills that are innate to &lt;a href=\"Godwoken\"&gt;Godwoken&lt;/a&gt; and are therefore automatically learnt (they require no memory in order to be usable). \nGodwoken skills.\nGodwoken source skills are skills that rely purely on Source and are acquired through their interaction with &lt;a href=\"the%20Seven%20Gods\"&gt;the Seven Gods&lt;/a&gt; or in case of &lt;a href=\"Curse%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Curse&lt;/a&gt; with the &lt;a href=\"Voidwoken\"&gt;Voidwoken&lt;/a&gt;. Out of all of these only \"Curse\" spell can be crafted as scroll. Alternatively &lt;a href=\"Spirit%20Vision\"&gt;Spirit Vision&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Source%20Vampirism\"&gt;Source Vampirism&lt;/a&gt; can be learnt by reading and in &lt;a href=\"the%20Academy%20of%20the%20Seven\"&gt;the Academy of the Seven&lt;/a&gt;.\nDivine skills.\nFollowing set of skills are skills that originate from &lt;a href=\"Divine%20Divinity\"&gt;Divine Divinity&lt;/a&gt; and are used exlusively by &lt;a href=\"Lucian\"&gt;Lucian&lt;/a&gt;. The other two Divine skills that made into the game are &lt;a href=\"Translocate%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Translocate&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Scorch%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Scorch&lt;/a&gt; however neither of these is classified as \"Sourcery\" and only \"Scorch\" can be accessed via Game Master Mode."}
