{"id": "20166", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=20166", "title": "Special Skills (Original Sin 2)", "text": "Special skills are &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Skills\"&gt;skills&lt;/a&gt; that belong into the special category in \"\".\nDescription.\nSpecial skills are skills that have special criteria which needs to be met in order to be used. One such criteria is weapon skills needing their corresponding weapon(s) equipped in order to be learnt and consequently used. Some skills are exclusive to summoned creatures such as the &lt;a href=\"Swap%20Places\"&gt;Swap Places&lt;/a&gt; spell of the &lt;a href=\"Black%20Cat\"&gt;Black Cat&lt;/a&gt;. \nCategories.\nRacial skills.\nRacial skills are skills that are innate to every playable race and are always accompanied by corresponding talents. \nWeapon skills.\nThe following skills are automatically obtained whenever character wields a specific type of weapon."}
{"id": "3818", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3818", "title": "Spectre at the Feast", "text": "Spectre at the Feast is a &lt;a href=\"Flames%20of%20Vengeance%20quests\"&gt;side quest&lt;/a&gt; received from the &lt;a href=\"ghost\"&gt;ghost&lt;/a&gt; of &lt;a href=\"Caracalla\"&gt;Caracalla&lt;/a&gt;, the fallen &lt;a href=\"champions\"&gt;Champion&lt;/a&gt; of &lt;a href=\"Aleroth\"&gt;Aleroth&lt;/a&gt;, who you meet at the foot of the stairs (south of the statue) in the &lt;a href=\"Great%20Market\"&gt;Great Market&lt;/a&gt; district during the events of \"\". \nDetailed Walkthrough.\nAs you approach Caracalla, a guard warns you to stay away as the ghost rages on about getting revenge. When you speak with him, Caracalla asks you to help him defeat his killers and says he will meet you at the &lt;a href=\"Crowell%27s%20House\"&gt;scene of the crime&lt;/a&gt;.\nBefore you head to the house, which is located in &lt;a href=\"Crow%27s%20Nest\"&gt;Crow's Nest&lt;/a&gt;, loot Caracalla's burning corpse to pick up his key.\nOnce you gain access to Crow's Nest (by completing &lt;a href=\"Bark%20up%20the%20Right%20Tree\"&gt;Bark up the Right Tree&lt;/a&gt;), head to &lt;a href=\"Crowell%27s%20House\"&gt;Crowell's House&lt;/a&gt; near the center of the district. You'll find Caracalla inside near the entrance. He talks to you, then follow you as you move around the house. Light the two candles by the door on the right. This reveals a hidden button on column to the left of the X written in blood on the east wall. Pressing the button reveals a hidden room. Pull the lever inside the room, then head back to the door where you lit the candles. Take the &lt;a href=\"Dead%20Champion%20Note\"&gt;Dead Champion Note&lt;/a&gt; (), and loot the Dining Room Key from the corpse. You can read the note for a hint.\nProceed north to the Dining Room. Take the &lt;a href=\"Fallen%20Warrior%20Note\"&gt;Fallen Warrior Note&lt;/a&gt; (quest item) next to Geta's corpse and read it for another hint. Light the two candles near the door to the west (this reveals a button in the room which you'll use later), then walk north along the hallway. Light the candles on both sides of the hall by the painting of the woman and the two at the end of the hall to remove the wall ahead.\nGo into the newly revealed area and head east. An autosave occurs before you enter the room and encounter the Invisible Terror, which talks briefly before sealing the doorway with a magical barrier to prevent your escape. You are attacked by several (invisible) level 38 Fleeting Wraith enemies. Listen to Caracalla for clues on what to do, which should be obvious if you've read the notes: Light the candles in the four corners of the room to reveal the &lt;a href=\"ghost\"&gt;ghost&lt;/a&gt;s attacking you. You can only see and attack the enemies while all the candles are lit, and they extinguish fairly quickly. Caracalla will tell you when a candle goes out. You'll likely need to relight the candles a few times before eliminating all the enemies.\nWhen all the ghosts are killed, the quest is complete. Caracalla offers his thanks and moves on to the &lt;a href=\"Hall%20of%20Echoes\"&gt;Hall of Echoes&lt;/a&gt;. You receive the rewards, and the teleporters in the house activate. Take the teleporter to Caracalla's chest, then press the nearby button to open the door."}
{"id": "14827", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=14827", "title": "Spellshield", "text": " is a &lt;a href=\"Divine%20Divinity%20skills%23Way%20of%20the%20mage\"&gt;Mage skill&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Divine%20Divinity\"&gt;Divine Divinity&lt;/a&gt;\".\nDescription.\nCreates a magic and poison damage absorbing shield around &lt;a href=\"Lucian\"&gt;Lucian&lt;/a&gt; which can be used simultaneously with the &lt;a href=\"Aura%20of%20Guarding\"&gt;Aura of Guarding&lt;/a&gt;. In addition to the visible ward, its strength is shown in the top-left corner of the screen. It doesn't affect base resistances and will dissipate after resting."}
{"id": "14262", "revid": "49426621", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=14262", "title": "Spider", "text": "Spiders are a collection of arachnids that can be seen throughout &lt;a href=\"Rivellon\"&gt;Rivellon&lt;/a&gt;.\nVariants.\nSpider.\nSpiders are ankle high arachnids commonly found throughout Rivellon.\nGiant Spider.\nA much larger and hairier arachnid. Its primary form of attack is to spit acid at its target.\nMutated Spider.\nIts appearance resembles that of a Giant Spider. They attack by shooting homing spheres, which are physical damage based.\nSewer Spider.\nFound in &lt;a href=\"Verdistis%20Sewers\"&gt;Verdistis Sewers&lt;/a&gt;. Poisonous melee attack.\nGiant Sewer Spider.\nFound in &lt;a href=\"Verdistis%20Sewers\"&gt;Verdistis Sewers&lt;/a&gt;. Spews acid.\nMutated Sewer Spider.\nFound in &lt;a href=\"Verdistis%20Sewers\"&gt;Verdistis Sewers&lt;/a&gt;. Shoots homing physical energy balls.\nForest Spider.\nFound in &lt;a href=\"Teneb%20Tiriel\"&gt;Teneb Tiriel&lt;/a&gt;.\nGiant Forest Spider.\nA large spider found in &lt;a href=\"Teneb%20Tiriel\"&gt;Teneb Tiriel&lt;/a&gt;.\nMutated Forest Spider.\nIts appearance resembles that of a Giant Spider. They attack by shooting homing spheres, which are physical damage based. Variant found in &lt;a href=\"Teneb%20Tiriel\"&gt;Teneb Tiriel&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "12385", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=12385", "title": "Spider Legs", "text": "Spider Legs is an &lt;a href=\"Polymorph%20%28Skill%20Class%29\"&gt;adept Polymorph&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Skills\"&gt;skill&lt;/a&gt; in \"\".\nDescription.\nSkill.\nSpider legs burst from your back. You can create web surfaces in an area to Entangle foes. Incompatible with &lt;a href=\"Spread%20Your%20Wings\"&gt;Spread Your Wings&lt;/a&gt;.\nSince relies on &lt;a href=\"Metamorphosis\"&gt;Metamorphosis&lt;/a&gt; magic it cannot be cast if caster is affected by &lt;a href=\"Silenced%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Silenced&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Enraged%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Enraged&lt;/a&gt; status effects. \nScroll and Skillbook.\n skillbook is a magical item that allows its reader to learn skill, if they have at least 2 points into &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Polymorph\"&gt;Polymorph&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Attributes%20and%20Abilities%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;ability&lt;/a&gt;, and use it indefinitely. In order to be able to cast the skill, character needs 1 free memory slot. Note that the book will disappear once read. The book weights 0.5 and its base value is 500 gold. A skillbook can be crafted if a scroll is combined with a &lt;a href=\"Blank%20Polymorph%20Skillbook\"&gt;Blank Polymorph Skillbook&lt;/a&gt;. Since is an adept Polymorph skill, traders will start selling the skillbook once &lt;a href=\"Godwoken\"&gt;Godwoken&lt;/a&gt; reach level 9.\n scroll is a magical item that allows any character to cast skill, regardless of skill prerequisites, but only once. The only limiting element in casting this way is the amount of &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Action%20Points\"&gt;Action Points (AP)&lt;/a&gt; character has at their disposal in current turn. The scroll is craftable, weights 0.02 and has base value of 260 gold.\nThe cost of Action Points between scroll and skill themselves remains the same. Both the scroll and the skill itself are affected by other skills, attributes and talents that may provide additional bonuses.\nLocations.\nTraders.\nFollowing table shows all NPCs who are guaranteed to sell Polymorph spellbooks, with their location and coordinates in the right column, from them. The location shown in the table (and the coordinates) are only for the initial location the NPC is in. Note that some of these may have other spell/skillbooks and goods to sell. "}
