{"id": "3593", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3593", "title": "Splitting Arrows", "text": "Splitting Arrows is a &lt;a href=\"Dragon%20Knight%20Saga%20Skills%23Ranger\"&gt;Ranger skill&lt;/a&gt; that can be used by &lt;a href=\"the%20Dragon%20Knight\"&gt;the Dragon Knight&lt;/a&gt; in \"\".\nDescription.\nSplitting Arrows is a active Ranger skill that allows the Knight to shoot multiple arrows at once. This skill requires equipped bow in order to be used, therefore using this skill with melee weapon in hand will cause the Knight to automatically switch to equipped bow.\nNotes.\nIt may not be readily apparent early-on, with Splitting Arrow firing so few shots at once at smaller groups of smaller enemies, but Splitting Arrows has a \"shotgun\" effect.\u00a0 Rather than a few arrows picking and chasing certain targets while the rest go off randomly and uselessly, the main target is chosen and all the extra arrows fly outward nearly randomly... yet any arrow that hits an enemy works as a single shot would have.\u00a0 Rather than \"allowing the bowman to hit multiple targets at the same time\", it should really say \"fires multiple arrows, all doing full damage to whatever they strike, even if the same enemy is hit by every arrow fired.\"\u00a0 With the way gear scales in the expansion (and enemy health and defenses, especially on Nightmare Mode), &lt;a href=\"Explosive%20Arrows\"&gt;Explosive Arrows&lt;/a&gt;' damage is quickly overtaken by even normal shots, and Splitting Arrows stacks just fine with &lt;a href=\"Way%20of%20the%20Ranger\"&gt;Way of the Ranger&lt;/a&gt;, while Explosive Arrows does not.\nOnce your Way of the Ranger increases your damage by nearly 600% (on an expansion-level Unique bow already hitting for 800+) and your ranger's crit rate is in the 75-80% range, it doesn't take a genius to do the math.\u00a0 Eventually the choice comes down to Explosive being guaranteed to hit a lot of enemies from really far away for a little damage (or what is a \"little\" in the expansion), or getting right up against a group of enemies and hitting 2-3 of them for 4-5,000 damage 4-5 times each.\u00a0\nExplosive is great up until the end of the Flying Fortresses and you won't even want more power because because it's totally unnecessary, but its faults start to show with scaling issues later and Splitting is probably the better choice."}
{"id": "15205", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=15205", "title": "Splitting Arrows (Divine Divinity)", "text": " is a &lt;a href=\"Divine%20Divinity%20skills%23Way%20of%20the%20warrior\"&gt;Warrior skill&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Divine%20Divinity\"&gt;Divine Divinity&lt;/a&gt;\".\nDescription.\nThis skill causes arrows to magically split into several more arrows that can hit multiple enemies. "}
{"id": "12126", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=12126", "title": "Spontaneous Combustion", "text": "Spontaneous Combustion is a &lt;a href=\"Pyrokinetic%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;novice pyrokinetic skill&lt;/a&gt; in \"\".\nDescription.\nSkill.\n is a offensive pyrokinetic skill that allows character to hurl a fiery curse at their target which deals fire damage. The curse will cause the target, and anyone in 3 meter radius, to take additional fire damage by converting any &lt;a href=\"Burning%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Burning&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Necrofire%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Necrofire&lt;/a&gt; status effects, with the latter status granting greater damage bonus. The size of the additional damage depends on how many turns have the status effects left. \nFor example if the skill itself does 8 - 10 fire damage and target has &lt;a href=\"Burning%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Burning&lt;/a&gt; for 3 turns the target will take 11 points of fire damage + 4 points of fire damage caused by explosion. However if target is afflicted with &lt;a href=\"Necrofire%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Necrofire&lt;/a&gt; status effect for 3 turns the will cause 9 points of fire damage + 10 points of fire damage caused by explosion.\nSince relies on &lt;a href=\"Pyrokinesis\"&gt;Pyrokinesis&lt;/a&gt; magic it cannot be cast if caster is affected by &lt;a href=\"Silenced%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Silenced&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Enraged%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Enraged&lt;/a&gt; status effects. skill is NOT reflected back when the target is under &lt;a href=\"Deflective%20Barrier\"&gt;Deflective Barrier&lt;/a&gt; skill (Definitive Edition only).\nScroll and Skillbook.\n skillbook is a magical item that allows its reader to learn skill, if they have at least 2 points into &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Pyrokinetic\"&gt;Pyrokinetic&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Attributes%20and%20Abilities%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;ability&lt;/a&gt;, and use it indefinitely. In order to be able to cast the skill, character needs 1 free memory slot. Note that the book will disappear once read. The book weights 0.5 and its base value is 190 gold. Since is a novice Pyrokinetic skill, traders will start selling the skillbook once &lt;a href=\"Godwoken\"&gt;Godwoken&lt;/a&gt; reach level 4.\n is one of the few magic-based skills in the game that does not have a scroll. \nSkill Modifiers.\nDamage of this skill is calculated with the following formula: (Base Damage) x (1 + Elemental Bonus%) x (1 + Attribute Bonus% + Weapon Skill Bonus %) x (1 + High Ground Bonus% + Crit Bonus%) x ( 1 + Misc Bonus %)\nThe damage of this skill is affected by the following attributes of the caster:\nOut of these the most effect on the damage have level and then Pyrokinetic ability as the latter increases damage by 5 % per point. Level provides greatest boost to the damage done. Intelligence provides the lowest bonus out of the three (3 points in Intelligence are equal to 1 point of Pyrokinetic).\nWhen it comes to enemies they may resist fire damage if they have: Fire Immunity Status and high enough Fire Resistance (which lowers fire damage done).\n properties can be affected by talents, consumable items (some of which may be affected by &lt;a href=\"Five-Star%20Diner%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Five-Star Diner&lt;/a&gt; talent) and other skills. \nLocations.\nTraders.\nFollowing table shows all NPCs who are guaranteed to sell pyrokinetic spellbooks, with their location and coordinates in the right column, from them. The location shown in the table (and the coordinates) are only for the initial location the NPC is in. Note that some of these may have other spell/skillbooks and goods to sell. &lt;a href=\"Almira\"&gt;Almira&lt;/a&gt; may follow the Godwoken on &lt;a href=\"The%20Lady%20Vengeance\"&gt;Lady Vengeance&lt;/a&gt; if her demands are met."}
{"id": "11503", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=11503", "title": "Spread Your Wings", "text": "Spread Your Wings is a &lt;a href=\"Polymorph%20%28Skill%20Class%29\"&gt;novice Polymorph&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Skills\"&gt;skill&lt;/a&gt; in \"\".\nDescription.\nSkill.\nUsing \"Spread Your Wings\" will give the character wings which let him hover and ignore the effects of ground based surfaces (not cloud based such as Deathfog) for 3 turns, it also grants them the skill &lt;a href=\"Flight\"&gt;Flight&lt;/a&gt; which allows you to leap large distances (great for positioning during a fight or before one). You can also reach ledges that would normally require you to use &lt;a href=\"Teleportation%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Teleport&lt;/a&gt; for.\nScroll and Skillbook.\n skillbook is a magical item that allows its reader to learn skill, if they have at least 2 points into &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Polymorph\"&gt;Polymorph&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Attributes%20and%20Abilities%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;ability&lt;/a&gt;, and use it indefinitely. In order to be able to cast the skill, character needs 1 free memory slot. Note that the book will disappear once read. The book weights 0.5 and its base value is 190 gold. A skillbook can be crafted if a scroll is combined with a &lt;a href=\"Blank%20Polymorph%20Skillbook\"&gt;Blank Polymorph Skillbook&lt;/a&gt;. Since is a novice Polymorph skill, traders will start selling the skillbook once &lt;a href=\"Godwoken\"&gt;Godwoken&lt;/a&gt; reach level 4.\n scroll is a magical item that allows any character to cast skill, regardless of skill prerequisites, but only once. The only limiting element in casting this way is the amount of &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Action%20Points\"&gt;Action Points (AP)&lt;/a&gt; character has at their disposal in current turn. The scroll is craftable, weights 0.02 and has base value of 120 gold.\nThe cost of Action Points between scroll and skill themselves remains the same. Both the scroll and the skill itself are affected by other skills, attributes and talents that may provide additional bonuses.\nLocations.\nTraders.\nFollowing table shows all NPCs who are guaranteed to sell Polymorph spellbooks, with their location and coordinates in the right column, from them. The location shown in the table (and the coordinates) are only for the initial location the NPC is in. Note that some of these may have other spell/skillbooks and goods to sell. "}
