{"id": "6466", "revid": "49426621", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=6466", "title": "Star Stone", "text": "Star stones, also known as blood stones or inert stones are in \"\"\nBackground.\nStar stones are threads torn from the &lt;a href=\"Tapestry%20of%20Time\"&gt;Tapestry of Time&lt;/a&gt; by the &lt;a href=\"Guardians\"&gt;Guardians&lt;/a&gt;, in an attempt to undo the lapse in their duty which resulted in the freeing of the &lt;a href=\"Void%20Dragon\"&gt;Void Dragon&lt;/a&gt; and the corruption of &lt;a href=\"Source\"&gt;Source&lt;/a&gt;. These threads rained down on &lt;a href=\"Rivellon\"&gt;Rivellon&lt;/a&gt;, becoming stones filled with great &lt;a href=\"Source\"&gt;Source&lt;/a&gt; power. It was discovered that through sacrifice, a Star Stone could be converted into a Blood Stone, an artifact that could be used for both healing or harm.\nCharacteristics.\nWhen &lt;a href=\"the%20Source%20Hunters\"&gt;the Source Hunters&lt;/a&gt; come into contact with a star stone (which appears as a blue gem), the stone's energy is completely drained as the duo reabsorb parts of their identity as Guardians. This will allow the &lt;a href=\"Weaver%20of%20Time\"&gt;Weaver of Time&lt;/a&gt; to partially repair the Tapestry, and reactivate portals at the &lt;a href=\"End%20of%20Time\"&gt;End of Time&lt;/a&gt;. When the Source Hunters find a blood stone, they are able to carry it in this stable state until they wish to use its healing powers. Once used, the blood stone will revert to an inert star stone.\nNormally once a blood stone has been used, the star stone can be converted back into one through sacrifice. However the star stones that the Source Hunters come into contact with are irreversibly drained by their proximity, becoming inert stones. It is not possible to recharge an inert stone to turn it back into a star stone, nor turn it into a blood stone."}
