{"id": "5592", "revid": "2056997", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5592", "title": "Status Effects", "text": ""}
{"id": "9897", "revid": "96155", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=9897", "title": "Status Effects (DOS EE)", "text": "Status effects are effects on a PC or NPC that provide buffs, damage, and or control, playing a major role both in and out of combat. For players, conditions are primarily inflicted through use of skills and traits, but also include scrolls and potions. \nAll statuses have duration stacking but not intensity stacking. PCs and NPCs have variable resistances to different types of status effects ranging from none to full immunity. "}
{"id": "20116", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=20116", "title": "Status Effects (Original Sin 2)", "text": "Status Effects are various reactions of characters influenced by environmental, skill or special effects which last certain amount of time in \"\".\nEnvironmental status effects.\nEnvironmental status effects are applied whenever character steps upon specific \"surface\" or \"cloud\". These effects are applied immediatelly upon making contact. They can be bypassed or negated with certain skills, opposing elemental influence or certain characteristics of affected character such as \"immunity\". When character is outside of said surface, the effect will wear of under normal circumstances \"around 2 turns\". \nElemental status effects are under normal circumstances automatically \"resisted\" by having corresponding armour values above 0. Note that if character has &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Talents\"&gt;Glass Canon talent&lt;/a&gt; then these statuses will apply even if character has both Magic and Physical armour above 0. Status effects will also be applied if character ends up in \"specific location or around specific character\", regardless of armour values. \nSkill status effects.\nSkill status effects are caused whenever character is a affected by specific skill, which may be both positive, negative or a bit of both. The duration of effects depends on the skill and whether caster has &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Talents\"&gt;Torturer talent&lt;/a&gt;.\nPositive.\nSkills that are Status Effects.\nFollowing table shows skills whose icons are exclusive to one kind of skill and use the skills icon for it.\nInfusions.\nFollowing status effects can be applied upon a &lt;a href=\"Conjure%20Incarnate\"&gt;Conjured Incarnate&lt;/a&gt;, granting them various bonuses and weaknesses. Only one elemental status infusion can be active at a time. Power infusions can be applied simultaneously and will not cancel each other out. If \"Gift Bag: Pet Power\" is activated then infusions can be applied to all summoned creatures. \nArrowhead.\nArrowhead infusions are exclusive to &lt;a href=\"Huntsman\"&gt;Huntsman&lt;/a&gt; skill &lt;a href=\"Elemental%20Arrowheads\"&gt;Elemental Arrowheads&lt;/a&gt; and allows character to deal additional elemental damage with their bows and crossbows, depending on the surface it was used on. \nSpecial status effects.\nThese status effects do not belong into any category and are earned by unique specific actions in the game. This category also includes NPC exclusive status effects."}
{"id": "11389", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=11389", "title": "Steam Lance", "text": " is an &lt;a href=\"Hydrosophist%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;expert Hydrosophist&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Sourcery%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;source&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Skills\"&gt;skill&lt;/a&gt; in \"\".\nDescription.\nSkill.\n is a supportive hydrosophist source skill that allows character to release a wave of blessed steam clouds up to 13 meter range. This blessed steam will set Steam Lance status effect unto all allied characters, restoring Vitality each turn up to 3 turns. Enemy characters caught in the blast will not be affected by this status, however like allied characters they will have their negative status effects removed.\nThe negative status effects removed by this skill are: &lt;a href=\"Frozen%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Frozen&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Necrofire%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Necrofire&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Diseased%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Diseased&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Decaying%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Decaying&lt;/a&gt;.\nSince relies on &lt;a href=\"Hydrosophy\"&gt;Hydrosophy&lt;/a&gt; magic it cannot be cast if caster is affected by &lt;a href=\"Silenced%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Silenced&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Enraged%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Enraged&lt;/a&gt; status effects. skill physical damage is not reflected back when the undead target is under &lt;a href=\"Deflective%20Barrier\"&gt;Deflective Barrier&lt;/a&gt; skill (Definitive Edition only).\nScroll and Skillbook.\n skillbook is a magical item that allows its reader to learn skill, if they have at least 3 points into &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Hydrosophist\"&gt;Hydrosophist&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Attributes%20and%20Abilities%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;ability&lt;/a&gt;, and use it indefinitely. In order to be able to cast the skill, character needs 2 free memory slots. Note that the book will disappear once read. The book weights 0.5 and its base value is 750 gold. A skillbook can be crafted if a scroll is combined with a &lt;a href=\"Blank%20Water%20Skillbook\"&gt;High Tier Blank Water Skillbook&lt;/a&gt;. Since is a expert Hydrosophist skill, traders will start selling the skillbook once &lt;a href=\"Godwoken\"&gt;Godwoken&lt;/a&gt; reach level 13.\n scroll is a magical item that allows any character to cast skill, regardless of skill prerequisites, but only once. The only limiting element in casting this way is the amount of &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Action%20Points\"&gt;Action Points (AP)&lt;/a&gt; character has at their disposal in current turn. The scroll is craftable, weights 0.02 and has base value of 350 gold.\nThe cost of Action Points between scroll and skill themselves varies. The cost to cast the as a source skill is 2 Action Points and 2 &lt;a href=\"Source%20Points%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Source Points&lt;/a&gt;. The cost to cast scroll is only 2 Action Points.\nBoth the scroll and the skill itself are affected by other skills and talents that may provide additional bonuses.\nSkill Modifiers.\n is a supportive skill whose effects depend on the following characteristics of the caster:\nOut of these, Level provides the greatest boon. In case of healing itself the main factor is how many points caster has in &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Hydrosophist\"&gt;Hydrosophist&lt;/a&gt; ability, however this also affects how much physical damage this skill deals to the Undead. Note that, since the skill causes physical damage to the Undead it is also affected by &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Warfare\"&gt;Warfare&lt;/a&gt; ability whose bonus stacks with that of &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Hydrosophist\"&gt;Hydrosophist&lt;/a&gt;.\n properties can be affected by talents, consumable items (some of which may be affected by &lt;a href=\"Five-Star%20Diner%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Five-Star Diner&lt;/a&gt; talent) and other skills. \nLocations.\nTraders.\nFollowing table shows all NPCs who are guaranteed to sell hydrosophist spellbooks, with their location and coordinates in the right column, from them. The location shown in the table (and the coordinates) are only for the initial location the NPC is in. Note that some of these may have other spell/skillbooks and goods to sell. &lt;a href=\"Almira\"&gt;Almira&lt;/a&gt; may follow the Godwoken on &lt;a href=\"The%20Lady%20Vengeance\"&gt;Lady Vengeance&lt;/a&gt; if her demands are met. Also note that &lt;a href=\"Lizard%20Dreamer\"&gt;Lizard Dreamer&lt;/a&gt; requires a persuasion check to be passed in order to speak with him, otherwise he (and the whole encampment) will turn hostile. "}
{"id": "17021", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=17021", "title": "Steamcloud Arrow", "text": " is a type of &lt;a href=\"Munitions%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;ammunition&lt;/a&gt; in \"\".\nCharacteristics.\n is a special arrow which deals water damage and inflicts &lt;a href=\"Wet%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Wet Status&lt;/a&gt; (2 turns) to all characters in area of impact where the arrow will also create a steam cloud (2 meter radius). Note that if character is affected by &lt;a href=\"Chilled%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Chilled Status&lt;/a&gt; using this arrow will cause the character to be affected by &lt;a href=\"Frozen%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Frozen Status&lt;/a&gt;. Likewise if character is affected by &lt;a href=\"Shocked%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Shocked Status&lt;/a&gt; this arrow will cause the character to be affected by &lt;a href=\"Stunned%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Stunned Status&lt;/a&gt;. These statuses are applied only if character has no Magic Armour.\nCharacters need to wield &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Weapons\"&gt;bow or crossbow&lt;/a&gt; in order to use this arrow. The damage of the arrow depends on: base damage of the wielded weapon, &lt;a href=\"Finesse\"&gt;Finesse&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Hydrosophist%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Hydrosophist&lt;/a&gt; and height (bonus from height difference is affected by &lt;a href=\"Huntsman\"&gt;Huntsman&lt;/a&gt;).\nSince is a special arrow it is affected by &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Talents\"&gt;Arrow Recovery&lt;/a&gt; talent which grants 33 % chance to recover a special arrow after firing it. This arrow is also affected by &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Talents\"&gt;Elemental Ranger&lt;/a&gt; talent that grants additional elemental damage bonus depending on the surface the shooting character is standing in. It is possible to increase the range of the arrow by 2 meters through the &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Talents\"&gt;Far Out Man&lt;/a&gt; talent."}
