{"id": "3595", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3595", "title": "Stun Arrows", "text": "Stun Arrows is a &lt;a href=\"Dragon%20Knight%20Saga%20Skills%23Ranger\"&gt;Ranger skill&lt;/a&gt; that can be used by &lt;a href=\"the%20Dragon%20Knight\"&gt;the Dragon Knight&lt;/a&gt; in \"\".\nDescription.\nStun Arrows is a active Ranger skill that allows the Knight to shoot a special arrow that will temporarily incapacitate the target, rendering them unable to move or attack. This skill requires equipped bow in order to be used, therefore using this skill with melee weapon in hand will cause the Knight to automatically switch to equipped bow."}
{"id": "20219", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=20219", "title": "Stunned (Status)", "text": "Stunned is a &lt;a href=\"Status%20Effects%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;status effect&lt;/a&gt; in \"\".\nDescription.\nStunned is a negative environmental &lt;a href=\"Status%20Effects%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;status effect&lt;/a&gt; caused by afflicted character being shocked with electricity twice or by coming into contact with water whilst &lt;a href=\"Shocked%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Shocked&lt;/a&gt;. Stunned status causes afflicted character to be paralysed by electricity, thus rendering them unable to act or dodge attacks (Dodging - 100 %). Stunned status also lowers \"Air Resistance\" by 15 % but increases \"Earth Resistance\" by 10 %. \nStunned status is also accompanied by Immunities to following status effects:\nCause.\nThere are two main ways through which burning status effect can be triggered. On &lt;a href=\"Rivellon\"&gt;Rivellon&lt;/a&gt; if character is already &lt;a href=\"Wet%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Wet&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Shocked%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Shocked&lt;/a&gt; coming in contact with any electrified \"blood\" or \"water\" surface or clouds will cause character to be Stunned unless they have innate immunity to said status. This does not apply to \"cursed electrified water surface\" and \"cursed electrified blood surface\" which will immediatelly apply Stunned status alongside air damage, whenever character without Magic armour makes contact with it. In combat Stunned follows the same rules and combination of \"Shocked\" and Wet can be caused by many of items or most commonly &lt;a href=\"Aerotheurge%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Aerotheurge&lt;/a&gt; spells with the addition of &lt;a href=\"Rain\"&gt;Rain&lt;/a&gt; spell. \nTreatment.\nStunned is a status effect that is tied to air element and is mostly caused if character is already afflicted with \"Shocked\" or \"Wet\" in first place and then once again afflicted with \"Shocked\". There are only two status effects that negate Stunned &lt;a href=\"Permafrost%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Permafrost&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Blessed%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Blessed&lt;/a&gt;. There is a third status that helps against Stunned which is &lt;a href=\"Magic%20Shell%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Magic Shell&lt;/a&gt; status associated with increased Magic armour which is crucial in resisting Stunned status in first place. \nAs with all magic based status effects, the best way to avoid being Stunned is to keep Magic armour above 0 which can be done by using any Magic Armour restoring items or spells. If items such as potions are used then these can be upgraded and their efficiency increased via &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Talents\"&gt;Five-Star Diner talent&lt;/a&gt;. If spells are used then their efficiency can be increased by investing points in &lt;a href=\"Hydrosophist%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Hydrosophist&lt;/a&gt; combat skill which increases Magic armour gained and given. As last resort Magic armour can be gained back through &lt;a href=\"Perseverance\"&gt;Perseverance&lt;/a&gt; but it will only work if character has been incapacitated. \nStatus removal.\nStunned can be removed only through spells or scrolls. Note that while affected character cannot act it is possible to gain temporary immunity against status through &lt;a href=\"Stoneskin%20Potion\"&gt;Stoneskin Potion&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "17105", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=17105", "title": "Stunning Flame Grenade", "text": " is a type of &lt;a href=\"Munitions%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;ammunition&lt;/a&gt; in \"\".\nCharacteristics.\n is a throwable grenade that deals air damage and inflicts &lt;a href=\"Shocked%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Shocked Status&lt;/a&gt; (for 2 turns) in 4 meter radius if the Magic Armour of affected characters reaches 0. Additionaly this grenade will electrify any blood or water surface (and clouds) at the area of impact and unlike the &lt;a href=\"Thunderbolt%20Grenade\"&gt;Thunderbolt Grenade&lt;/a&gt;, the will leave fire surface at the area of impact as well.\nNote that if character is affected by &lt;a href=\"Shocked%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Shocked Status&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Wet%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Wet Status&lt;/a&gt; this grenade will cause the character to be affected by &lt;a href=\"Stunned%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Stunned Status&lt;/a&gt;.\nAll characters can throw this grenade. The damage of the grenade depends on &lt;a href=\"Aerotheurge%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Aerotheurge&lt;/a&gt; ability and can be further increased by &lt;a href=\"Huntsman\"&gt;Huntsman&lt;/a&gt; which boosts the damage bonus provided by height difference.\nSince is a grenade it is affected by &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Talents\"&gt;Ambidextrous&lt;/a&gt; talent which decreases the cost of using grenades and scrolls by 1 AP when the secondary hand is free. is also affected by &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Talents\"&gt;Slingshot&lt;/a&gt; which increases its range by 5 meters and by &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Talents\"&gt;Far Out Man&lt;/a&gt; talent which increases range by 2 meters."}
{"id": "17086", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=17086", "title": "Stunning Ice Grenade", "text": " is a type of &lt;a href=\"Munitions%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;ammunition&lt;/a&gt; in \"\".\nCharacteristics.\n is a throwable grenade that deals air damage and inflicts &lt;a href=\"Shocked%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Shocked Status&lt;/a&gt; (for 2 turns) in 4 meter radius if the Magic Armour of affected characters reaches 0. Additionaly this grenade will electrify any blood or water surface (and clouds) at the area of impact and unlike the &lt;a href=\"Thunderbolt%20Grenade\"&gt;Thunderbolt Grenade&lt;/a&gt;, the will leave ice surface at the area of impact as well.\nNote that if character is affected by &lt;a href=\"Shocked%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Shocked Status&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Wet%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Wet Status&lt;/a&gt; this grenade will cause the character to be affected by &lt;a href=\"Stunned%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Stunned Status&lt;/a&gt;.\nAll characters can throw this grenade. The damage of the grenade depends on &lt;a href=\"Aerotheurge%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Aerotheurge&lt;/a&gt; ability and can be further increased by &lt;a href=\"Huntsman\"&gt;Huntsman&lt;/a&gt; which boosts the damage bonus provided by height difference.\nSince is a grenade it is affected by &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Talents\"&gt;Ambidextrous&lt;/a&gt; talent which decreases the cost of using grenades and scrolls by 1 AP when the secondary hand is free. is also affected by &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Talents\"&gt;Slingshot&lt;/a&gt; which increases its range by 5 meters and by &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Talents\"&gt;Far Out Man&lt;/a&gt; talent which increases range by 2 meters."}
