{"id": "14101", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=14101", "title": "Succubus", "text": "A Succubus (plural: Succubi) are a subrace of &lt;a href=\"demon\"&gt;demon&lt;/a&gt;s.\nDescription.\nSuccubi are a female demons who attack their victims with illusions and charms. They will try to get near their victims, because their kiss is lethal to mortals. They original appeared as very tall, about 3\u20134 meters height, blue skinned women with a long tail and two hymenopteras wings (in this form they appeared only in Divine Divinity).\nIn later games, namely and , the succubi\u00a0are presented as &lt;a href=\"human\"&gt;human&lt;/a&gt;-like women. They mostly wear revealing clothes, have tattoos and may have small horns. They often serve as spies, interrogators and courtesans of their masters. Their most feared ability, the \"lethal\" kiss that is not lethal anymore, can make the receiver a thrall of the succubus."}
