{"id": "12413", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=12413", "title": "Summon Fire Slug", "text": "Summon Fire Slug is an &lt;a href=\"Pyrokinetic%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;adept pyrokinetic source skill&lt;/a&gt; in \"\".\nDescription.\nSkill.\n is a summoning pyrokinetic source skill that allows caster to conjure a friendly fire slug that will fight for them for 5 turns. The fire slug does fire damage with its base close-range attacks and leaves behind a small trail of fire surface as it moves. The slug has + 120 % Fire Resistance that allows it to heal from any fire damage done, but takes increased water damage as it has - 50 % Water Resistance. The slug also has small amount of Physical Armour and large amount of Magic Armour.\nThe fire slug has access to two skills. An adept pyrokinetic skill &lt;a href=\"Laser%20Ray\"&gt;Laser Ray&lt;/a&gt; and a special skill &lt;a href=\"Slug%20Rush\"&gt;Slug Rush&lt;/a&gt; that works the same way as Bull Rush, that pushes the slug forward, dealing fire damage to all enemies in vicinity and leaving fire surface behind it. \nSince relies on &lt;a href=\"Pyrokinesis\"&gt;Pyrokinesis&lt;/a&gt; magic it cannot be cast if caster is affected by &lt;a href=\"Silenced%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Silenced&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Enraged%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Enraged&lt;/a&gt; status effects.\nScroll and Skillbook.\n skillbook is a magical item that allows its reader to learn skill, if they have at least 3 points into &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Pyrokinetic\"&gt;Pyrokinetic&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Attributes%20and%20Abilities%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;ability&lt;/a&gt;, and use it indefinitely. In order to be able to cast the skill, character needs 2 free memory slots. Note that the book will disappear once read. The book weights 0.5 and its base value is 800 gold. Since is a adept Pyrokinetic skill, traders will start selling the skillbook once &lt;a href=\"Godwoken\"&gt;Godwoken&lt;/a&gt; reach level 9.\n is one of the few magic-based skills in the game that does not have a scroll.\nSkill Modifiers.\n is a summoning skill and as such it is primarily affected by Level, &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Summoning\"&gt;Summoning&lt;/a&gt; ability of the caster. Due to the fire slug relying heavily on fire based attacks and skills it also receives large bonus from Pyrokinetic ability that is in itself defined by the level of the caster.\n properties can be affected by talents and skills. With the exception of infusions, which do not work in the base game, the fire slug can be buffed the same way as any allied character or companion. \nLocations.\nTraders.\nFollowing table shows all NPCs who are guaranteed to sell pyrokinetic spellbooks, with their location and coordinates in the right column, from them. The location shown in the table (and the coordinates) are only for the initial location the NPC is in. Note that some of these may have other spell/skillbooks and goods to sell. &lt;a href=\"Almira\"&gt;Almira&lt;/a&gt; may follow the Godwoken on &lt;a href=\"The%20Lady%20Vengeance\"&gt;Lady Vengeance&lt;/a&gt; if her demands are met.\nAlso sold by &lt;a href=\"Hannag\"&gt;Hannag&lt;/a&gt; at &lt;a href=\"Cloisterwood\"&gt;Cloisterwood&lt;/a&gt; who sells only Adept and Expert Source spells of various magic schools. She is not exclusively Pyrokinetic vendor.\nGift Bag: Pet Power.\nGift bag: Pet Power allows the player to infuse not only their Incarnate but also all other summoned creatures. This includes \"Fire slug\" as well. Note that skills gained by infusing it, may differ from skills gained by infusing other summoned creatures."}
{"id": "3674", "revid": "32621914", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3674", "title": "Summon Friend", "text": "Summon Friend is a &lt;a href=\"Skills%20%28Dragon%20Knight%20Saga%29%23Dragon\"&gt;dragon skill&lt;/a&gt; that can be used by &lt;a href=\"Dragon\"&gt;Dragon&lt;/a&gt;s and &lt;a href=\"Dragon%20Knights\"&gt;Dragon Knights&lt;/a&gt;. \nDescription.\nSummon Friend is a \"dragon skill\" that will summon a friendly &lt;a href=\"wyvern\"&gt;wyvern&lt;/a&gt; that will attack enemies and structures in its sight. The wyvern will not follow the dragon and will fly around the location it has been summoned."}
{"id": "3599", "revid": "49135869", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3599", "title": "Summon Ghost", "text": "Summon Ghost is a &lt;a href=\"Dragon%20Knight%20Saga%20Skills%23Priest\"&gt;Priest skill&lt;/a&gt; that can be used by &lt;a href=\"the%20Dragon%20Knight\"&gt;the Dragon Knight&lt;/a&gt; in \"\".\nDescription.\nSummon Ghost is a active Priest skill that allows the Knight to summon a &lt;a href=\"Ghost\"&gt;Ghost&lt;/a&gt; from &lt;a href=\"Hall%20of%20Echoes\"&gt;Hall of Echoes&lt;/a&gt;. The Ghost will follow and attack enemies as well as heal the Knight. Each level increases the Ghost's damage, HP, resistances and spell power.\u00a0The exact amounts are not shown but a summoned creature is almost always able to win a one-on-one fight with a &lt;a href=\"Creatures\"&gt;monster&lt;/a&gt; of the same level.\nNote: You may not have more than 1 summoned creature (excluding your pet) at once.\nThis skill can also be used to resolve &lt;a href=\"Divine%20Descendant\"&gt;a quest&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "12336", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=12336", "title": "Summon Hungry Flower", "text": "Summon Hungry Flower is an &lt;a href=\"Geomancer%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;adept Geomancer&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Sourcery%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;source&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Skills\"&gt;skill&lt;/a&gt; in \"\".\nDescription.\nSkill.\n is a summoning geomancer source skill that allows caster to conjure a friendly Hungry Flower for 5 turns in 13 meter range. The flower does poison damage with its close range basic attacks. Characters without Physical Armour will be afflicted with &lt;a href=\"Poisoned%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Poisoned&lt;/a&gt; status effect for 2 turns and suffer damage directly to their health. \nThe flower has high Magic Armour and little Physical Armour. Starts combat with 4 Action Points and possesses + 120 % Poison Resistance allowing it to heal from all poison damage done to it. The second highest resistance it has is + 80 % Earth Resistance, then + 30 % Water Resistance and + 20 % Air Resistance. The plant will however take increased fire damage as it has - 50 % Fire Resistance. Other than this the plant has no talents but has immunity to &lt;a href=\"Poisoned%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Poisoned&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Acid%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Acid&lt;/a&gt; status effects. The plant can move 4 meters per 1 Action Point. Its main attributes are &lt;a href=\"Strength\"&gt;Strength&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Constitution\"&gt;Constitution&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe Hungry Flower has access to 3 skills:\nSince relies on &lt;a href=\"Geomancy\"&gt;Geomancy&lt;/a&gt; magic it cannot be cast if caster is affected by &lt;a href=\"Silenced%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Silenced&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Enraged%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Enraged&lt;/a&gt; status effects.\nScroll and Skillbook.\n skillbook is a magical item that allows its reader to learn skill, if they have at least 3 points into &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Geomancer\"&gt;Geomancer&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Attributes%20and%20Abilities%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;ability&lt;/a&gt;, and use it indefinitely. In order to be able to cast the skill, character needs 2 free memory slots. Note that the book will disappear once read. The book weights 0.5 and its base value is 800 gold. A skillbook can be crafted if a scroll is combined with a &lt;a href=\"Blank%20Earth%20Skillbook\"&gt;Blank Earth Skillbook&lt;/a&gt;. Since is a adept Geomancer skill, traders will start selling the skillbook once player character or their &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Companions\"&gt;companions&lt;/a&gt; reach level 9.\n scroll is a magical item that allows any character to cast skill, regardless of skill prerequisites, but only once. The only limiting element in casting this way is the amount of &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Action%20Points\"&gt;Action Points (AP)&lt;/a&gt; character has at their disposal in current turn. The scroll is craftable, weights 0.02 and has base value of 260 gold.\nThe cost of Action Points between scroll and skill themselves varies. The cost to cast as a source skill is 3 Action Points and 1 Source Point whereas the cost to cast as a scroll is only 3 Action Points.\nBoth the scroll and the skill itself are affected by other skills and talents that may provide additional bonuses.\nSkill Modifiers.\n is a summoning skill and as such it is primarily affected by Level, &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Summoning\"&gt;Summoning&lt;/a&gt; ability of the caster. Due to the hungry flower relying heavily on poison attacks and skills it also receives large bonus from Geomancer ability. The Hungry Flower begins to receive points into Geomancer when caster is level 1. Following table shows at which level the flower receives points into Geomancer.\n properties can be affected by talents and skills. With the exception of infusions, which do not work in the base game, the Hungry Flower can be buffed the same way as any allied character or companion. \nLocations.\nTraders.\nFollowing table shows all NPCs who are guaranteed to sell Geomancer spellbooks, with their location and coordinates in the right column, from them. The location shown in the table (and the coordinates) are only for the initial location the NPC is in. Note that some of these may have other spell/skillbooks and goods to sell. Out of these only &lt;a href=\"Gareth%20Pryce\"&gt;Gareth&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Almira\"&gt;Almira&lt;/a&gt; may follow the &lt;a href=\"Godwoken\"&gt;Godwoken&lt;/a&gt; throughout the game on &lt;a href=\"the%20Lady%20Vengeance\"&gt;the Lady Vengeance&lt;/a&gt;, provided their demands are met.\nGift Bag: Pet Power.\nGift bag: Pet Power allows the player to infuse not only their Incarnate but also all other summoned creatures. This includes \"Hungry Flower\" as well. Note that skills gained by infusing it, may differ from skills gained by infusing other summoned creatures."}
