{"id": "21367", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=21367", "title": "Summoning Diary 2", "text": " is a &lt;a href=\"Beyond%20Divinity%20books%20and%20notes\"&gt;book&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Beyond%20Divinity\"&gt;Beyond Divinity&lt;/a&gt;\"."}
{"id": "11519", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=11519", "title": "Supercharger", "text": "Supercharger is a &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Summoning\"&gt;novice Summoning&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Skills\"&gt;skill&lt;/a&gt; in \"\".\nDescription.\nSkill.\nSupercharger skill will increase the attack power of the Incarnate by 50%. However it will also make it die its next turn. \nSince relies on &lt;a href=\"Summoning\"&gt;Summoning&lt;/a&gt; magic it cannot be cast if caster is affected by &lt;a href=\"Silenced%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Silenced&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Enraged%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Enraged&lt;/a&gt; status effects.\nScroll and Skillbook.\n skillbook is a magical item that allows its reader to learn skill, if they have at least 2 points into &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Summoning\"&gt;Summoning&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Attributes%20and%20Abilities%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;ability&lt;/a&gt;, and use it indefinitely. In order to be able to cast the skill, character needs 1 free memory slot. Note that the book will disappear once read. The book weights 0.5 and its base value is 190 gold. Since is a novice Summoning skill, traders will start selling the skillbook once &lt;a href=\"Godwoken\"&gt;Godwoken&lt;/a&gt; reach level 4.\n is one of the few magic-based skills in the game that does not have a scroll.\nLocations.\nTraders.\nFollowing table shows all NPCs who are guaranteed to sell summoning spellbooks, with their location and coordinates in the right column, from them. The location shown in the table (and the coordinates) are only for the initial location the NPC is in."}
{"id": "12292", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=12292", "title": "Superconductor", "text": "Superconductor is a &lt;a href=\"Aerotheurge%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;master Aerotheurge&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Sourcery%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;source&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Skills\"&gt;skill&lt;/a&gt; in \"\".\nDescription.\nSkill.\n is a offensive aerotheurge skill that allows caster to shoot an electric spark at all enemies up to 8 meters from them. The sparks deal air damage.\nCharacters without Magic Armour (with the exception of the caster) will be afflicted with &lt;a href=\"Shocked%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Shocked&lt;/a&gt; status effect for 2 turns and will suffer damage directly to their health. If character is already affected by &lt;a href=\"Shocked%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Shocked&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Wet%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Wet&lt;/a&gt;, they will be instead affected by &lt;a href=\"Stunned%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Stunned&lt;/a&gt; status effect which will paralyse them for 1 turn.\nSince relies on &lt;a href=\"Aerotheurgy\"&gt;Aerotheurgy&lt;/a&gt; magic it cannot be cast if character is affected by &lt;a href=\"Silenced%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Silenced&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Enraged%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Enraged&lt;/a&gt; status effects. skill is reflected back when the target is under &lt;a href=\"Deflective%20Barrier\"&gt;Deflective Barrier&lt;/a&gt; skill.\nScroll and Skillbook.\n skillbook is a magical item that allows its reader to learn skill, if they have at least 3 points into &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Aerotheurge\"&gt;Aerotheurge&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Attributes%20and%20Abilities%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;ability&lt;/a&gt;, and use it indefinitely. In order to be able to cast the skill, character needs 1 free memory slot. Note that the book will disappear once read. The book weights 0.5 and its base value is 1400 gold. A skillbook can be crafted if a scroll is combined with a &lt;a href=\"Blank%20Air%20Skillbook\"&gt;High Tier Blank Air Skillbook&lt;/a&gt;. Since is a master Aerotheurge skill, traders will start selling the skillbook once player character or their &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Companions\"&gt;companions&lt;/a&gt; reach level 16.\n scroll is a magical item that allows any character to cast skill, regardless of skill prerequisites, but only once. The only limiting element in casting this way is the amount of &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Action%20Points\"&gt;Action Points&lt;/a&gt; character has at their disposal in current turn. The scroll is craftable, weights 0.02 and has base value of 350 gold.\nThe cost of Action Points between scroll and skill themselves remains the same. Both the scroll and the skill itself are affected by other skills and talents that may provide additional bonuses.\nSkill Modifiers.\nDamage of this skill is calculated with the following formula: (Base Damage) x (1 + Elemental Bonus%) x (1 + Attribute Bonus% + Weapon Skill Bonus %) x (1 + High Ground Bonus% + Crit Bonus%) x ( 1 + Misc Bonus %)\nThe damage of this skill is affected by the following attributes of the caster:\nOut of these the most effect on the damage have Level and then Aerotheurge ability as the latter increases damage by 5 % per point. Level provides greatest boost to the damage done. Intelligence provides the lowest bonus out of the three (3 points in Intelligence are equal to 1 point of Aerotheurge).\nWhen it comes to enemies they may resist air damage if they have: Air Immunity Status and high enough Air Resistance (which lowers air damage done).\n properties can be affected by talents, consumable items (some of which may be affected by &lt;a href=\"Five-Star%20Diner%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Five-Star Diner&lt;/a&gt; talent) and other skills. \nLocations.\nTraders.\nFollowing table shows all NPCs who are guaranteed to sell hydrosophist spellbooks, with their location and coordinates in the right column, from them. The location shown in the table (and the coordinates) are only for the initial location the NPC is in. Note that some of these may have other spell/skillbooks and goods to sell. &lt;a href=\"Almira\"&gt;Almira&lt;/a&gt; may follow the Godwoken on &lt;a href=\"The%20Lady%20Vengeance\"&gt;Lady Vengeance&lt;/a&gt; if her demands are met. Also note that &lt;a href=\"Lizard%20Dreamer\"&gt;Lizard Dreamer&lt;/a&gt; requires a persuasion check to be passed in order to speak with him, otherwise he (and the whole encampment) will turn hostile. \nNotes.\nThe skill appears to be bugged in PC version of the Definitive Edition. In the Game Master mode the skill has only 5 meter range instead of 8 meter range as written in the skill description."}
{"id": "12412", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=12412", "title": "Supernova", "text": "Supernova is a &lt;a href=\"Pyrokinetic%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;novice pyrokinetic skill&lt;/a&gt; in \"\".\nDescription.\nSkill.\n is a offensive pyrokinetic skill that allows character to release a fiery explosion around themselves in 4 meter radius. The wave of fire is blocked by obstacles and deals fire damage to all targets, including the caster, and ignites all susceptible surfaces as well as de-frosts all frozen surfaces. Characters without Magic Armour will be afflicted with &lt;a href=\"Burning%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Burning&lt;/a&gt; status effect for 2 turns and suffer damage directly to their health. Due to this skill dealing area of effect damage around the caster it will reveal all hostile characters under &lt;a href=\"Invisible%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Invisible&lt;/a&gt; status effect.\nSince relies on &lt;a href=\"Pyrokinesis\"&gt;Pyrokinesis&lt;/a&gt; magic it cannot be cast if caster is affected by &lt;a href=\"Silenced%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Silenced&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Enraged%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Enraged&lt;/a&gt; status effects. skill is reflected back when the target is under &lt;a href=\"Deflective%20Barrier\"&gt;Deflective Barrier&lt;/a&gt; skill (Definitive Edition only).\nScroll and Skillbook.\n skillbook is a magical item that allows its reader to learn skill, if they have at least 2 points into &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Pyrokinetic\"&gt;Pyrokinetic&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Attributes%20and%20Abilities%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;ability&lt;/a&gt;, and use it indefinitely. In order to be able to cast the skill, character needs 1 free memory slot. Note that the book will disappear once read. The book weights 0.5 and its base value is 190 gold. A skillbook can be crafted if a scroll is combined with a &lt;a href=\"Blank%20Fire%20Skillbook\"&gt;Blank Fire Skillbook&lt;/a&gt;. Since is a novice Pyrokinetic skill, traders will start selling the skillbook once &lt;a href=\"Godwoken\"&gt;Godwoken&lt;/a&gt; reach level 4.\n scroll is a magical item that allows any character to cast skill, regardless of skill prerequisites, but only once. The only limiting element in casting this way is the amount of &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Action%20Points\"&gt;Action Points (AP)&lt;/a&gt; character has at their disposal in current turn. The scroll is craftable, weights 0.02 and has base value of 100 gold.\nThe cost of Action Points between scroll and skill themselves remains the same. Both the scroll and the skill itself are affected by other skills, attributes and talents that may provide additional bonuses.\nSkill Modifiers.\nDamage of this skill is calculated with the following formula: (Base Damage) x (1 + Elemental Bonus%) x (1 + Attribute Bonus% + Weapon Skill Bonus %) x (1 + High Ground Bonus% + Crit Bonus%) x ( 1 + Misc Bonus %)\nThe damage of this skill is affected by the following attributes of the caster:\nOut of these the most effect on the damage have Level and then Pyrokinetic ability as the latter increases damage by 5 % per point. Level provides greatest boost to the damage done. Intelligence provides the lowest bonus out of the three (3 points in Intelligence are equal to 1 point of Pyrokinetic).\nWhen it comes to enemies they may resist fire damage if they have: Fire Immunity Status and high enough Fire Resistance (which lowers fire damage done).\n properties can be affected by talents, consumable items (some of which may be affected by &lt;a href=\"Five-Star%20Diner%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Five-Star Diner&lt;/a&gt; talent) and other skills.\nLocations.\nTraders.\nFollowing table shows all NPCs who are guaranteed to sell pyrokinetic spellbooks, with their location and coordinates in the right column, from them. The location shown in the table (and the coordinates) are only for the initial location the NPC is in. Note that some of these may have other spell/skillbooks and goods to sell. &lt;a href=\"Almira\"&gt;Almira&lt;/a&gt; may follow the Godwoken on &lt;a href=\"The%20Lady%20Vengeance\"&gt;Lady Vengeance&lt;/a&gt; if her demands are met."}
