{"id": "14599", "revid": "49426621", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=14599", "title": "Svadilfari cave", "text": " is a cave in &lt;a href=\"Red%20Hammer%20Tribe\"&gt;Red Hammer Tribe&lt;/a&gt; territory within &lt;a href=\"Orobas%20Fjords\"&gt;Orobas Fjords&lt;/a&gt;.\nLayout.\nThe cave itself is a T-shaped structure, with the entrance at the southern point. From the entrance, one must travel down the stairs to the junction. To the east is &lt;a href=\"Groth\"&gt;Groth&lt;/a&gt;, behind a locked door, which cannot be opened and will not open until &lt;a href=\"Much%20Ado%20About%20Goblins\"&gt;Much Ado About Goblins&lt;/a&gt; has been competed. In this chamber with Groth is a &lt;a href=\"Dragon%20Skill%20Book\"&gt;Dragon Skill Book&lt;/a&gt; and two keys, which open chests in the west chamber.\nTo the west, &lt;a href=\"Timpuk\"&gt;Timpuk&lt;/a&gt; the trader can found just beyond the junction, further in to the rear is &lt;a href=\"Svadilfari\"&gt;Svadilfari&lt;/a&gt; with the bulk of the tribe. To the north of the fires in the chamber are two chests, both locked (the aforementioned keys are required to open them) and the &lt;a href=\"Hunter%20Cuirass\"&gt;Hunter Cuirass&lt;/a&gt; can be found in the eastern of the two. On the western wall, is a scaffolding platform with a third chest, containing &lt;a href=\"Svadilfari%27s%20Dragon%20Armour\"&gt;Svadilfari's Dragon Armour&lt;/a&gt; (if Svadilfari was mindread)."}
{"id": "19966", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=19966", "title": "Swap Places", "text": " is a &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Skills\"&gt;special skill&lt;/a&gt; in \"\".\nDescription.\nSwap places is a special skill exclusive to the &lt;a href=\"Black%20Cat\"&gt;Black Cat&lt;/a&gt;, summoned through the spell &lt;a href=\"Summon%20Cat%20Familiar\"&gt;Summon Cat Familiar&lt;/a&gt;. It allows the cat to switch places with its summoner if they are in its range of sight. Unlike &lt;a href=\"Teleportation%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Teleportation&lt;/a&gt; this spell does not cause any physical damage upon using it. "}
