{"id": "9223", "revid": "49426621", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=9223", "title": "Teddy", "text": "Teddy is a psychiatric patient at the &lt;a href=\"Wild%20Willows%20Manor\"&gt;Wild Willows Manor&lt;/a&gt; in the &lt;a href=\"Crow%27s%20Nest\"&gt;Crow's Nest&lt;/a&gt; district of &lt;a href=\"Aleroth\"&gt;Aleroth&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0in 1300 AD.\nBackground.\nHe is located near the lobby, locked in the cell directly north of the building's entrance. If asked who is, he initially says \"Josiah the talking turtle.\" Later on, however, he believes that he is a wolf and needs to return to his pack because the cubs are hungry. If\u00a0freed he will take\u00a0the opportunity to flee the asylum unless asked to help with the plates. Afterwards he can be found roaming the building.\nInteractions with player character.\nRelated Quests.\nThe key to Teddy's cell is in the possession of the criminal &lt;a href=\"Jango\"&gt;Jango&lt;/a&gt;. To get it, you can:\nThere is no benefit to freeing Teddy after the pressure plates have been activated, but he does take the opportunity to flee the asylum. If asked to help with the plates he remains in the building afterwards."}
{"id": "15014", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=15014", "title": "Telekinesis (Divine Divinity)", "text": " is a &lt;a href=\"Divine%20Divinity%20skills%23Way%20of%20the%20mage\"&gt;Mage skill&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Divine%20Divinity\"&gt;Divine Divinity&lt;/a&gt;\".\nDescription.\nAllows &lt;a href=\"Lucian\"&gt;Lucian&lt;/a&gt; to use objects and pickup items from afar. It doesn't work for unidentifed items that are not in a container, but does work on them if they are in a container. One cast per container is enough, but items outside container are picked up one-by-one.\nCan be used with &lt;a href=\"Wizard%27s%20Sight\"&gt;Wizard's Sight&lt;/a&gt; to take items, even from stores without penalties, albeit in a small time window."}
{"id": "6355", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=6355", "title": "Telekinesis (Original Sin)", "text": "Telekinesis is a skill in and its . \nTelekinesis.\nThis skill grants you the ability to pick up items from a distance and/or move objects in the game world (barrels/boxes/etc.)\nEvery level increases the maximum distance by 2 meters, starting from 0.\nEvery level increases the weight of items able to be picked up/moved. Not affected by strength.\nTelekinesis can be used Offensively in combat. Just drag a heavy (a crate filled with barrels kept in inventory for example) item onto an enemy. Costs 2 AP.\nIn game you can spot items (keys etc.) which would otherwise be out of reach, or trapped (behind lava etc.). This ability can help you to collect them.\nSince some gear can increase this ability, you don't necessarily need to fully invest into it to reach max ability level.\nTelekinesis Skill &amp; Gear.\nYou can find Rings and Bracers that increase Telekinesis skill."}
{"id": "10743", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=10743", "title": "Telekinesis (Original Sin 2)", "text": "Telekinesis is a &lt;a href=\"Attributes%20and%20Abilities%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;civil ability&lt;/a&gt; in \"\".\nDescription.\nTelekinesis is a skill that allows the collection, placement and movement of objects in the world from a distance, this range increases with each point into the ability.\nThis is useful for collecting items that are behind other objects that block your character from physically standing in-front of them to collect them, it is also helpful to move objects onto traps such as poison traps to block their cloud effect.\nTelekinesis Combat Exploit.\nThere is a known combat exploit using Telekinesis which over time can make combat in Divinity Original Sin 2 nearly trivial. This is based on the following aspects:\nThe above, combined with a player diligently picking up everything that isn't nailed down and putting it into the invincible container and then \"carrying\" the container via Telekinesis wherever they go (you will need to have the character pick it up into inventory to be able to get it through a site transition door/ladder/portal), will result in a container quickly obtaining a weight in the thousands which when thrown into an enemy via Telekinesis will one-shot kill every enemy in the game."}
