{"id": "10349", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=10349", "title": "Teleportation (Original Sin 2)", "text": "Teleportation is a &lt;a href=\"Aerotheurge%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;novice Aerotheurge&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Skills\"&gt;skill&lt;/a&gt; in \"\".\nCharacteristics.\nSkill.\nTeleportation allows the user to move objects (inanimate or otherwise) from one location to another and can be vital in retrieving objects that cannot be reached in any other way. Teleporting individuals and objects damages that which is moved, depending on the &lt;a href=\"Aerotheurge%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;aerotheurge&lt;/a&gt; skill of the caster, and this damage can be blocked by Physical armor.\nNote, the caster cannot teleport themself. To be able to teleport your entire party you will need at least 2 members with Teleport, and it is recommended to get this early as a large number of areas will need this kind of mobility to get through.\nScroll and Skillbook.\n skillbook is a magical item that allows its reader to learn skill, if they have at least 2 points into &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Aerotheurge\"&gt;Aerotheurge&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Attributes%20and%20Abilities%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;ability&lt;/a&gt;, and use it indefinitely. In order to be able to cast the skill, character needs 1 free memory slot. Note that the book will disappear once read. The book weights 0.5 and its base value is 120 gold. A skillbook can be crafted if a scroll is combined with a &lt;a href=\"Blank%20Air%20Skillbook\"&gt;Blank Air Skillbook&lt;/a&gt;. Since is a novice Aerotheurge skill, traders will start selling the skillbook once player character or their &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Companions\"&gt;companions&lt;/a&gt; reach level 4. \n scroll is a magical item that allows any character to cast skill, regardless of skill prerequisites, but only once. The only limiting element in casting this way is the amount of &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Action%20Points\"&gt;Action Points (AP)&lt;/a&gt; character has at their disposal in current turn. The scroll is craftable, weights 0.02 and has base value of 100 gold.\nThe cost of Action Points between scroll and skill themselves remains the same. Both the scroll and the skill itself are affected by other skills, attributes and talents that may provide additional bonuses.\nLocations.\nTraders.\nFollowing table shows all NPCs who are guaranteed to sell hydrosophist spellbooks, with their location and coordinates in the right column, from them. The location shown in the table (and the coordinates) are only for the initial location the NPC is in. Note that some of these may have other spell/skillbooks and goods to sell. &lt;a href=\"Almira\"&gt;Almira&lt;/a&gt; may follow the Godwoken on &lt;a href=\"The%20Lady%20Vengeance\"&gt;Lady Vengeance&lt;/a&gt; if her demands are met. Also note that &lt;a href=\"Lizard%20Dreamer\"&gt;Lizard Dreamer&lt;/a&gt; requires a persuasion check to be passed in order to speak with him, otherwise he (and the whole encampment) will turn hostile. "}
{"id": "14906", "revid": "49426621", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=14906", "title": "Teleporter Activation Scroll", "text": "Teleporter Activation Scrolls are &lt;a href=\"Divine%20Divinity%20quest%20items\"&gt;quest items&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Divine%20Divinity\"&gt;Divine Divinity&lt;/a&gt;.\"\nCharacteristics.\nThese scrolls are used to activate Teleporters around &lt;a href=\"Rivellon\"&gt;Rivellon&lt;/a&gt;. Each race has their own activation scroll which is well guarded to prevent misuse of the teleporters.\nThe scrolls are only needed to activate teleporters: after being activated, the teleporters can be used without a scroll."}
