{"id": "11577", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=11577", "title": "Tentacle Lash", "text": "Tentacle lash is a &lt;a href=\"Polymorph%20%28Skill%20Class%29\"&gt;starter Polymorph&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Skills\"&gt;skill&lt;/a&gt; in \"\".\nDescription.\nSkill.\nTentacle lash throws a long octopus tentacle out at the target that deals &lt;a href=\"Physical%20and%20Magical%20Armor%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Physical damage&lt;/a&gt; and sets &lt;a href=\"Status%20Effects%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29%23Negative\"&gt;Atrophy&lt;/a&gt; it also disarms the target. Damage is based on level and receives bonus from &lt;a href=\"Strength\"&gt;Strength&lt;/a&gt;.\nScroll and Skillbook.\n skillbook is a magical item that allows its reader to learn skill, if they have at least 1 point into &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Polymorph\"&gt;Polymorph&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Attributes%20and%20Abilities%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;ability&lt;/a&gt;, and use it indefinitely. In order to be able to cast the skill, character needs 1 free memory slot. Note that the book will disappear once read. The book weights 0.5 and its base value is 120 gold. A skillbook can be crafted if a scroll is combined with a &lt;a href=\"Blank%20Polymorph%20Skillbook\"&gt;Blank Polymorph Skillbook&lt;/a&gt;. Since is a starter Polymorph skill, it is available right from the start of the game. Traders selling Polymorph skillbooks will have this book for sale since the start of the game as well. \n scroll is a magical item that allows any character to cast skill, regardless of skill prerequisites, but only once. The only limiting element in casting this way is the amount of &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Action%20Points\"&gt;Action Points (AP)&lt;/a&gt; character has at their disposal in current turn. The scroll is craftable, weights 0.02 and has base value of 70 gold.\nThe cost of Action Points between scroll and skill themselves remains the same. Both the scroll and the skill itself are affected by other skills, attributes and talents that may provide additional bonuses.\nLocations.\nTraders.\nFollowing table shows all NPCs who are guaranteed to sell Polymorph spellbooks, with their location and coordinates in the right column, from them. The location shown in the table (and the coordinates) are only for the initial location the NPC is in. Note that some of these may have other spell/skillbooks and goods to sell. "}
