{"id": "12148", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=12148", "title": "Fire Essence", "text": "Fire essence is a &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Crafting\"&gt;crafting component&lt;/a&gt; in ' and '.\nDescription.\nFire essence is an ingredient, that can be bought from various NPCs or looted from monsters. On its own the essence is useless. However it is essential in crafting various &lt;a href=\"Pyrokinetic%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Pyrokinetic&lt;/a&gt; scrolls and a &lt;a href=\"Potion%20of%20Strong%20Will\"&gt;Potion of Strong Will&lt;/a&gt;\nLocations.\nCreatures.\nFollowing table shows all creatures which have a chance to drop the item upon death. Highlighted creatures in this table have 100 % chance to drop said item. Note that creatures may drop other items as well.\nUsage.\nFollowing table shows all items for which this item is used for. Note that for more powerful Pyrokinetic scrolls a better quality Fire essence is required. If the scroll utilises base Fire essence it is possible to use higher quality essence as substitute. In short you cannot use \"Fire Essence\" in recipe requiring \"Alien Fire Essence\" or \"High Quality Fire Essence\"."}
{"id": "12445", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=12445", "title": "Fire Infusion", "text": "Fire infusion is a &lt;a href=\"Pyrokinetic%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Pyrokinetic&lt;/a&gt; and a &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Summoning\"&gt;Summoning skill&lt;/a&gt; in \"\".\nDescription.\nSkill.\n is a supportive mixed skill that allows caster to change their summoned Incarnate's element to fire. By changing the element, the Incarnate gains multiple boons associated with it. Its basic close attack will deal fire damage. Due to the Incarnate being infused with fire it gains Fire Resistance + 100 % but it suffer from decreased resistance: Water Resistance - 20 %. Besides Fire resistance being increased the Incarnate becomes immune to &lt;a href=\"Burning%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Burning&lt;/a&gt; status effect. Alongside this the Incarnate learns the Pyrokinetic skill &lt;a href=\"Fireball%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Fireball&lt;/a&gt;. Lastly it will receive + 5 points to &lt;a href=\"Pyrokinetic%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Pyrokinetic&lt;/a&gt; ability itself.\nNote that the effects of are achieved by summoning the Incarnate unto any fire surface.\nSince relies on &lt;a href=\"Pyrokinesis\"&gt;Pyrokinesis&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Summoning\"&gt;Summoning&lt;/a&gt; magic it cannot be cast if caster is affected by &lt;a href=\"Silenced%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Silenced&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Enraged%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Enraged&lt;/a&gt; status effects.\nScroll and Skillbook.\n skillbook is a magical item that allows its reader to learn skill, if they have at least 1 point into both &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Pyrokinetic\"&gt;Pyrokinetic&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Summoning\"&gt;Summoning&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Attributes%20and%20Abilities%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;abilities&lt;/a&gt;, and use it indefinitely. In order to be able to cast the skill, character needs 1 free memory slot. Note that the book will disappear once read. The book weights 0.5 and its base value is 190 gold. A skillbook can be crafted if a any non-source &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Pyrokinetic\"&gt;Pyrokinetic&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Summoning\"&gt;Summoning&lt;/a&gt; skillbooks are combined. Since is a mixed skill, traders do not have the skillbook for sale.\n is one of the few magic-based skills in the game that does not have a scroll.\nLocations.\nTraders.\nThis skill cannot be bought or stolen from NPCs in the game. \nGift Bag: Pet Power.\nGift Bag: Pet Power allows this skill to be used on any summoned creature. This gift bag also shortens the cooldown of this skill from 3 turns to 1 turn. Following table shows what skills will specific summoned entity gain from . Note that there are no changes to the skill and bonuses granted by the skill to the &lt;a href=\"Conjure%20Incarnate\"&gt;Incarnate&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "10940", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=10940", "title": "Fire Resistance Potion (Original Sin 2)", "text": "Fire resistance potion is a &lt;a href=\"Consumables%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;potion&lt;/a&gt; in \"\".\nCharacteristics.\nFire resistance potion is a consumable potion that grants + 15 % Fire resistance for 3 turns. If character has \"&lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Talents\"&gt;Five-Star Diner talent&lt;/a&gt;\", the potion will grant + 30 % Fire resistance instead of + 15 %. The potions weight is 0.25 and its value is 30 gold.\nMedium fire resistance potion is a consumable potion that grants + 50 % Fire resistance for 3 turns. If character has \"Five-Star Diner talent\", the potion will grant + 100 % Fire resistance instead of + 50 %. The potions weight is 0.25 and its value is 45 gold.\nLarge fire resistance potion is a consumable potion that grants 75 % Fire resistance for 2 turns. If character has \"Five-Star Diner talent\", the potion will grant + 150 % Fire resistance instead of + 75 %. The potions weight is 0.25 and its value is 150 gold.\nHuge fire resistance potion is a consumable potion that grants 90 % Fire resistance for 2 turns. If character has \"Five-Star Diner talent\", the potion will grant + 180 % Fire resistance instead of + 90 %. The potions weight is 0.25 and its value is 450 gold.\nLocations.\nTraders.\nFollowing NPCs sell a large variety of potions and thus have a solid chance (not guaranteed) of having in their stock. Note that as a consumable item may be very randomly sold by other NPCs."}
