{"id": "12345", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=12345", "title": "First Aid (Original Sin 2)", "text": "First aid is a &lt;a href=\"Huntsman\"&gt;starter Huntsman&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Skills\"&gt;skill&lt;/a&gt; in \"\".\nDescription.\nSkill.\nHeals Vitality. Removes the following status effects: \nScroll and Skillbook.\n skillbook is a magical item that allows its reader to learn skill, if they have at least 1 point into &lt;a href=\"Huntsman\"&gt;Huntsman&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Attributes%20and%20Abilities%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;ability&lt;/a&gt;, and use it indefinitely. In order to be able to cast the skill, character needs 1 free memory slot. Note that the book will disappear once read. The book weights 0.5 and its base value is 120 gold. Since is a starter Huntsman skill, it is available right from the start of the game. Traders selling Huntsman skillbooks will have this book for sale since the start of the game as well.\nSince is a weapon based skill and as such it does not have a scroll. It is also not possible to craft a skillbook.\nLocations.\nTraders.\nFollowing table shows all NPCs who are guaranteed to sell huntsman skillbooks, with their location and coordinates in the right column, from them. The location shown in the table (and the coordinates) are only for the initial location the NPC is in. Note that some of these may have other spell/skillbooks and goods to sell."}
{"id": "3195", "revid": "49426621", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3195", "title": "First Aid (quest)", "text": "First Aid is a &lt;a href=\"Flames%20of%20Vengeance%20quests\"&gt;side quest&lt;/a&gt; offered by &lt;a href=\"Peter\"&gt;Peter&lt;/a&gt; east of the elevator in the &lt;a href=\"Mardaneus%20Plaza\"&gt;Mardaneus Plaza&lt;/a&gt; district of &lt;a href=\"Aleroth\"&gt;Aleroth&lt;/a&gt; during the events of \"\".\nDetailed Walkthrough.\nAcquisition.\nSpeak to Peter in Mardaneus Plaza and you'll learn that he is in need of a &lt;a href=\"Healing%20Orb\"&gt;Healing Orb&lt;/a&gt; from the Source, which is more powerful than any &lt;a href=\"Herbs\"&gt;herb&lt;/a&gt;, but quite a rare commodity that is unfeasible to obtain at the moment since the &lt;a href=\"Source%20Square\"&gt;Source Square&lt;/a&gt; area of the city is off-limits. Luckily, he knows of one in the basement of the &lt;a href=\"Healers%27%20House\"&gt;Healers' House&lt;/a&gt; in the &lt;a href=\"Great%20Market\"&gt;Great Market&lt;/a&gt; district.\nObtaining the Orb.\nAt the Healers' House on the west side of the market, go downstairs and open the basement door with the password (\"honeysuckle\") that Peter provided. The Healing Orb is on a table next to the door, along with a &lt;a href=\"Books%20and%20notes%20%28Dragon%20Knight%20Saga%29\"&gt;book&lt;/a&gt; about them titled \"&lt;a href=\"A%20History%20of%20Healing%20Orbs\"&gt;A History of Healing Orbs&lt;/a&gt;\". (By entering the room you'll automatically begin a conversation with &lt;a href=\"Kelton\"&gt;Kelton&lt;/a&gt; who offers the quest &lt;a href=\"Something%20Rotten\"&gt;Something Rotten&lt;/a&gt;.)\nTake the orb and return to Peter, who offers his thanks along with a reward."}
