{"id": "17107", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=17107", "title": "Flame Dazzler Grenade", "text": " is a type of &lt;a href=\"Munitions%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;ammunition&lt;/a&gt; in \"\".\nCharacteristics.\n is a throwable grenade that deals no damage on its own but inflicts &lt;a href=\"Blinded%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Blinded Status&lt;/a&gt; (2 turns) in 4 meter radius, if the Magic Armour of affected characters reaches 0. Unlike simple &lt;a href=\"Razzle%20Dazzle%20Grenade\"&gt;Razzle Dazzle Grenade&lt;/a&gt; the also creates a fire surface at an area of impact in 2 meter radius.\nAll characters can throw this grenade. However due to the grenade dealing no damage and only inflicting status effect it is not possible to increase its effectiveness through abilities or attributes.\nSince is a grenade it is affected by &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Talents\"&gt;Ambidextrous&lt;/a&gt; talent which decreases the cost of using grenades and scrolls by 1 AP when the secondary hand is free. is also affected by &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Talents\"&gt;Slingshot&lt;/a&gt; which increases its range by 5 meters and by &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Talents\"&gt;Far Out Man&lt;/a&gt; talent which increases range by 2 meters."}
{"id": "17367", "revid": "24816040", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=17367", "title": "Flame Rune", "text": " is a type of &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Items\"&gt;magical item&lt;/a&gt; in \"\"\nCharacteristics.\n is a magical item that can be crafted and subsequently inserted into equipment with rune slots in order to grant bonuses to &lt;a href=\"Critical%20Chance\"&gt;Critical Chance&lt;/a&gt;, Fire Resistance or add additional Fire Damage . These bonuses depend on the rune size and whether it is imbued with rune frames which add additional properties. The bonuses the rune provides are, in most cases, increased with its size. The weight of the rune is 0.1 and remains unchanged through crafting or increasing its size. \nLocations.\nCreatures and NPCs.\nFollowing table shows all creatures and NPCs which have a chance to drop the item upon death. Highlighted creatures in this table have 100 % chance to drop said item. Note that creatures may drop other items as well."}
