{"id": "21423", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=21423", "title": "Flames of Vengeance skills", "text": ""}
{"id": "12416", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=12416", "title": "Flaming Crescendo", "text": " is a &lt;a href=\"Pyrokinetic%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;master pyrokinetic skill&lt;/a&gt; in \"\".\nDescription.\nSkill.\n is an offensive pyrokinetic skill that allows character to cast a powerful fiery curse at their target, making them explode in the moment of their death or when the effect expires after 1 turn. The explosion has 3 meter radius and deals very large amount of fire damage to all caught in the blast. Additionaly the explosion creates a fire surface in 3 meter radius which will inflict &lt;a href=\"Burning%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Burning&lt;/a&gt; status effect to all without Magic Armour. \nNote that even if target has Magic Armour above 0 they will still be affected by the .\nSince relies on &lt;a href=\"Pyrokinesis\"&gt;Pyrokinesis&lt;/a&gt; magic it cannot be cast if caster is affected by &lt;a href=\"Silenced%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Silenced&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Enraged%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Enraged&lt;/a&gt; status effects. skill is reflected back when the target is under &lt;a href=\"Deflective%20Barrier\"&gt;Deflective Barrier&lt;/a&gt; skill (Definitive Edition only).\nScroll and Skillbook.\n skillbook is a magical item that allows its reader to learn skill, if they have at least 3 points into &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Pyrokinetic\"&gt;Pyrokinetic&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Attributes%20and%20Abilities%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;ability&lt;/a&gt;, and use it indefinitely. In order to be able to cast the skill, character needs 1 free memory slot. Note that the book will disappear once read. The book weights 0.5 and its base value is 1400 gold. A skillbook can be crafted if a scroll is combined with a &lt;a href=\"Blank%20Fire%20Skillbook\"&gt;High Tier Blank Fire Skillbook&lt;/a&gt;. Since is a master Pyrokinetic skill, traders will start selling the skillbook once &lt;a href=\"Godwoken\"&gt;Godwoken&lt;/a&gt; reach level 16.\n scroll is a magical item that allows any character to cast skill, regardless of skill prerequisites, but only once. The only limiting element in casting this way is the amount of &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Action%20Points\"&gt;Action Points&lt;/a&gt; character has at their disposal in current turn. The scroll is craftable, weights 0.02 and has base value of 350 gold.\nThe cost of Action Points between scroll and skill themselves remains the same. Both the scroll and the skill itself are affected by other skills and talents that may provide additional bonuses.\nSkill Modifiers.\nDamage of this skill is calculated with the following formula: (Base Damage) x (1 + Elemental Bonus%) x (1 + Attribute Bonus% + Weapon Skill Bonus %) x (1 + High Ground Bonus% + Crit Bonus%) x ( 1 + Misc Bonus %)\nThe damage of this skill is affected by the following attributes of the caster:\nOut of these the most effect on the damage have level and then Pyrokinetic ability as the latter increases damage by 5 % per point. Level provides greatest boost to the damage done. Intelligence provides the lowest bonus out of the three (3 points in Intelligence are equal to 1 point of Pyrokinetic).\nWhen it comes to enemies they may resist fire damage if they have: Fire Immunity Status and high enough Fire Resistance (which lowers fire damage done).\n properties can be affected by talents, consumable items (some of which may be affected by &lt;a href=\"Five-Star%20Diner%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Five-Star Diner&lt;/a&gt; talent) and other skills. \nLocations.\nTraders.\nFollowing table shows all NPCs who are guaranteed to sell pyrokinetic spellbooks, with their location and coordinates in the right column, from them. The location shown in the table (and the coordinates) are only for the initial location the NPC is in. Note that some of these may have other spell/skillbooks and goods to sell. &lt;a href=\"Almira\"&gt;Almira&lt;/a&gt; may follow the Godwoken on &lt;a href=\"The%20Lady%20Vengeance\"&gt;Lady Vengeance&lt;/a&gt; if her demands are met."}
{"id": "17103", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=17103", "title": "Flaming Nailbomb", "text": " is a type of &lt;a href=\"Munitions%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29%23Gift%20Bag%20-%20Song%20Of%20Nature\"&gt;ammunition&lt;/a&gt; in \".\"\nCharacteristics.\n is a throwable grenade that deals physical damage and inflicts &lt;a href=\"Bleeding%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Bleeding Status&lt;/a&gt; (3 turns) in 4 meter radius, if the Physical Armour of affected characters reaches 0. Unlike simple &lt;a href=\"Nailbomb%20Grenade\"&gt;Nailbomb grenade&lt;/a&gt; the also creates a fire surface at an area of impact in 2 meter radius.\nAll characters can throw this grenade. The damage of the grenade depends on &lt;a href=\"Warfare%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Warfare&lt;/a&gt; ability and can be further increased by &lt;a href=\"Huntsman\"&gt;Huntsman&lt;/a&gt; which boosts the damage bonus provided by height difference.\nSince is a grenade it is affected by &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Talents\"&gt;Ambidextrous&lt;/a&gt; talent which decreases the cost of using grenades and scrolls by 1 AP when the secondary hand is free. is also affected by &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Talents\"&gt;Slingshot&lt;/a&gt; which increases its range by 5 meters and by &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Talents\"&gt;Far Out Man&lt;/a&gt; talent which increases range by 2 meters."}
{"id": "12393", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=12393", "title": "Flaming Skin", "text": " is a &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Pyrokinetic\"&gt;Pyrokinetic&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Polymorph\"&gt;Polymorph&lt;/a&gt; source skill in \"\".\nDescription.\nSkill.\n is a supportive mixed source skill that allows caster to enchant their very skin with fiery energies for 2 turns, thus granting them immunity to &lt;a href=\"Warm%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Warm&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Burning%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Burning&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Necrofire%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Necrofire&lt;/a&gt; status effects alongside increased Fire Resistance by 100 %. However this skill will also decrease Water Resistance by 30 %. When caster is directly damaged they will bleed fire (note that this excludes bleeding caused by &lt;a href=\"Flesh%20Sacrifice\"&gt;Flesh Sacrifice&lt;/a&gt;). \nSince this skill applies positive status effect it will always bypass armour. Note that this skill may provide protection against lava surfaces rendering them non-lethal but only if characters Fire Resistance is above + 115 %. If Fire Resistance becomes lower than 115 % while the skill is active the character will begin to take large amount of fire damage. \nSince relies on &lt;a href=\"Pyrokinesis\"&gt;Pyrokinesis&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Metamorphosis\"&gt;Metamorphosis&lt;/a&gt; magic it cannot be cast if caster is affected by &lt;a href=\"Silenced%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Silenced&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Enraged%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Enraged&lt;/a&gt; status effects.\nScroll and Skillbook.\n skillbook is a magical item that allows its reader to learn skill, if they have at least 2 points into both &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Pyrokinetic\"&gt;Pyrokinetic&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Polymorph\"&gt;Polymorph&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Attributes%20and%20Abilities%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;abilities&lt;/a&gt;, and use it indefinitely. In order to be able to cast the skill, character needs 2 free memory slots. Note that the book will disappear once read. The book weights 0.5 and its base value is 500 gold. A skillbook can be crafted by combining any &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Pyrokinetic\"&gt;Pyrokinetic&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Polymorph\"&gt;Polymorph&lt;/a&gt; skillbooks out of which atleast one must be a source skillbook. Since is a mixed source skill, traders do not have the skillbook for sale.\n is one of the few magic-based skills in the game that does not have a scroll.\nSkill Modifiers.\n is a supportive skill that provides clear set bonuses. As such these bonuses by themselves cannot be increased, however they can stack with other items, skills or talents that provide them.\nSince the AP cost to cast this skill is always 1 AP it cannot be lowered by any means.\nThe only way to improve this skill is to increase its range through skills or talents.\nLocations.\nTraders.\nThis skill cannot be bought or stolen from NPCs in the game."}
{"id": "12415", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=12415", "title": "Flaming Tongues", "text": " is an &lt;a href=\"Pyrokinetic%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;adept pyrokinetic skill&lt;/a&gt; in \"\".\nDescription.\nSkill.\n is a supportive pyrokinetic skill that grants its caster a fiery aura that will cause fire damage to all enemies that get into 3 meter radius from the caster. Alongside the damage done a small fire surface, that lasts 1 turn, will be created under the enemy and deal additional damage alongside the main damage caused by the skill. Since this skill applies positive status effect it will always bypass armour of the caster. Note that enemies will be attacked only once when they get into the range of the aura. Forcibly moving an enemy into the range of the skill will trigger it. Enemies that will leave and return into the range of the aura will be damaged once again. \nSince relies on &lt;a href=\"Pyrokinesis\"&gt;Pyrokinesis&lt;/a&gt; magic it cannot be cast if caster is affected by &lt;a href=\"Silenced%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Silenced&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Enraged%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Enraged&lt;/a&gt; status effects. Damage done by skill is NOT reflected back when the enemy that approaches the caster is under the effect of &lt;a href=\"Deflective%20Barrier\"&gt;Deflective Barrier&lt;/a&gt; skill (Definitive Edition only).\nScroll and Skillbook.\n skillbook is a magical item that allows its reader to learn skill, if they have at least 2 points into &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Pyrokinetic\"&gt;Pyrokinetic&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Attributes%20and%20Abilities%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;ability&lt;/a&gt;, and use it indefinitely. In order to be able to cast the skill, character needs 1 free memory slot. Note that the book will disappear once read. The book weights 0.5 and its base value is 500 gold. A skillbook can be crafted if a scroll is combined with a &lt;a href=\"Blank%20Fire%20Skillbook\"&gt;Blank Fire Skillbook&lt;/a&gt;. Since is an adept Pyrokinetic skill, traders will start selling the skillbook once &lt;a href=\"Godwoken\"&gt;Godwoken&lt;/a&gt; reach level 9.\n scroll is a magical item that allows any character to cast skill, regardless of skill prerequisites, but only once. The only limiting element in casting this way is the amount of &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Action%20Points\"&gt;Action Points (AP)&lt;/a&gt; character has at their disposal in current turn. The scroll is craftable, weights 0.02 and has base value of 260 gold.\nThe cost of Action Points between scroll and skill themselves remains the same. Both the scroll and the skill itself are affected by other skills, attributes and talents that may provide additional bonuses.\nSkill Modifiers.\nDamage of this skill is calculated with the following formula: (Base Damage) x (1 + Elemental Bonus%) x (1 + Attribute Bonus% + Weapon Skill Bonus %) x (1 + High Ground Bonus% + Crit Bonus%) x ( 1 + Misc Bonus %)\nThe damage of this skill is affected by the following attributes of the caster:\nOut of these the most effect on the damage have Level and then Pyrokinetic ability as the latter increases damage by 5 % per point. Level provides greatest boost to the damage done. Intelligence provides the lowest bonus out of the three (3 points in Intelligence are equal to 1 point of Pyrokinetic).\nWhen it comes to enemies they may resist fire damage if they have: Fire Immunity Status and high enough Fire Resistance (which lowers fire damage done).\n properties can be affected by talents, consumable items (some of which may be affected by &lt;a href=\"Five-Star%20Diner%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Five-Star Diner&lt;/a&gt; talent) and other skills.\nLocations.\nTraders.\nFollowing table shows all NPCs who are guaranteed to sell pyrokinetic spellbooks, with their location and coordinates in the right column, from them. The location shown in the table (and the coordinates) are only for the initial location the NPC is in. Note that some of these may have other spell/skillbooks and goods to sell. &lt;a href=\"Almira\"&gt;Almira&lt;/a&gt; may follow the Godwoken on &lt;a href=\"The%20Lady%20Vengeance\"&gt;Lady Vengeance&lt;/a&gt; if her demands are met."}
