{"id": "12398", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=12398", "title": "Flay Skin", "text": "Flay Skin is a &lt;a href=\"Polymorph%20%28Skill%20Class%29\"&gt;master Polymorph&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Skills\"&gt;skill&lt;/a&gt; in \"\".\nDescription.\nSkill.\nDestroy Magic Armour on target character. Set status that halves resistances.\nDamage to Magic Armour is scaled on casters level and strength.\nSince relies on &lt;a href=\"Metamorphosis\"&gt;Metamorphosis&lt;/a&gt; magic it cannot be cast if caster is affected by &lt;a href=\"Silenced%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Silenced&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Enraged%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Enraged&lt;/a&gt; status effects.\nScroll and Skillbook.\n skillbook is a magical item that allows its reader to learn skill, if they have at least 3 points into &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Polymorph\"&gt;Polymorph&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Attributes%20and%20Abilities%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;ability&lt;/a&gt;, and use it indefinitely. In order to be able to cast the skill, character needs 1 free memory slot. Note that the book will disappear once read. The book weights 0.5 and its base value is 1400 gold. A skillbook can be crafted if a scroll is combined with a &lt;a href=\"Blank%20Polymorph%20Skillbook\"&gt;High Tier Blank Polymorph Skillbook&lt;/a&gt;. Since is a master Polymorph skill, traders will start selling the skillbook once &lt;a href=\"Godwoken\"&gt;Godwoken&lt;/a&gt; reach level 16.\n scroll is a magical item that allows any character to cast skill, regardless of skill prerequisites, but only once. The only limiting element in casting this way is the amount of &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Action%20Points\"&gt;Action Points&lt;/a&gt; character has at their disposal in current turn. The scroll is not craftable, weights 0.02 and has base value of 350 gold.\nThe cost of Action Points between scroll and skill themselves varies. The cost to cast as a skill is 2 Action Points, but the cost to cast as a scroll is 3 Action Points.\nBoth the scroll and the skill itself are affected by other skills and talents that may provide additional bonuses.\nLocations.\nTraders.\nFollowing table shows all NPCs who are guaranteed to sell Polymorph spellbooks, with their location and coordinates in the right column, from them. The location shown in the table (and the coordinates) are only for the initial location the NPC is in. Note that some of these may have other spell/skillbooks and goods to sell. "}
