{"id": "7248", "revid": "84805", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=7248", "title": "For Whom the Troll Tolls", "text": " is a in \"\". This quest is obtained when you come across a bridge troll arguing with some immaculates just southeast of the &lt;a href=\"Phantom%20Forest\"&gt;Phantom Forest&lt;/a&gt; entrance.\nNotes.\nRight behind the bridge there's an offering scale with a sign (inscription: \"The hen who shares her feed receives a greater second helping.\") Placing 501+ gold on the scale will produce a treasure chest. The quality of the items inside doesn't seem to change based on the quantity of good placed upon the scale."}
{"id": "2100", "revid": "27868532", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=2100", "title": "For a Pound of Flesh", "text": " is a &lt;a href=\"Ego%20Draconis%20quests\"&gt;side quest&lt;/a&gt; given by &lt;a href=\"Locke\"&gt;Locke&lt;/a&gt; in \"\". This quest can be completed only one way, but has a side option that will fail the quest if you choose to take it.\nDetailed walkthrough.\nAfter talking to &lt;a href=\"Keane\"&gt;Keane&lt;/a&gt; he states that &lt;a href=\"Richard\"&gt;Richard&lt;/a&gt; already collected the debt for &lt;a href=\"Locke\"&gt;Locke&lt;/a&gt;. You can verify this by going to &lt;a href=\"Richard\"&gt;Richard&lt;/a&gt; and asking him about it. &lt;a href=\"Richard\"&gt;Richard&lt;/a&gt; brags about how he did the quest previously. Although, this does not seem to change the quest's story line (so far). But this does prove that &lt;a href=\"Keane\"&gt;Keane&lt;/a&gt; is innocent, and that &lt;a href=\"Locke\"&gt;Locke&lt;/a&gt; is actually harassing &lt;a href=\"Keane\"&gt;Keane&lt;/a&gt;.\nIt may be noted that since you have the option to keep Locke's Wallet for yourself, Richard may have done the same, making both Keane and Locke innocent.\nRewards.\nYou can use mind reading on &lt;a href=\"Locke%27s%20Cart\"&gt;Locke's Cart&lt;/a&gt; to receive the password should you side with Locke. This way you get rewards #1 and #2."}
