{"id": "20240", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=20240", "title": "Fortified (Status)", "text": "Fortified is a &lt;a href=\"Status%20Effects%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;status effect&lt;/a&gt; in \"\".\nDescription.\nFortified is a positive environmental status effect which restores Physical armour.\nCause.\nFortified can be caused by coming into contact with \"blessed oil surface\" which is created by casting &lt;a href=\"Bless%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Bless&lt;/a&gt; upon regular \"oil surface\". Out of all spells only &lt;a href=\"Fortify\"&gt;Fortify&lt;/a&gt; directly sets Fortified status.\nStatus negation.\nThere are no ways to cancel out the Fortified effect directly. The only way to counter its Physical armour boosting effect is to deal enough physical damage. "}
{"id": "5555", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5555", "title": "Fortify", "text": "Fortify is a &lt;a href=\"Geomancer%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;starter Geomancer&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Skills\"&gt;skill&lt;/a&gt; in \"\".\nCharacteristics.\nSkill.\n is a supportive geomancer skill that allows caster to conjure a defensive barrier around their target, which provides &lt;a href=\"Fortified%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Fortified&lt;/a&gt; status effect that restores Physical Armour each turn for 3 turns but also increases the maximum amount of it. This status also prevents character from being forcefully teleported by any means. &lt;a href=\"Fortified%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Fortified&lt;/a&gt; status effect may be additionally granted by walking over blessed oil surfaces. Since this skill applies positive status effect it will always bypass armour. \nAlongside these effects the will also remove &lt;a href=\"Poisoned%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Poisoned&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Bleeding%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Bleeding&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Burning%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Burning&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Acid%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Acid&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Decaying%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Decaying&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Diseased%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Diseased&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Infected%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Infected&lt;/a&gt; status effects. \nSince relies on &lt;a href=\"Geomancy\"&gt;Geomancy&lt;/a&gt; magic it cannot be cast if caster is affected by &lt;a href=\"Silenced%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Silenced&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Enraged%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Enraged&lt;/a&gt; status effects.\nScroll and Skillbook.\n skillbook is a magical item that allows its reader to learn skill, if they have at least 1 point into &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Geomancer\"&gt;Geomancer&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Attributes%20and%20Abilities%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;ability&lt;/a&gt;, and use it indefinitely. In order to be able to cast the skill, character needs 1 free memory slot. Note that the book will disappear once read. The book weights 0.5 and its base value is 120 gold. A skillbook can be crafted if a scroll is combined with a &lt;a href=\"Blank%20Earth%20Skillbook\"&gt;Blank Earth Skillbook&lt;/a&gt;. Since is a starter Geomancer skill, it is available right from the start of the game. Traders selling Geomancer skillbooks will have this book for sale since the start of the game as well. \n scroll is a magical item that allows any character to cast skill, regardless of skill prerequisites, but only once. The only limiting element in casting this way is the amount of &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Action%20Points\"&gt;Action Points (AP)&lt;/a&gt; character has at their disposal in current turn. The scroll is craftable, weights 0.02 and has base value of 50 gold.\nThe cost of Action Points between scroll and skill themselves remains the same. Both the scroll and the skill itself are affected by other skills and talents that may provide additional bonuses.\nSkill Modifiers.\n is a supportive skill whose effects depend on the following characteristics of the caster:\nOutside of the Level of the caster only their &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Geomancer\"&gt;Geomancer&lt;/a&gt; ability can influence the amount of Physical Armour gained by . \n properties can be affected by talents and other skills only. \nLocations.\nTraders.\nFollowing table shows all NPCs who are guaranteed to sell Geomancer spellbooks, with their location and coordinates in the right column, from them. The location shown in the table (and the coordinates) are only for the initial location the NPC is in. Note that some of these may have other spell/skillbooks and goods to sell. Out of these only &lt;a href=\"Gareth%20Pryce\"&gt;Gareth&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Almira\"&gt;Almira&lt;/a&gt; may follow the &lt;a href=\"Godwoken\"&gt;Godwoken&lt;/a&gt; throughout the game on &lt;a href=\"the%20Lady%20Vengeance\"&gt;the Lady Vengeance&lt;/a&gt;, provided their demands are met."}
