{"id": "2436", "revid": "27868532", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=2436", "title": "From Soup to Nuts", "text": " is a &lt;a href=\"Ego%20Draconis%20quests\"&gt;side quest&lt;/a&gt; accepted from &lt;a href=\"Hermit\"&gt;Hermit&lt;/a&gt; on &lt;a href=\"Sentinel%20Island\"&gt;Sentinel Island&lt;/a&gt;. He asks you to find and bring him a &lt;a href=\"wyvern%20mother%20egg\"&gt;wyvern mother egg&lt;/a&gt; to make soup with.\nDetailed Walkthrough.\nWhen you first exit the &lt;a href=\"Maxos%20Temple\"&gt;Maxos Temple&lt;/a&gt; unto Sentinel Island continue straight ahead toward the rocks directly in front of the temple. The Crazy Hermit lives in a cave inside these rocks. \nWhen you first meet him, he tries to cast ridiculous spells on you that fail to work and runs to the back of the cave after realizing they aren't working. If you follow him and then talk to him, you can receive the quest and also trade with him.\nAfter accepting the quest you can go retrieve the wyvern egg from wyvern spire north of Vacca's cave. If you can't make it to the nest, try and complete the quest &lt;a href=\"Ghostbuster\"&gt;Ghostbuster&lt;/a&gt; where Vacca gives you the wyvern salve which makes wyverns non hostile."}
{"id": "12136", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=12136", "title": "Frost Grenade", "text": " is a type of &lt;a href=\"Munitions%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;grenade&lt;/a&gt; in ' and '.\nDescription.\nOriginal Sin.\nCauses 26-39 water damage and has a 50% chance to set frozen status for 2 turns in a 4m radius.\nOriginal Sin II.\n is a throwable grenade that water damage and inflicts &lt;a href=\"Chilled%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Chilled Status&lt;/a&gt; if the Magic Armour of affected characters reaches 0. Additionally this grenade creates an ice surface at the area of impact (2 meters).\nAll characters can throw this grenade. The damage of the grenade depends on &lt;a href=\"Hydrosophist%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Hydrosophist&lt;/a&gt; ability and can be further increased by &lt;a href=\"Huntsman\"&gt;Huntsman&lt;/a&gt; which boosts the damage bonus provided by height difference.\nSince is a grenade it is affected by &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Talents\"&gt;Ambidextrous&lt;/a&gt; talent which decreases the cost of using grenades and scrolls by 1 AP when the secondary hand is free. is also affected by &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Talents\"&gt;Slingshot&lt;/a&gt; which increases its range by 5 meters and by &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Talents\"&gt;Far Out Man&lt;/a&gt; talent which increases range by 2 meters.\nUsage.\nFollowing table shows all items for which this item is used for."}
{"id": "17371", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=17371", "title": "Frost Rune", "text": " is a type of &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%202%20Items\"&gt;magical item&lt;/a&gt; in \"\"\nCharacteristics.\n is a magical item that can be crafted and subsequently inserted into equipment with rune slots in order to grant bonuses to &lt;a href=\"Movement\"&gt;Movement&lt;/a&gt;, Water Resistance or add additional Water Damage. These bonuses depend on the rune size and whether it is imbued with rune frames which add additional properties. The bonuses the rune provides are, in most cases, increased with its size. The weight of the rune is 0.1 and remains unchanged through crafting or increasing its size. "}
