{"id": "20215", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=20215", "title": "Frozen (Status)", "text": "Frozen is a &lt;a href=\"Status%20Effects%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;status effect&lt;/a&gt; in \"\". \nDescription.\nFrozen is a negative environmental status effect that incapacitates affected character, rendering them unable to act. Frozen also lowers Dodging by 100 % and Water resistance by 20 %, however it increases Fire Resistance by 10 %. Frozen also grants immunity to following status effects:\nCause.\nFrozen is a water based status effect which can be caused by many ways and is applied only if Magic armour is at 0. First and most common is by combining &lt;a href=\"Wet%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Wet&lt;/a&gt; status with &lt;a href=\"Chilled%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Chilled&lt;/a&gt; or by applying Chilled status effect twice. Frozen can also be inflicted by stepping unto \"cursed ice surface\". Note that there are few places on &lt;a href=\"Rivellon\"&gt;Rivellon&lt;/a&gt; where environment itself may freeze characters such as &lt;a href=\"Arx%20Harbour\"&gt;Arx Harbour&lt;/a&gt; cellar flooded with freezing water regardless of Magic armour being above 0.\nIn combat Frozen can be inflicted by casting certain &lt;a href=\"Hydrosophist%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Hydrosophist&lt;/a&gt; spells or using certain items. \nNotable NPCs.\nFollowing NPCs are characters which may utilise spells or items that will afflict their enemies with Frozen status.\nTreatment.\nFrozen is a status that is based on water and damages Magic armour, therefore it can be negated via fire based tools and spells or resisted through increasing Magic armour. On &lt;a href=\"Rivellon\"&gt;Rivellon&lt;/a&gt; Frozen status will be negated via fire surface or fire cloud. \nMagic armour restoration.\nMagic armour can be increased via blessed ice surface, items or through spells. Notable status effect that is associated with increased Magic armour is &lt;a href=\"Magic%20Shell%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Magic shell&lt;/a&gt;.\nStatus negation.\nAs mentioned above the easiest way to utterly remove Frozen is through fire based status effects such as Burning. Other status effect that directly removes Frozen is &lt;a href=\"Blessed%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Blessed&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Permafrost%20%28Status%29\"&gt;Permafrost&lt;/a&gt; which turns negative properties of Frozen into positive ones but still renders character incapacitated."}
{"id": "18208", "revid": "27868532", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=18208", "title": "Fruit", "text": "The is a &lt;a href=\"Divine%20Divinity%20consumables\"&gt;consumable&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Divine%20Divinity\"&gt;Divine Divinity&lt;/a&gt;\".\nCharacteristics.\nA small assortment of various fruits, which when consumed provide a boost to &lt;a href=\"Intelligence%23Divine%20Divinity\"&gt;Intelligence&lt;/a&gt;.\nIf combined with a bucket, basket, bowl or crate, the result is an &lt;a href=\"Apple%20%28Divine%20Divinity%29\"&gt;apple&lt;/a&gt; in the same container.\nPre-made fruit baskets boost &lt;a href=\"Intelligence%23Divine%20Divinity\"&gt;Intelligence&lt;/a&gt; by 1."}
