{"id": "14911", "revid": "49426621", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=14911", "title": "Gareth (Divine Divinity)", "text": " is a &lt;a href=\"Humans\"&gt;human&lt;/a&gt; soldier in the service of the &lt;a href=\"Ducal%20Army\"&gt;Ducal Army&lt;/a&gt; at the &lt;a href=\"barracks\"&gt;barracks&lt;/a&gt; in 1218 AD.\nBackground.\nAlthough not on the front lines, but remaining at the barracks, Gareth is unhappy with being in the army and wants to leave; however; he signed a 25 year contract. He seeks a way out to be with his lover, &lt;a href=\"Isolde\"&gt;Isolde&lt;/a&gt;, via a feign death potion. Once he has the potion, he will move to &lt;a href=\"the%20Farmlands\"&gt;the Farmlands&lt;/a&gt; and abandon his military attire."}
{"id": "10505", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=10505", "title": "Gareth Pryce", "text": "Gareth is the leader of the &lt;a href=\"Seekers\"&gt;Seekers&lt;/a&gt; who sought to free &lt;a href=\"Verdas\"&gt;Verdas&lt;/a&gt; from &lt;a href=\"Fort%20Joy\"&gt;Fort Joy&lt;/a&gt; in 1242 AD.\nBackground.\nGareth is a human who was born and raised in the farmlands on &lt;a href=\"Reaper%27s%20Coast\"&gt;Reaper's Coast&lt;/a&gt; and is the leader of the Seeker contingent on Fort Joy. Initially making camp on the hillside south of the north east harbour, &lt;a href=\"the%20Magisters\"&gt;the Magisters&lt;/a&gt; launched an assault on the contingent. Moving the escapees and wounded who were not captured to &lt;a href=\"Sanctuary%20of%20Amadia\"&gt;Sanctuary of Amadia&lt;/a&gt;, Gareth then sought out to investigate the Magister activity at the old &lt;a href=\"Fort%20Joy%20armoury\"&gt;Fort Joy armoury&lt;/a&gt;, where again he alone was attacked by the Magisters within.\nUpon being rescued by the Godwoken and discovering Verdas' condition, he worked with them to escape &lt;a href=\"Reapers%27%20Eye\"&gt;Reapers' Eye&lt;/a&gt;, by the stealing the &lt;a href=\"Lady%20Vengeance\"&gt;Lady Vengeance&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Dallis\"&gt;Dallis&lt;/a&gt;' personal ship and sailing out to Reapers' Coast.\nUpon arrival he returned home to discover his parents murdered by &lt;a href=\"Silent%20Monk\"&gt;Silent Monk&lt;/a&gt;s, two of which were locked inside his home. After burying his parents he continued with the Godwoken and &lt;a href=\"Malady\"&gt;Malady&lt;/a&gt; to the &lt;a href=\"Nameless%20Isle\"&gt;Nameless Isle&lt;/a&gt; and further onwards to &lt;a href=\"Arx\"&gt;Arx&lt;/a&gt;."}
