{"id": "3414", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3414", "title": "Ghost", "text": "A ghost is a spiritual manifestation of a long-past soul that has not been able to fully pass on through the &lt;a href=\"Hall%20of%20Echoes\"&gt;Hall of Echoes&lt;/a&gt;; as they have one or more tethering links that restrain it to the world of the living. Due to their forced stay in the mortal realm, many ghosts are hateful toward anything that still lives, though others seek out the living to help them complete their tasks and move on to the next life.\nMost mortals are incapable of seeing Ghosts, though may sometimes feel their presence or even hear them. There are magical means of allowing a mortal to see Ghosts clearly, such as the &lt;a href=\"Sourcery%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;Sourcery&lt;/a&gt; skill &lt;a href=\"Spirit%20Vision\"&gt;Spirit Vision&lt;/a&gt;, or the &lt;a href=\"Dragon%20Slayers\"&gt;Dragon Slayer&lt;/a&gt; ritual that involves an initiate absorbing &lt;a href=\"Dragons\"&gt;Dragon&lt;/a&gt; memories which, alongside other effects, allows the newborn Slayer to see Ghosts.\nPhysiology.\nGhosts can appear as different forms (differing depending on the game) though are always incorporeal and transparent.\nIn \"&lt;a href=\"Divine%20Divinity\"&gt;Divine Divinity&lt;/a&gt;\", &lt;a href=\"Ghost%20%28Divine%20Divinity%29\"&gt;Ghosts&lt;/a&gt; appear as orbs of light until they enter combat, where they shift into a floating, vaguely humanoid form that lacks a lower body.\nIn \", most Ghosts appear as a pale upper bodies. Their faces are contorted in agony and they possess black hair that floats as if it were submerged underwater. A head hangs from where their torso ends, presumably the same head they once bore in life, though this is not reflected in-game. Most Ghosts float, though some crawl across the ground at alarming speeds.\nin \" ghosts or spirits appear like perfect copies of their living counterparts. They are distinguished from the living by the spectral green color and transparent body. Unlike in other games they are incapable of causing direct harm to the libing however they may haunt them and cause them all manner of unpleasantries such as preventing wounds from healing or making them loose their sanity. If spirits are deprived of their Source they will cease to exist."}
{"id": "17823", "revid": "49426621", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=17823", "title": "Ghost (Divine Divinity)", "text": " is a &lt;a href=\"Divine%20Divinity%20creatures\"&gt;creature&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Divine%20Divinity\"&gt;Divine Divinity&lt;/a&gt;\".\nCharacteristics.\nWhen not in combat, they appear as floating spheres, which can be seen even on the minimap. Upon attacking, they appear as a more humanoid form, and attack with melee attacks. They are immune to poison and spiritual damage."}
{"id": "2437", "revid": "94713", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=2437", "title": "Ghostbuster", "text": " is a &lt;a href=\"Ego%20Draconis%20quests\"&gt;side quest&lt;/a&gt; given by &lt;a href=\"Vacca\"&gt;Vacca&lt;/a&gt; on &lt;a href=\"Sentinel%20Island\"&gt;Sentinel Island&lt;/a&gt; in \"\".\nDetailed Walkthrough.\nGhosbuster is a side quest issued by Vacca, who will ask &lt;a href=\"The%20Dragon%20Knight\"&gt;the Knight&lt;/a&gt; to clear the ghosts out from his cave which is down a trap-door right next to him.\nAfter you enter the cave through the trap-door next to Vacca, you will be met with eight \"Ghost Crawler Warriors\" (level 16), two of which will attack you immediately upon entering the cave. They have no offensive or defensive skills, save for their basic attacks. Once all enemies are dead a message will appear on screen saying that the cave is clear.\nAfter all enemies are dead you can return to Vacca for a reward. \nHowever, before completing the quest, you may take &lt;a href=\"Vacca%27s%20Gem\"&gt;Vacca's Gem&lt;/a&gt; which sits on a pillow in middle of the cave. However the gem has to be sold before speaking to Vacca, otherwise he will take it from you. If you refuse to return the gem, Vacca will become hostile."}
