{"id": "4432", "revid": "27868532", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4432", "title": "Goblin heart", "text": " is a quest item in \"\".\nDescription.\nThe heart of a &lt;a href=\"Goblin\"&gt;Goblin&lt;/a&gt; which is needed for the &lt;a href=\"Hearttaker\"&gt;Hearttaker&lt;/a&gt; quest. They are worth 50 gold each. If &lt;a href=\"Richard\"&gt;Richard&lt;/a&gt; has been &lt;a href=\"mindread\"&gt;mindread&lt;/a&gt; and confronted through dialogue, they are worth 150 gold and 150 experience each.\nLocations.\nDrop by &lt;a href=\"goblins\"&gt;goblins&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Broken%20Valley\"&gt;Broken Valley&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "4424", "revid": "49426621", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4424", "title": "Goblins", "text": "Goblins are one of the lesser sentient &lt;a href=\"race\"&gt;race&lt;/a&gt;s of &lt;a href=\"Rivellon\"&gt;Rivellon&lt;/a&gt;. Like the seven sentient races, they have also mastered magic. They also have an innate attraction to shiny objects.\nPhysiology.\nGoblins come in a variety of shapes and sizes.\nThe most common variety of Goblin is short and squat, they possess pointed ears, a single glowing eye and lack a mouth. The top of their heads curve back and taper to a point, and their upper bodies are marked with glowing, vein-like lines.\nAnother variant is a winged Goblin. Seen most commonly in the &lt;a href=\"Red%20Hammer%20Tribe\"&gt;Red Hammer Tribe&lt;/a&gt;, these Goblins are much larger than average Goblins, with certain individuals such as the Red Hammer Tribe's leader &lt;a href=\"Svadilfari\"&gt;Svadilfari&lt;/a&gt; towering over humans. As the name suggests, winged Goblins possess two large wings that give them the ability to fly.\nThe last variant is by far the furthest removed from the form of a common Goblin is the &lt;a href=\"Beholders\"&gt;Goblin Beholder&lt;/a&gt;, though whether they are truly Goblins or originate from elsewhere is unknown. Goblin Beholders take the form of glowing orbs that hover over the ground. Beholders are typically orange, though alternate colors and patterns have been observed on certain Beholders such as &lt;a href=\"Alutiiq\"&gt;Alutiiq&lt;/a&gt;.\nCulture.\nTribal and territorial, goblins are a diverse race, from trading nomads who barter for skins, &lt;a href=\"troll\"&gt;troll&lt;/a&gt; teeth, colored pebbles, and pieces of wood to carve a totem to warrior bands, such as the &lt;a href=\"Red%20Hammer%20Tribe\"&gt;Red Hammer Tribe&lt;/a&gt;. \nThe totems found within their camps are revered as avatars of their gods and the word of the totem is sacrosanct. The living totems within their tribes chronicle the rich history of the tribe. Although they do have an intricate written script, it is considered sacrilegious to use this outside the inner walls of tombs, where the deeds of their dead are written.\nEven within their kind, there are those that find their way of life uncivilised."}
{"id": "13934", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=13934", "title": "God King", "text": "The God King is an ancient and immortal being who leads the &lt;a href=\"voidwoken\"&gt;voidwoken&lt;/a&gt;, former &lt;a href=\"eternals\"&gt;eternals&lt;/a&gt; who were tainted by the void and the &lt;a href=\"The%20Sworn\"&gt;Sworn&lt;/a&gt;. He sought to avenge the 'Original Sin' by punishing &lt;a href=\"the%20Seven%20Gods\"&gt;the Seven Gods&lt;/a&gt; for banishing his people into the &lt;a href=\"Void\"&gt;Void&lt;/a&gt;, while also trying to return his people back to &lt;a href=\"Rivellon\"&gt;Rivellon&lt;/a&gt;. \nBackground.\nAeons before the mortal races walked Rivellon, the God King was sovereign of the eternals. Serving under him were the seven lords who operated as 'local barons.' However, when &lt;a href=\"Fane\"&gt;Fane&lt;/a&gt; discovered the &lt;a href=\"Veil\"&gt;Veil&lt;/a&gt; and informed the lords, they sealed the God King and the rest of the eternals in the void. \nIn 1233 AD &lt;a href=\"Lucian\"&gt;Lucian&lt;/a&gt; with his council had decided to use a deathfog bomb in order to defeat a &lt;a href=\"Black%20Ring\"&gt;Black Ring&lt;/a&gt; army but since &lt;a href=\"Alexandar\"&gt;Alexandar&lt;/a&gt; released the deathfog before &lt;a href=\"elves\"&gt;elves&lt;/a&gt; had a chance to pass through the Rift it resulted in their decimation as well as the enemy army. Due to elven population being decimated &lt;a href=\"The%20Seven%20Gods\"&gt;the Seventh God&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Tir-Cendelius\"&gt;Tir-Cendelius&lt;/a&gt; was weakened and was not able to keep the Veil sealed.\nOnce the veil had an opening, the voidwoken were able to flow back through the veil to Rivellon. The God King used this opening to spread his influence, primarily by gaining the allegiance of the &lt;a href=\"Black%20Ring\"&gt;Black Ring&lt;/a&gt; and offering various individuals his favour if they swore to him at the cost of their mortal lives.\nIn 1242 AD he and his Voidwoken were once and for all trapped within the Void as Lucian, &lt;a href=\"Dallis\"&gt;Dallis the Hammer&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Godwoken\"&gt;Godwoken&lt;/a&gt; seal the Veil with the world's combined &lt;a href=\"Source\"&gt;Source&lt;/a&gt;.\nAppearance.\nHe is only mentioned and spoken to in \"\". The encounters with him are in &lt;a href=\"Driftwood%20Fields\"&gt;Driftwood Fields&lt;/a&gt; where he speaks through a scarecrow and &lt;a href=\"Linder%20Kemm\"&gt;Lord Kemm&lt;/a&gt;'s secret shrine (in &lt;a href=\"Arx\"&gt;Arx&lt;/a&gt;).\nHe makes an appearance in ."}
{"id": "17551", "revid": "27868532", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=17551", "title": "Godbox", "text": ""}
{"id": "15522", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=15522", "title": "Godwoken", "text": "The Godwoken are champions of the &lt;a href=\"Seven%20Gods\"&gt;Seven Gods&lt;/a&gt; who have been appointed to ascend to Divinity. \nBackground.\n&lt;a href=\"Sourcerer\"&gt;Sourcerer&lt;/a&gt;s by nature, Godwoken have an innate connection to &lt;a href=\"Source\"&gt;Source&lt;/a&gt;, capable already of wielding its power. They were appointed out of necessity by each god to attain divine power for their &lt;a href=\"race\"&gt;race&lt;/a&gt; and aid in the sealing of the veil between &lt;a href=\"Rivellon\"&gt;Rivellon&lt;/a&gt; and the &lt;a href=\"Void\"&gt;Void&lt;/a&gt;. As seen on the example of &lt;a href=\"Verdas\"&gt;Verdas&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Sebille%20Kaleran\"&gt;Sebille&lt;/a&gt;, as well as &lt;a href=\"Lohse\"&gt;Lohse&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Ifan%20ben-Mezd\"&gt;Ifan&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Karon\"&gt;Karon&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Alexandar\"&gt;Alexandar&lt;/a&gt; one god can have multiple chosen, albeit they can fall out of grace and be abandoned by their deity.\nThe issues with previously established lore.\nIn &lt;a href=\"Divine%20Divinity\"&gt;Divine Divinity&lt;/a&gt;, the god's chosen are referred to as the &lt;a href=\"Marked%20One\"&gt;Marked One&lt;/a&gt;s. However, there are few key differences between them, and the Godwoken concepts. In the case of the Marked Ones, they were not appointed by an individual god to ascend, but rather through a decision of an unnamed divine being, that is sacrificed in the game's intro. What's more, Marked One's ascension required a ritual self-sacrifice performed by the entire &lt;a href=\"Council%20of%20Seven\"&gt;Council of Seven&lt;/a&gt;.\nCranley Hubwert's origin of the Godwoken.\nAccording to Abridged History of Rivellon, the Godwoken are the descendants of mortal heroes who helped to repel the Void in the first Chaos war. Cranley Huwbert refers to Lucian as Godwoken explicitly in his Abridged History of Rivellon. \nAfter the Divine's alleged death, the order of &lt;a href=\"Seekers%20%28Divine%20Order%29\"&gt;Seekers&lt;/a&gt; have been established to find and guide the Godwoken to ascension, but they were disbanded after an event known as the Besan incident. \nIn the light of &lt;a href=\"Lucian\"&gt;Lucian&lt;/a&gt;'s machinations to close the Void, all potential successors to Divinity were sought out and killed on the behalf of the &lt;a href=\"Divine%20Order\"&gt;Divine Order&lt;/a&gt;, who also hired &lt;a href=\"The%20Lone%20Wolves\"&gt;Lone Wolves&lt;/a&gt; to eradicate all Godwoken.\nSeveral Godwoken were killed prior to 1242 AD, but the gods would merely find a or already have a replacement champion when their current one became indisposed. As of 1242 AD there were 6 such champions who escaped &lt;a href=\"Fort%20Joy\"&gt;Fort Joy&lt;/a&gt;, some tales speak of an individualistic escape and others of a unified one.\nThe Godwoken that fled the Joy with the help of the disgraced Seekers still following their principles attained further power and insight into their own potential and role with the help of Seeker's leader, &lt;a href=\"Meistr%20Siva\"&gt;Meistr Siva&lt;/a&gt;, who shared the knowledge of the Godwoken ritual with them. As it stands, a Godwoken must obtain the skills of &lt;a href=\"Spirit%20Vision\"&gt;Spirit Vision&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Source%20Vampirism\"&gt;Source Vampirism&lt;/a&gt; to proceed with the ascension.\nThe gods turned on their chosen, after the latter failed to ascend at the Well of Ascension due to Dallis' intervence. At least one of the Seven was killed in the fight that followed. The Godwoken status of the surviving chosen is unknown after this happened. It is also unknown whether any new Godwoken arises after that point."}
{"id": "11187", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=11187", "title": "Goemoe", "text": "Goemoe is a &lt;a href=\"lizard\"&gt;lizard&lt;/a&gt; healer living in &lt;a href=\"Aleroth\"&gt;Aleroth&lt;/a&gt; in 1218 AD.\nBackground.\nGoemoe is an outcast lizard who is living in &lt;a href=\"Aleroth\"&gt;Aleroth&lt;/a&gt;. He is versed in the arts of healing. He has a patient, &lt;a href=\"Simon\"&gt;Simon&lt;/a&gt;, in his care who requires treatment using the power of the &lt;a href=\"Source\"&gt;Source&lt;/a&gt;, but is unable to do so as the \"&lt;a href=\"Source\"&gt;Source&lt;/a&gt; has been tainted by evil.\"\nGoemoe also has a &lt;a href=\"healing%20shrine\"&gt;healing shrine&lt;/a&gt;, which only holds a single &lt;a href=\"healing%20gem\"&gt;healing gem&lt;/a&gt; which could be used to treat Simon. However, doing so would be against his vows as &lt;a href=\"Otho%20Rignaforoixx\"&gt;Otho&lt;/a&gt; also has a patient who requires the same treatment, preventing the healers from choosing one life over another. When asked if &lt;a href=\"Lucian\"&gt;Lucian&lt;/a&gt; can use the power of the healing shrine, he tells him to \"ask it yourself\".\nFollowing the &lt;a href=\"Restore%20Mardaneus%27%20Sanity\"&gt;restoring Mardaneus' sanity&lt;/a&gt; quest Geomoe travels with the healers to the &lt;a href=\"Blue%20Boar%20Inn\"&gt;Blue Boar Inn&lt;/a&gt; to help curing the &lt;a href=\"Find%20a%20Solution%20to%20the%20Plague%20Problem%20in%20Rivertown\"&gt;plague&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Rivertown\"&gt;Rivertown&lt;/a&gt;'s &lt;a href=\"poor%20area\"&gt;poor area&lt;/a&gt;. Whilst investigating this, his kin come to take him home to succeed his father. This turns out to be a lie which results in him being &lt;a href=\"Polymorph%20%28Divine%20Divinity%29\"&gt;polymorphed&lt;/a&gt; and trapped in a dungeon by the &lt;a href=\"Black%20Ring\"&gt;Black Ring&lt;/a&gt; to prevent him from joining the &lt;a href=\"Council%20of%20Seven\"&gt;Council of Seven&lt;/a&gt;. Upon his rescue he joined the council and helped &lt;a href=\"Lucian\"&gt;Lucian&lt;/a&gt; rise to Divinity, losing his life in the process when he was slain by the &lt;a href=\"orcs\"&gt;orcs&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Death%20Knight\"&gt;Death Knight&lt;/a&gt;s that had invaded the council alongside &lt;a href=\"Janus%20Ferol\"&gt;Janus Ferol&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "18934", "revid": "49426621", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=18934", "title": "Goemoe's House", "text": " is a house in &lt;a href=\"Aleroth\"&gt;Aleroth&lt;/a&gt;.\nLayout.\nGoemoe's house has a single floor and a small yard. There are two rooms; a central area and a small bedroom with a wooden cupboard where the patient &lt;a href=\"Simon\"&gt;Simon&lt;/a&gt; resides. In the central area is a table with various clutter as well as &lt;a href=\"Fruit\"&gt;fruit&lt;/a&gt;, a &lt;a href=\"Dirk\"&gt;dirk&lt;/a&gt;, and a &lt;a href=\"Mug%20of%20Water%20%28Divine%20Divinity%29\"&gt;mug of water&lt;/a&gt;. Next to the table is a chest, a book about &lt;a href=\"Tanceti\"&gt;Tanceti&lt;/a&gt; and a bookshelf consisting of three sections.\nThe northtern part of the house serves as Goemoe's bedroom, with a Lizard Bed and a bowl of water next to it. Next to a barrel there are a couple of buckets of water. There is also another table, with clutter and an &lt;a href=\"Apple%20%28Divine%20Divinity%29\"&gt;apple&lt;/a&gt; on top of it. Lastly there is a decorative skeleton next to the table.\nOutside of the house is a small fenced yard where a &lt;a href=\"Cow\"&gt;cow&lt;/a&gt; wanders. A &lt;a href=\"Wooden%20Buckler\"&gt;wooden buckler&lt;/a&gt; is found at the corner of the stone fence."}
