{"id": "16098", "revid": "53418829", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=16098", "title": "The Advocate (quest)", "text": "The Advocate is a &lt;a href=\"Quests%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;side quest&lt;/a&gt; in \"\".\nDetailed walkthrough.\nUpon entering the Bloodmoon Island by crossing the fallen bridge, a possessed \"pilgrim\" (close to a \"knight\" and \"bride\") will urge the Godwoken to speak with their master. Their master is located at a south-west part of the Bloodmoon Island. The Advocate will ask the Godwoken to kill the Black Ring troops at the Ancestor tree in middle of the island. If the Godwoken agrees to the deal, they will then receive an expansion of their capacity for source, before completing what the Advocate has asked of them.\nWhile speaking with him it is possible to ask who is behind the Voidwoken. However to be able to receive an answer the Godwoken needs to successfully pass a persuasion check. If passed the Advocate will reveal that the &lt;a href=\"God%20King\"&gt;God King&lt;/a&gt; is behind the Voidwoken attacks, and in doing so, summon a hostile group of Voidwoken.\nAfter the Godwoken has killed the Black Ring troops, the Advocate will reveal the location of the Nameless Isle and move with his servants to the Ancestor tree."}
