{"id": "20175", "revid": "53418829", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=20175", "title": "The Bark's Bite", "text": " is a in \"\".\nDetailed walkthrough.\nAfter using Spirit Vision and placing their hand on the log, the &lt;a href=\"Godwoken\"&gt;Godwoken&lt;/a&gt; witnesses a vision from the perspective of the log, who's spirit used to be an Ancestor Tree. In the vision, the Ancestor Tree passes memories to a small elven child who used to be the daughter of the elf who turned into this Ancestor Tree. She says she will return again tomorrow and leaves. However this is cut short by a man who cuts down the tree.\nThe log's spirit asks the player to make the spirit of this man pay for this and let's the player know where he is.\nCrossing the bridge which leads to and out of the encampment then taking the second turn to the right, you will find three graves, located in the north-west of the barren area below the encampment. Digging the west-most grave and using Spirit Vision will reveal a spirit right next to the grave, and draining his source will complete the quest.\nUpon speaking to the log's spirit again, it will say it instantly knew when you drained the spirit's source and that it is at peace. A source-filled slab of livewood bark slides free from the log and the wounded bark heals, supplying the player with an item called \"Livewood Shield.\""}
