{"id": "6935", "revid": "49426621", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=6935", "title": "The Chest by the Well", "text": "The Chest by the Well is a &lt;a href=\"Original%20Sin%20Quests\"&gt;side quest&lt;/a&gt; in \"\". \nDescription.\nThe chest is located just to the west of the well in Hiberheim, directly north of Haizea from \"&lt;a href=\"The%20Captives%20In%20The%20Crystals\"&gt;The Captives in the Crystals&lt;/a&gt;\". The chest contains a Royal Guard Talisman which can be used to obtain the &lt;a href=\"Winter%20Ring\"&gt;Winter Ring&lt;/a&gt;\nWalkthrough.\nAlternative walkthrough.\nThis method can be used in case the above steps do not work for you past step 5. No special skills required. Tested on Enhanced Edition version 2.0.119.430 (GOG), 23-03-2019."}
{"id": "15018", "revid": "49426621", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=15018", "title": "The Church", "text": " is a &lt;a href=\"Divine%20Divinity%20quests\"&gt;side quest&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Divine%20Divinity\"&gt;Divine Divinity&lt;/a&gt;\".\nWalkthrough.\nUpon entering the &lt;a href=\"Church\"&gt;Church&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Lucian\"&gt;Lucian&lt;/a&gt; saw &lt;a href=\"Ghost%20%28Divine%20Divinity%29\"&gt;Ghosts&lt;/a&gt; attacking a priest and a monk. The priest manages to escape into confession chair, while the monk perishes to the attacking ghosts.\nFurther investigating situation, Lucian finds &lt;a href=\"Father%20Theofolus\"&gt;Father Theofolus&lt;/a&gt; hiding in a secret library of the church. When asked about the current events in the church, Theofolus explains that all happened few days ago; howling and ghostly appearances, and now &lt;a href=\"Father%20Danos\"&gt;Father Danos&lt;/a&gt; was killed. Theofolus describes the howling like someone screaming in pain. Ghosts are appearing out of nowhere as well. Father Theofolus describes Father Danos as a good worker, always doing his tasks on time, unlike &lt;a href=\"Vinny\"&gt;Vinny&lt;/a&gt; who they took within church and was wandering in &lt;a href=\"Rivertown\"&gt;Rivertown&lt;/a&gt;.\nTheofolus suspects desecration being cause of the events in the church, but cannot pinpoint how this desecration was done.\nUpon exiting the confession chair, Lucian sees a boy urinating into wine chest. Suspecting this to be the desecration act, Lucian informs Father Theofolus who is sure this was the act of desecration that angered the spirits of the church.\nAfter this, Theofolus rewards Lucian with gold and experience."}
