{"id": "14457", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=14457", "title": "The Crypt of Lucian", "text": "The Crypt of Lucian is a last resting place of &lt;a href=\"Lucian\"&gt;Lucian&lt;/a&gt; the Divine in 1242 AD. \nBackground.\nAfter the Divine died at the end of Chaos War in 1233 AD, his body was moved to &lt;a href=\"Arx\"&gt;Arx&lt;/a&gt; where &lt;a href=\"Paladin\"&gt;Paladin&lt;/a&gt;s and &lt;a href=\"Magisters\"&gt;Magisters&lt;/a&gt; waged a furious debate over the right to bury their leader's remains. This debate almost escalated into outright bloodshed in the streets where it not for the Bishop &lt;a href=\"Alexandar\"&gt;Alexandar's&lt;/a&gt; intervention. The debate that day was settled with &lt;a href=\"the%20Cathedral\"&gt;the Cathedral&lt;/a&gt; and Crypt being built in Arx, with usage of Source magic to speed up the process, while Magisters gained a new headquarters in Arx.\u00a0\nThe Crypt of Lucian was built by many engineers like Toymaker &lt;a href=\"Sanders\"&gt;Sanders&lt;/a&gt; and supervised by &lt;a href=\"Arhu\"&gt;Lord Arhu&lt;/a&gt;, under the guidance of the Divine to serve as his last resting place. Due to the importance of the place many protections where put in place to deter &lt;a href=\"Godwoken\"&gt;unwanted entities&lt;/a&gt; as well as &lt;a href=\"Black%20Ring\"&gt;Black Ring&lt;/a&gt; cultists from ever laying their hands on Lucian's mortal remains which still held the divine powers.\nThe crypt can be entered by going through &lt;a href=\"the%20Path%20of%20Blood\"&gt;the Path of Blood&lt;/a&gt;. An entrance leading to the &lt;a href=\"Line%20of%20Anquish\"&gt;Line of Anquish&lt;/a&gt; will open beneath the Divine's false coffin should someone succesfully solve the puzzle.\nLayout.\nWhen Godwoken enter the crypt they are met with the last waypoint shrine in the game. Beyond the waypoint shrine lies a coffin of the Divine, which is empty. Further away from the coffin lies an altar with a pipe puzzle where the Godwoken have to lead blessed blood, water and fire to their respective places in order to proceed further.\nEncounters.\nIf the Godwoken had released Karon he will appear near the waypoint shrine and attack them with his undead minions."}
