{"id": "7156", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=7156", "title": "The Godbox", "text": "The Godbox is an artifact that appears in \"\". It's the only vessel capable of containing an immortal being, according to &lt;a href=\"Zandalor\"&gt;Zandalor&lt;/a&gt;.\nBackground.\nIn ancient days, a great evil called the &lt;a href=\"Void%20Dragon\"&gt;Void Dragon&lt;/a&gt; threatened &lt;a href=\"Rivellon\"&gt;Rivellon&lt;/a&gt;. Two great human warriors fought against the dragon and sealed it in this box. After then, two warriors volunteered as the Guardians of the Godbox and kept it closed for eternal times.\nBut one day, &lt;a href=\"Astarte\"&gt;Astarte&lt;/a&gt; was allured by the &lt;a href=\"Trife\"&gt;Trife&lt;/a&gt; and distracted the Guardians. She opened the Godbox mistakenly, and the &lt;a href=\"Void%20Dragon\"&gt;Void Dragon&lt;/a&gt; was set free. After then, Astarte had been fighting with the &lt;a href=\"Void%20Dragon\"&gt;Void Dragon&lt;/a&gt; for ages but the power of the Void was growing bigger and bigger.\nAfter the final battle, Astarte once again seals the Great Evil inside the Godbox and the Guardians lived happily ever after."}
