{"id": "10641", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=10641", "title": "The Murderous Gheist", "text": " is a side &lt;a href=\"Quests%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;quest&lt;/a&gt; received by speaking with either &lt;a href=\"Migo\"&gt;Migo&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Yarrow\"&gt;Magister Yarrow&lt;/a&gt; at &lt;a href=\"Fort%20Joy\"&gt;Fort Joy&lt;/a&gt; in \"\".\nDetailed Walkthrough.\nIf beginning from Magister Yarrow, ascend the fort's ramparts to find her () and speak to her. She will ask if the &lt;a href=\"Godwoken\"&gt;Godwoken&lt;/a&gt; have seen an inmate called Migo. From here head to the beach to the south of &lt;a href=\"Fort%20Joy\"&gt;Fort Joy&lt;/a&gt; and east of the &lt;a href=\"Caverns%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;caverns&lt;/a&gt; where &lt;a href=\"Saheila\"&gt;Saheila&lt;/a&gt; and the elves reside (). Here Migo, now a gheist in a state of &lt;a href=\"Fugue\"&gt;Fugue&lt;/a&gt; can be found, along with several bodies. Approaching Migo at this stage will result in discussion followed by an inevitable battle. Defeating him will result in &lt;a href=\"Migo%27s%20Ring\"&gt;Migo's Ring&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Migo%27s%20Breastplate\"&gt;Migo's Breastplate&lt;/a&gt; being dropped.\nIf one does not want to fight him, they must acquire a yarrow flower before approaching Migo. There are ten flowers on the island, however, three can be obtained before escaping the fort into the &lt;a href=\"Hollow%20Marshes\"&gt;Hollow Marshes&lt;/a&gt;:\nReturn to the beach and approach Migo, offering him the flower. He will calm down and present the Godwoken with his ring. Regardless of the outcome, return (or find) Magister Yarrow and advise her of her father's fate; presenting the ring as proof. She will then make her way down to the beach. If found there, she will reward the player with the &lt;a href=\"Magister%27s%20Key\"&gt;Magister's Key&lt;/a&gt;, completing the quest."}
