{"id": "16431", "revid": "31775388", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=16431", "title": "The Path &amp; the Pilgrimage", "text": " is a &lt;a href=\"books%20and%20notes%20%28Original%20Sin%202%29\"&gt;book&lt;/a&gt; in \"\"."}
{"id": "15653", "revid": "43671602", "url": "https://divinity.fandom.com/wiki?curid=15653", "title": "The Path of Blood", "text": "The Path of Blood is a part of &lt;a href=\"the%20Cathedral\"&gt;the Cathedral&lt;/a&gt; of &lt;a href=\"Arx\"&gt;Arx&lt;/a&gt;.\nBackground.\nBuilt and designed by Toymaker &lt;a href=\"Sanders\"&gt;Sanders&lt;/a&gt; and Lord &lt;a href=\"Arhu\"&gt;Arhu&lt;/a&gt; who oversaw the construction. The Path of Blood is a central part of the Arx Cathedral and the first line of defence used to protect &lt;a href=\"Lucian\"&gt;Lucian&lt;/a&gt;s body. Besides its defensive purpose, the statue is used as an idol by worshippers of the Divine, to which they pray during the holiday known as Lucian's Day in order to find out whether they are pure or not. However most priest discourage this knowing that those who walk the Path and are \"not free from sin\" are met with swift death. In spite of the priests warnings and the reputation there are few pilgrims every year who attempt to walk the Path, since there are rumours that those who will pass the judgement, will become the next Divine. \nThose that do enter the Path are met with the Simulacrum of Lucian, a golden statue of the Divine turned towards the entrance gate which locks itself the moment a visitor enters the Path. In order to progress the visitor must adress the Simulacrum. The statue will ask them whether they are ready to answer its four questions. Should visitor fail to meet the criteria or attempt to lie about their sins, they will be called Impure and killed. Should the visitor pass all the questions, without lying, they will be called \"Pure\", receive Lucian's blessing and an entrance to the &lt;a href=\"the%20Crypt%20of%20Lucian\"&gt;the Crypt of Lucian&lt;/a&gt; will reveal itself and open.\nPassing the Path of Blood.\nThere are two ways of passing the Path of Blood and gaining access to the Crypt of Lucian.\nThe Pure Path.\nThe Pure Path revolves around answering the questions asked by the Simulacrum of Lucian. In order to pass its judgement one must meet the following criteria pertaining to the questions. Should Godwoken release &lt;a href=\"Deathfog\"&gt;Deathfog&lt;/a&gt; upon Arx, as part of the quest &lt;a href=\"Deathfog%20Rising\"&gt;Deathfog Rising&lt;/a&gt;, they will all be automatically marked as Impure thus failing the Path of Blood and making it impossible to pass it via Pure method.\nNote: It is possible to achieve this route by having a mercenary answer the questions.\nUsing the Amulet.\nThe Godwoken has to gain the &lt;a href=\"Source%20Amulet\"&gt;Source Amulet&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Scroll%20of%20Atonement\"&gt;Scroll of Atonement&lt;/a&gt; from Toy Maker &lt;a href=\"Sanders\"&gt;Sanders&lt;/a&gt; as part of the Wisdom of the Keeper sub-quest for the &lt;a href=\"Hammerfall\"&gt;Hammerfall&lt;/a&gt; main quest. "}
